title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate. Cook and stir ground beef and onion until beef is brown; drain. Stir in salt and pepper.
Spread in pie plate; sprinkle with cheese.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted in center comes out clean (about 30 minutes).
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting. Refrigerate any leftovers.

title: sour cream potato salad
directions: Cut eggs in half and remove yolks.
Mash yolks and blend with mayonnaise, sour cream and mustard.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Blend shortening, sugar, egg and milk.
Gradually stir in combined ingredients.
Place small balls of dough on cookie sheet. Flatten and bake 5 to 7 minutes at 400°.

title: hamburger pie
directions: In a large skillet, cook ground meat and onion until meat is browned and onion is tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in beans, soup, water, salt and pepper.
Turn mixture into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.

title: butterscotch dumplings
directions: Make a syrup of the brown sugar, water and butter.
Mix remaining dry ingredients and add enough milk to make a stiff dough.
Drop rounded tablespoons of dumpling dough into boiling syrup.
Boil until done, 12 to 15 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: lavender shortbread
directions: *Put a few lavender buds in a sealed jar with powdered sugar for a day.

title: nacho pie
directions: Place rolls in 9-inch round pie plate.
All points should go toward center.
Press into plate.
Sprinkle chips over crust (half).
Top with mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese and remaining chips.

title: special k delights
directions: Measure corn syrup and sugar in large saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring, until sugar is dissolved and mixture bubbles.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter.
Add cereal and raisins; stir until well coated.
Press mixture evenly and firmly into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Let stand until cool.

title: instant hot cocoa
directions: Mix well. Sift sugar. Mix. Store in airtight container.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, seasoning and 1/2 French fried onions.
Pour into 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Sprinkle remaining cheese and French fried onions in diagonal rows across top.
Bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over low heat.
Blend in flour, salt and
pepper.
Add milk all at once.
Cook quickly, stirring constantly,
until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Remove sauce from
heat.
(Add
cheese
or
other flavorings at this point,
if so
desired.)
Add
onions
and potatoes to sauce. Return to heat and cook until hot.

title: pear bread
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, vanilla, vegetable oil and pears together. Add dry ingredients.
Put into two loaf pans and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: meat loaf no. 2
directions: Shape in loaf and bake in loaf pan or iron skillet at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Just before it is completely done, you may sprinkle some catsup over it.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Boil first 5 ingredients for exactly 2 minutes (medium-high). Add vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal. Stir in first mixture and quickly drop by tablespoons on wax paper or foil. If mixture gets too thick, add 1 to 2 tablespoons milk.

title: whatever cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
While cake is still hot, punch holes in top with fork.
Pour entire can Eagle Brand milk over top of cake.
Follow with caramel, then fudge topping.
Set and cool. After cooling, add coconut.
Then add Cool Whip to cover top. Refrigerate until served.
You can omit coconut, if desired.
Also add nuts.

title: biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together. Cut in shortening until fine. Pour in milk and knead lightly. Round up on a floured surface. Roll out or pat out until about 1/2-inch thick. Cut with biscuit cutter. Place in baking pan. Bake for 10 minutes at 450° (preheated oven). Brush tops with melted butter.

title: ramen salad
directions: Crush Ramen in package.
Boil in 2 cups water until tender. Drain.
Blanch in cold water.
Add seasoning packet and mix well. Add vegetables and Italian dressing.
Chill.

title: meat loaf pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Bake meat loaf at 375° for 1/2 hour. Put mashed potatoes and cheese on meat loaf and bake until cheese is melted.

title: chicken and rice(spanish)
directions: Cut up chicken as for frying. Put olive oil in deep frying pan and heat gradually. Add garlic cloves. When garlic begins to color, lay in chicken and turn several times until golden brown all over; add peppers, cut in strips, and onions, sliced. Continue cooking until onions are colored. Add tomatoes, skinned and quartered, and rice; add water or stock sufficient to cover. Salt to taste and simmer until tender. Add more stock if necessary.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Mix Bisquick and milk until soft dough forms. Roll 1/2 inch thick. Spread sausage over dough. Roll like jelly roll. Freeze for 1 hour. Slice into 48 slices. Bake 8 to 10 minutes until golden brown.

title: tangy tomato salad dressing
directions: Combine cornstarch and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Add vegetable juice.
Cook and stir until thickened plus 1 minute.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill.
Makes 1 1/3 cups.

title: jackie's pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Add corn syrup, eggs, evaporated milk, pecan pieces and milk.
Mix well.
Pour in pastry crust. Bake at 375° for 50 minutes (can double everything and pour into 3 bought crusts; bake at 350°).

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Cook wiener pieces and other ingredients 1 hour in oven at 250°, stirring often.
Serve hot in chafing dish with decorative toothpicks as servers.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken until done. Save the broth. Debone chicken and put in bowl. Saute onion and pepper with stick of butter.
Pour into bowl with chicken and add soup, Velveeta cheese and spaghetti which has been cooked in chicken broth.
Mix all together.
Put in baking dish and bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Sprinkle 2/3 cup of the coconut into bottom of crust; set aside.
Spread remaining 2/3 cup of coconut in an even layer in a shallow pan.
Toast at 350° for 7 to 12 minutes, or until lightly browned, stirring frequently.
Cool.

title: pumpkin roll cake
directions: Beat eggs at high speed with mixer.
Beat in sugar, pumpkin and lemon juice.
Add flour, baking powder, cinnamon, ginger and nutmeg.
Mix well.
Spread into greased and floured jelly pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Turn out onto towel with 10x sugar on it.
Put 10x sugar on top of cake.
Roll towel and cake up.
Let cool and unroll.
Spread with filling and roll.

title: chess squares
directions: Combine margarine, cake mix and 1 egg in mixer bowl; mix well. Press into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Combine confectioners sugar, 2 eggs and cream cheese in mixer bowl; mix until smooth.
Spread over cake mix layer.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Cool on wire rack. Cut into squares.

title: peanut butter chocolate bars
directions: Beat peanut butter, butter, brown sugar, white sugar and vanilla in a large bowl until creamy.
Beat in eggs and flour. Stir in 3/4 cup morsels.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.
Remove from oven; immediately sprinkle with remaining morsels.
Let stand for 5 minutes; spread. Sprinkle colored sugar over melted chocolate.
Cool in pan on wire rack.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: busy day casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Pour beef in crock pot, add potatoes, carrots, peas, and onion.
Mix tomato soup and water. Pour into crock pot.
Cook 6 -8 hours on low or 4-6 hours on high.

title: coconut - caramel pie
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Add coconut and pecans; cook until golden brown, stirring frequently.
Set mixture aside. Combine cream cheese and sweetened condensed milk; beat until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping.
Layer 1/4 of cream cheese mixture in each shell.
Drizzle 1/2 of caramel topping on each pie.
Sprinkle 1/4 of coconut mixture evenly over each.
Repeat layers with remaining ingredients; cover and freeze until firm. Let frozen pie stand at room temperature 5 minutes before slicing. Yields two 9-inch pies.

title: popovers
directions: Mix all ingredients, one egg at a time.
Fill buttered tins halfway.
Bake 15 minutes on 400°, then lower heat to 350° for 20 more minutes.

title: punch
directions: Boil 13 cups water. Add sugar and jello. Stir until dissolved then cool.
Add pineapple juice and lemon juice and freeze in ziploc baggies. When ready to use add ginger ale.

title: amish chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix well and chill for 1 hour.
Bake at 350°.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat slowly; spoon off fat. Add next 5 ingredients. Simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Cook noodles until tender; drain and rise. Combine remaining ingredients except the Mozzarella cheese. Place half the noodles in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Spread with half the cottage cheese filling. Add half the Mozzarella cheese and half the meat sauce. Repeat layers. Bake at 375° about 30 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes before cutting in squares; filling will set slightly. Makes 12 or so servings.

title: italian bread crumbs for fried chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Dip chicken in bread crumb mixture.
Bake in oven at 350°.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix the soup, milk and flour in large pan and cook.
Add the cheese to the soup mixture, plus the mixed vegetables and chunk chicken.
Stir well; heat through.
Pour into pan; bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fruit loaf
directions: Soak over night.
Next day, mix in 1 cup self rising flour. Bake at 375 degrees.
Check after 3/4 hour, could cook up to 1-1/4 hours.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Place all ingredients in covered casserole dish.
Bake 2 hours at 350°.
May cook in crock-pot on low, 3 to 4 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: vichyssoise
directions: In medium saucepan, melt butter.
Add leeks and saute until soft.
Add chicken broth; bring to boil.
Add potatoes.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes (or until potatoes are tender).
Place 1/3 of the soup in blender.
Add 1/2 cup skim milk.
Puree.
Repeat until all the soup is pureed.
Return to saucepan.
Stir in nutmeg and cayenne.
Heat until warm or chill.
Garnish with extra leek slices.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Saute the green pepper, onion, olives, garlic powder and chili powder in the margarine.
Mix together the soups and chicken and add to the first mixture. Combine well.
Cook the spaghetti and place in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Spread sauce on top. Cover with the cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: hawaiian banana bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to flour mixture, stirring until just moistened.
Spoon batter into two greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until wooden pick comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes, remove from pan and cool on racks.
Yields 2 loaves.
Freezes well.

title: chocolate syrup brownies
directions: In a bowl, cream together butter, sugar and eggs until very creamy and well blended.
Add salt.
Stir in flour, mixing to blend well.
Add chocolate syrup, vanilla and chopped nuts.
Turn mixture into well-greased and lightly floured 9-inch square pan. Smooth top.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes or until a stick inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on wire rack but loosen cake at edges.
Cut into squares.
Makes 16 to 18 brownies.

title: meat pies
directions: Combine meat, chopped onions, yogurt, pine nuts, lemon juice and seasonings.
Shape dough patties in triangles or rounds, putting small amount of mixture in center.
Fold and pinch, pat with oil and put in oiled baking tray.
Bake at 350° until bottom is brown.
Then put on top shelf to brown on top.
Yields 3 to 4 dozen pies.

title: dad's pork chops
directions: Place all the ingredients except the chops in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange the chops on top of the rice mixture.
Cover pan with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken

title: fig jam
directions: Combine figs, sugar and Jell-O.
Allow to sit for 30 minutes. Cook on medium heat until it comes to a boil.
Cook for 10 minutes. Then let it cool for 30 minutes and place in jars.

title: breakfast bun
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add balance of ingredients, except raisins and English walnuts.
Bake in 2 large cake pans.
Before putting in oven, put drops of butter all over them.
Next cover thickly with brown sugar.
Drop a few seedless raisins and English walnuts on top.
Raisins can be omitted.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: chicken cornelia
directions: Put fryer legs in 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.
Mix soup with milk.
Pour soup mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with rice or noodles. Serves 4.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar, eggs and carrots, then add flour, baking soda and cinnamon.
Add nuts.
Bake in floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: frozen strawberry dessert
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water in bowl.
Stir in strawberries, pineapple, bananas and pecans.
Pour half the gelatin mixture in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Chill, covered, for 30 to 50 minutes or until set.
Prepare cheesecake using package directions.
Spread over congealed gelatin.
Cover with remaining gelatin mixture.
Chill until set.
Yield: 15 servings.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water.
Stir cranberry sauce until smooth; blend into gelatin with orange rind.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in diced orange and pineapple. Chill until firm.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package and drain. Mix together the broccoli, mushroom soup and cheese.
Place in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix together stuffing, butter and water. Spread on top of broccoli mixture.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: vegetable beef barley soup
directions: Cook hamburger and drain off fat. Set aside. Stir-fry the chopped celery and onions in the oil. Add 3 cups water and barley and boil 15 minutes.
Add cooked hamburger, carrots with their water and tomatoes. Add more water (3 cups), if needed.
Heat, then add beef base 1 tablespoon at a time until broth has a good flavor. Heat and serve.

title: margarita
directions: Mix all ingredients in a blender.
Blend in ice to the consistency you want.

title: barbecued onions
directions: Parboil onions for 4 to 5 minutes.
Drain and put in a buttered, shallow, 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix catsup, water, vinegar, salt and pepper and spread over onions.
Sprinkle mixture with brown sugar and bacon.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Stir together flour, soda and salt; set aside.
Measure margarine, sugar and brown sugar into large mixing bowl.
Beat until well blended.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix until combined.
Stir in Rice Krispies and chocolate morsels.
Drop level spoon on greased sheet.
Bake on 350° about 10 minutes.
Cool about 1 minute before removing from sheet.
Yields about 6 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine
chicken,
onion,
bell
pepper, celery, mayonnaise, broth,
salt and pepper.
Place 4 slices of cubed bread in bottom of 3 quart casserole dish and spread chicken mixture over.
Beat eggs
into
cup
milk
and pour over chicken mixture.
Put other 4 pieces of bread cubes over and refrigerate overnight or freeze until ready to serve.
When ready, mix mushroom soup
with 1/2
can of milk and heat until lumps are gone.
Pour over casserole.
Cover with grated cheese and bake about 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Makes 10 servings.
Freezes well.

title: polish stir-fry
directions: In Teflon pan or wok, place all the ingredients.
Saute until onions clarify, about 30 to 40 minutes, on medium heat.
Serve.

title: topsy-turvy pie
directions: In a large skillet, cook and stir ground meat, onion and green pepper until meat is browned.
Spoon off drippings.
Stir in tomato sauce, salt, chili powder and olives.
Spread in a 9-inch pie pan.

title: beef stew
directions: In a plastic bag, combine flour and 1 teaspoon salt.
Add meat cubes, a few at a time, shaking to coat.
In a large saucepan, brown meat, half at a time, in hot oil.
Return all meat to saucepan; add onion, garlic and thyme.
Stir in vegetable juice, bouillon, hot pepper sauce and 1 cup water.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover; simmer for 1 1/4 hours for beef or until meat is nearly tender.
Stir in potatoes, celery and carrot.
Cover; simmer 30 minutes more. Skim off fat. Serves 6.

title: country granola
directions: Combine oats, coconut and nuts in large pan (11 x 15). Bake 20 minutes at 300°, stirring occasionally. Melt butter in medium-size saucepan. Add brown sugar and honey. Remove from heat; add vanilla. Add wheat germ to oats. Drizzle with butter mixture. Toss. Bake at 350° for 5 minutes. Add raisins. Toss again. Press mixture into pan. Bake additional 5 to 7 minutes. Cool. Store in airtight container.

title: butter frosting
directions: Beat until fluffy the Crisco and butter.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: fowler's favorite salad
directions: Pour the boiling water over the gelatin, flavoring, cream cheese and marshmallows.
Mix thoroughly until well blended and then chill until it starts to congeal.
Then add crushed pineapple, carrots and pecans.
Lastly, add whipped cream and fold into the mixture.
Pour into a 9-inch square pan and chill until firm.
Cut in squares and serve on lettuce.

title: chicken puffs
directions: In saucepan, combine chicken broth, salt, salad oil, cayenne pepper, celery seed and parsley flakes.
Add Worcestershire sauce. Add flour all at once and stir rapidly over low heat until mixture leaves sides of pan and forms a ball.
Remove from heat until mixture is smooth and shiny.
Add chicken and almonds.
Blend well and drop on greased cookie sheet.
Make them small.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes until light brown.
These freeze well.
Reheat at 250° for 10 minutes.

title: spinach quiche bites
directions: Cover bottom and 1/4-inch of sides of greased 9 x 13-inch pan with rolls.
Flatten out the crescent rolls and press against bottom of pan to form a flat crust for quiche; set aside.

title: pear preserves
directions: Make syrup of liquid and sugar.
Add fruit to partly cooled syrup and bring gently to boil.
Boil rapidly until clear and tender.
Cool rapidly.
Stand in syrup to plump.
Pack fruit in sterilized jar and add reheated syrup to within 1/2-inch of top. Seal immediately.

title: steamed crabs
directions: Put rack in pot.
Add vinegar and beer.
Rack should be above the liquid.
With crab tongs, place crabs in pot.
Sprinkle 1/2 handful of seasoning mix on top.
Place lid on, turn high heat until steam starts to escape well.
Hold lid on so crabs do not get out.
Turn heat down and steam until crabs turn a bright red. Take crabs out and put in a large paper bag.
Each layer of crabs sprinkle a handful of Seasoning Mix until all crabs are in the bag.
Close bag loosely and let sit 10 minutes.
Shake bag and dump on table and turn all crabs, backs up.

title: swedish potato wedges
directions: Peel and cut potatoes into wedges.
Arrange in single layer in a large, buttered baking dish.
Pour butter over potatoes.
Combine shredded cheese, paprika, salt and bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake at 425° for 35 minutes or until tender and golden brown, basting occasionally.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients; drop by tablespoon.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: pork tenderloins with spicy chinese sauce
directions: Mix soy sauce, hoisin, oil and sugar in large plastic zip lock bag.
Add pork and marinate at least one hour or overnight.
Pre heat oven to 500°.
Line a small roasting pan with foil; spray a cake cooling rack with Pam and place pork on rack.
Roast 9-10 minutes.
Turn meat over and roast 9-10 minutes more.
More time may be needed if the pork is thick.
Test with meat thermometer. It should register 148°.

title: chicken by alice
directions: Arrange chicken in a baking dish.
Pour dressing over the chicken.
Mix preserves and soup mix and pour over chicken. Bake at 350° until chicken is done.

title: orange-glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Peel sweet potatoes, wash them and quarter.
Place in boiling water and cook until soft.
Place in buttered pan.
Meanwhile, simmer orange juice, sugar, cornstarch, salt, lemon peel and butter until it thickens up to a nice syrup, about 5-inch.
Pour this syrup over sweet potatoes and bake, covered, in the oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Baste often.

title: mom's chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Remove skin and bones from chicken.
Combine soup, butter, mayonnaise, lemon juice, curry powder and water chestnuts in mixing bowl.
Place a layer of chicken, broccoli and half of the soup mixture in a large casserole.
Repeat until all ingredients are used.
Sprinkle slivered almonds on top.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through and bubbly. Serve over rice.
Yields 12 servings.

title: apricot nectar cooler
directions: Combine nectar, yogurt and lemon juice in blender and mix well.
Pour into chilled glass and garnish with mint.
If thicker drink is desired, freeze apricot nectar until almost firm before combining with remaining ingredients.
Makes 1 cup.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill at least 4 hours before serving. Eat with crackers or place in Hawaiian bread that has had center carved out.
Eat with bread.

title: swiss steak
directions: Trim fat off the steak; cut in pieces.
Roll in flour, salt and pepper to taste.
Brown in cooking oil.
Put in cooker and alternate steak, onions and peppers, then add tomatoes on top. Cook on medium heat for about 1 hour or until tender.
Stir often.

title: velveeta nacho cheese dip
directions: Cut cheese into cubes.
Pour desired amount of salsa in microwave 3 minutes on High.
Stir.
Microwave 3 more minutes. Stir.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: dean's elephant soup
directions: Prepare elephant by cutting into small bite size pieces. Season and cover with beef broth.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Continue cooking about 3 weeks.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar and milk in saucepan and bring to boil. Boil 3 minutes. Add peanut butter and marshmallow fluff. Stir until combined. Place in a 9 x 9-inch square baking dish lined with waxed paper. Cut before fudge cools completely.

title: ratatouille
directions: Saute eggplant and zucchini in oil in Dutch oven about 10 minutes.
Remove and set aside.
Saute onions and green peppers, 5 minutes, until tender, stirring occasionally.
Add tomatoes, parsley, garlic, eggplant and zucchini.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Simmer for 25 minutes, covered, until vegetables are tender and most liquid has disappeared.
(To reduce liquid, remove cover and continue to cook.)
Serve hot or cold.

title: red flannel hash
directions: Fry pork until crisp.
Remove pieces and retain as a garnish. Combine beets, potatoes, salt, pepper, corned beef, onions and milk.
Spread mixture in skillet in which pork was fried.
Brown slowly, then turn and brown on other side.
Serve with pork on top.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Place Doritos in dish. Heat other ingredients.
Pour over chips.
Top with cheese.
Melt cheese.
Serve.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into patties.
Pour 1/2 cup oil in frypan and heat.
Form patties and fry in oil until brown on both sides.
Use left over oil to make gravy.

title: sweet and sour chicken and rice
directions: Roll chicken in skillet and fry until done and tender.
Cut into bite size chunks.
In saucepan, cook vegetables until tender by steaming with 1 cup of water.
When chicken is done, drain vegetables of any remaining water.
Add chicken to vegetables.
Add sauce.
Add 1/2 cup of hot water if needed to thin.
Add pineapple chunks; simmer 10 minutes on low heat.
Pour over cooked rice.

title: lemon crunch pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco together. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add flavoring, then flour, 1/2 cup at a time, beating after each addition. Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: perogy casserole(meatless lasagne)
directions: In 9 x 13-inch or 7 x 11-inch pan, layer 3 noodles.
Blend potatoes, onions, cheese and melted butter.
Layer 1/2 on top of noodles.
Repeat.
Top with noodles.
Spread with 1 tablespoon melted butter.
Cover with foil.
Bake 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes more.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Melt the chocolate chips.
Add egg yolks and a dash of salt. Mix well.
Beat egg whites and 1/2 cup of sugar; beat until stiff. Mix chocolate mixture, egg whites, Cool Whip and vanilla.
Mix together and pour over crumbled angel food cake.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients; bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with toasted French bread slices.

title: hawaiian haystacks
directions: Cook skinless chicken pieces and debone.
Place 3 cans cream of chicken soup and water in pot (or crock-pot).
Add cooked chicken and simmer until heated through, stir occasionally.
Prepare all other ingredients as listed.
To serve, stack the ingredients one on top of each other in order:
rice, Chinese noodles, chicken gravy.
Stack remaining ingredients as desired.

title: taco salad(for lots of people)
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Put in taco seasoning and let cool.
Wash and drain lettuce.
Chop lettuce into big bowl.
Put in cool ground beef, onion, tomatoes and cheese.
Before serving, toss salad.
Crunch up chips; add and stir in taco sauce.

title: tomato-mozzarella salad
directions: Cut cheese 1/4-inch thick in rounds with cookie cutter.
Set aside.
Line serving plate with lettuce.
Arrange tomato slices on lettuce and sprinkle with salt.
Top each tomato with cheese slice.
Spoon dressing over salad.
Serve immediately.

title: slime-a-birthday cake
directions: Step 1:
Make the cake according to the directions on the box. You need to make two 8 or 9-inch layers.

title: creamed tacos
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add chili, beans and Ro-Tel; heat well. Add cheese on top of meat mixture and let melt slowly.
Stir real good.
Just before serving add whipping cream or sour cream.
Serve over crumbled chips.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Break cauliflower into medium size flowerets.
Cook until crisp-tender (10 minutes).
Drain.

title: spinach squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Beat eggs.
Add flour, milk, salt and baking powder; mix.
Add cheese, spinach (drain excess water) and onion.
Pour into pan over melted butter.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool 45 minutes.
Cut into small squares.
Reheat for about 12 to 15 minutes at 350° if necessary.
Squares can be frozen after baking.

title: polish pound cake
directions: Do not preheat oven.
Cream margarine, shortening and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix in flour, salt, milk and water. Fold in flavoring, cherries and pecans.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 45 minutes, or until done.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix thoroughly shortening, butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
(For a softer, rounder cookie, add 1/2 cup flour.)
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown.
Cool slightly before removing from baking sheet.
Yields about 7 dozen.

title: orkney bride cog
directions: Mix well; serve at room temperature.
Serves 200!

title: peach macaroon pie
directions: Fill a 9-inch unbaked pie shell half full with sliced peaches. In bowl, mix rest of ingredients and pour over peaches.
Bake in a 350° oven until golden brown, about 50 to 60 minutes.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: In large bowl, mix flour, sugars, baking soda, salt, shortening, peanut butter, milk, vanilla and egg.
Mix at low speed until stiff dough forms.
Shape into 1 inch balls; roll in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove and immediately top with a candy kiss, pressing down firmly so cookie cracks around edge.
Yield: approximately 4 dozen.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except ginger ale.
Add ale just before serving.
Makes 50 servings.

title: chimichangas
directions: Saute beef and onion.
Remove from heat, add beans, tomato, parsley, salsa, oregano, cumin and half of olives.
Fry each tortilla until crisp. Quickly spoon filling into center of tortilla.
Fold inside and roll up around filling.
Secure with toothpick.
Fry rolls in oil.
Top with olives, cheese, lettuce and tomatoes.

title: sock-it-to-me cake
directions: Mix together brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts. Set aside. Mix together cake mix, sour cream, eggs, oil, sugar and flavoring. Pour half of cake batter into a greased Bundt pan. Put nut mixture on top of batter, then cover this with remaining batter. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans, pimento and chestnuts.
Then mix with undiluted soup.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Sprinkle onions on top.
Bake at 325° until hot and bubbly.

title: cornbread pie
directions: Stir until blended; pour over casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash; drain well and mash.
Add soup, sour cream, carrots, pimento and carrots.
Mix butter and cornbread mix.
Line bottom of pan with stuffing mixture.
Reserve 1 cup to sprinkle on top of casserole.
Add squash mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
This dish freezes well.

title: marshmallow fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: filet mignon roast
directions: If you want, you can turn the ends under to keep thickness equal.
Preheat the oven to 450°.
Season the meat by rubbing it with garlic and sprinkling it with fresh ground pepper.
Place filet in shallow pan and place in oven for 33 to 40 minutes for medium rare.
Remove and let meat "rest" for 20 minutes before carving.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Melt all ingredients together.
Serve with chips.
In place of chili you can use sausage.

title: applesauce spice cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs well.
Add applesauce with soda added to it.
Sift and add spices, salt and flour.
Add the floured raisins and nutmeats.
Bake in greased loaf pan in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry ice(fat-free)
directions: Place strawberries in blender or food processor container fitted with steel blade; cover.
Blend until smooth.

Microwave marshmallows and milk in large mixing bowl on High for 1 to 2 minutes or until smooth when stirred, stirring after 1 minute. Gradually add strawberries to marshmallow mixture, beating until well blended.
Blend in juice and peel.
Pour into 9-inch square baking pan; freeze at least 2 hours or until almost firm. Coarsely chop mixture; spoon into chilled mixing bowl.
Beat with electric mixer until smooth; freeze 4 to 6 hours or until firm. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: apple cake in a jar
directions: Mix the ingredients together in order given.
Sterilize 7 to 9 wide mouth pint jars and lids.
Grease them with shortening.
Fill jars half full and bake on metal wire rack in oven for 45 minutes at 325°.
As soon as cakes are done remove from oven one at a time. Wipe rims of jars with cloth and put on hot, sterilized lids. Screw down bands and let cool.
Slice and serve with lemon sauce. This cake has one year shelf life.

title: la granpiollis grand marnier sauce
directions: Select a 2-quart mixing bowl that will rest snugly on top of a slightly larger saucepan filled with water and bring to a boil. Put yolk and a half cup of sugar in the bowl and beat vigorously and thoroughly with a wire whisk or electric portable mixer, making sure that you scrape around the inside and bottom of the bowl with the mixer.
Place the mixing bowl over the saucepan but not in the water and continue beating for 10 minutes until yolks are quite thick.
Remove the bowl from the saucepan and stir in half of the Amaretto.
Let the sauce cool.
Refrigerate to cool thoroughly. Beat the cream with remaining sugar until almost stiff.
Fold cream in sauce.
Stir in remaining Amaretto.
This will make 10 to 12 servings.

title: u.s.  senate bean soup
directions: Wash beans and soak overnight.
Rinse and add water to make 5 quarts.
Add ham bone and simmer 2 hours on low heat.
Add vegetables and simmer 1 hour more.
Remove bone, leaving meat in soup.
Season as desired with salt and pepper.
Makes about 4 1/2 quarts.

title: hamburger surprise
directions: In
large bowl, mix the hamburger, onion, pepper, eggs, salt and pepper to taste.
Then make patties the size you want and fry these
done;
drain and place in baking dish.
Pour 2 cans of cream of mushroom soup or any soup you like.
Bake for 20
minutes or
until	the soup is bubbly.
(Cream of chicken soup
is good.)
The
sauce	this
makes goes great on mashed potatoes.

title: mother's divinity
directions: Boil sugar, water and Karo until it reaches the crackle stage.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Combine first 11 ingredients in a stockpot.
Bring to a boil, lower heat and simmer for 1 hour covered. Combine ground beef, chicken and sausage in a saucepan. Cook until done and add to tomato mixture.
Simmer for another 20 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix first three ingredients together.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tony danza's pasta dish
directions: Boil capellini while preparing sauce.
Saute garlic in oil until lightly brown.
Add chopped tomatoes until heated.
Then add arugula and cook for just a few minutes.
Add strained clam juice and cook for several minutes.
Add clams and simmer.
Toss together with drained capellini.
Mix well and serve warm.

title: w~c~c hot chicken salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients except potato chips, which are sprinkled on top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
May be made ahead and reheated to heat through and crisp the topping.

title: puffy corn fritters
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Blend milk with egg.
Add gradually to dry ingredients.
Stir in corn and drop from tablespoon into deep fat, heated to 375°.
Fry until golden brown, 4 to 8 minutes, depending upon the size.
Drain on absorbent towel and serve.
Makes 16 to 18 fritters.

title: yummy chicken
directions: Mix flour, salt, pepper and thyme in a plastic bag.
Shake chicken to coat well.
Brown the chicken in butter and remove to casserole dish.
Add green onions and mushrooms to frying pan. Cover and simmer for 3 minutes.
Add to casserole dish.
Mix lemon juice, sugar, salt and apple juice.
Pour over chicken and bake covered at 325° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Mix well the shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift together the dry ingredients.
Mix in pecans, dates and cherries.
Drop with teaspoon about 2 inches apart onto lightly greased baking sheet. Bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 300°.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: cheesy vegetable casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine vegetables, mayonnaise, onion and cheese. Pour into buttered dish.
Top with bread crumbs. Bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: orange delight salad
directions: Drain oranges.
Add water to make 2 cups of liquid and boil. Add jello and stir, then stir in sherbet and ice cream until all is melted.
Add orange sections and pour into 1 1/2-quart mold.

title: sweet and sour spareribs
directions: Combine sugar and juice.
Pour over salted ribs and bake in 300° oven until tender, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Combine melted butter and crumbs.
Beat in peanut butter and sugar.
Spread on ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and spread over top; let set.
Keep covered.

title: plantation chicken
directions: Saute the celery, onion and green pepper. Add the soups, pimento and cheese.
Heat and stir until melted. Add the ham, chicken and noodles.
Cover with buttered bread crumbs. Bake 30 minutes at a medium heat.

title: taco salad dip
directions: Spread bean dip on bottom of dish.
Mix taco seasoning and sour cream together.
Add a little salt and pepper.
Spread over bean dip.
Add your toppings in the following order: onions (diced), tomatoes (diced), olives (sliced) and shredded cheese.

title: "rattlesnake" chicken
directions: Saute garlic, red pepper, jalapenos and green onions in the butter.
Add spices, then slowly add milk and lemon juice, simmer until thickened.
Add Parmesan cheese, stir until blended.
Add noodles (cooked according to package instructions) and chicken breasts, serve immediately.
Have the fire extinguisher near! Just kidding.
It is hot and spicy though.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta until tender; drain and cool.
Add tomatoes and cucumber.
Mix dressing and Salad Supreme; add to pasta mixture.

title: pumpkin crunch cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and pour into a greased 13X9-inch pan. Evenly sprinkle cake mix over pumpkin mixture.
Sprinkle pecans over cake mix.
Thinly slice margarine over pecans, covering entire top of cake.
Bake at 350 for 50 minutes.

title: tropical paradise(method:  dutch oven)
directions: Thoroughly grease Dutch oven with butter or margarine.
Peel bananas; cut them in halves lengthwise.
Arrange banana halves, side by side, in layers in greased Dutch oven.
Combine orange juice and brown sugar; pour over bananas.
Mix together the coconut and bread crumbs; sprinkle on top of bananas.
Bake for approximately 20 minutes, until bananas are tender and coconut is brown.
Serve immediately.
Serves 12.

title: milk chocolate bar cake
directions: Bake the cake mix as directed in three separate 8 in. cake pans.
Cool for 10 min.
Beat cream cheese, powdered sugar and sugar until creamy.
Chop four candy bars and add to cream cheese icing.
Add cool whip to mixture.
Spread between layers of cake, top and sides.
Chop remaining candy bars and sprinkle on the top of the cake.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: lillian's potato casserole
directions: In a small bowl, mix soup, salt and paprika.
In a greased 2-quart baking dish, arrange potatoes (sliced in layers). Sprinkle with cheese.
Spoon soup mixture over cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake 45 minutes at 400°.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: mexican salsa
directions: Food processor will come in very handy.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix well and form into 3 long rolls.
Wrap in aluminum foil and place in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chicken-pecan quiche
directions: Combine flour, 1 cup shredded cheese, chopped pecans, salt and paprika.
Stir in the oil.
Press in the bottom and up the sides of a 9-inch quiche dish.
Prick bottom and sides of crust with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Set aside.
Combine eggs, sour cream, mayonnaise and chicken broth in a medium bowl, stirring well.
Stir in chicken, remaining cheese, onion, dillweed and hot sauce.
Pour into prepared crust.
Top with pecan halves. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until a knife inserted comes out clean.

title: beef noodles
directions: Put beef stew meat, dry soup mix and mushroom soup in slow cooker.
Cook all day.
Shred meat into small pieces.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and melted butter together.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar and place on top of cake batter mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onion, then drain. Combine all ingredients and simmer until done.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Mix together the cake mix, eggs and the butter.
Spread in greased
and
floured
9 x 11-inch pan.
Mix powdered sugar and cream
cheese
and
layer on top of cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: shrimp alfredo
directions: Cook noodles by directions and drain.
Combine all ingredients and put in large casserole.
Top with onion rings.
Seal with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Put bones with salt, whole onion, celery leaves and parsley in large pan and cover with 3 to 4 cups cold water.
Simmer for 2 hours.
Cool, remove vegetables and refrigerate.
When cold, remove fat.
Heat stock and add vegetables.
Stewing beef or chuck can be added.
Simmer 1 hour.
Add seasonings to taste.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Place 1/2 crumbs in greased baking dish; alternate layers of asparagus, egg and cheese sauce and top with remaining crumbs. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: watermelon wally
directions: In a small bowl, combine the sugar, rum and lime juice.
Place the watermelon in a serving dish and pour the rum mixture over all.
Cover and chill for 2 to 3 hours.
Serves 6.

title: barbecued pork chops in a skillet
directions: Flour chops lightly
in
flour,
salt and pepper.
Heat cooking oil.
Brown
pork chops on both sides, turning to make sure of an even brown.
Remove chops from cooking oil.
Remove cooking oil from
skillet.
Add
cup water.
Add barbecue sauce and chops.
Cover
and
cook for 30 to 40 minutes over a low fire.
Turn chops occasionally to make sure that the sauce penetrates the chops.
Serves 5 to 7.

title: mom's soup
directions: Cut up potatoes, carrots and onions.
Add just enough water to cook, season with salt.
Cook on medium-high heat until vegetables are tender.
Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Add meat, beans and tomatoes.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: baked salmon filets(serves 4)
directions: Place salmon in shallow nonstick (or lightly oiled metal) baking dish.
Mix together mustard, lemon juice, green onion, chopped cilantro, hot pepper sauce and white pepper.
Arrange evenly over salmon, spreading to cover top surface with spatula. Sprinkle evenly with bread crumbs.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 10 minutes.
Add wine to corners of pan (not on top of fish). Continue baking 5 minutes, or until fish begins to flake when tested with a fork.
Serve immediately garnished with cilantro sprigs and lemon slices.

title: kings ranch chicken
directions: Bake chicken until tender; keep stock and dice chicken.
Line bottom and sides of a large casserole with tortillas.
Sprinkle with some broth; add a layer of undiluted soup and sprinkle about half of the chicken, onions, cheese and chili powder.
Add a layer of tortillas and repeat until it's all gone.
Bake at 300° for about 1 hour.
Serves a large group.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together well.
Add eggs, one at a time, mix well after each.
Add milk and flour.
Beat thoroughly. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: bourbon sweet potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes; rinse well.
Boil until almost done, not "gooky" soft, but firm.
Peel and slice potatoes into a 9-inch pan, spreading evenly.
Sliced potatoes can be stacked on one edge, if necessary.
Crumble butter and sugar together until well mixed.
Sprinkle/distribute evenly over top of all potatoes.
Bake at 375°, uncovered, until it bubbles, approximately 30 to 45 minutes.

title: potato-broccoli-cheese soup
directions: In a large stockpot, mix together chicken broth, chicken bouillon and gravy. Stir together over medium heat until gravy is incorporated into broth and bouillon cubes are dissolved. Increase heat and bring mixture to a boil. Add potatoes, onion flakes and pepper. Cook for about 5 minutes and then add broccoli pieces. Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until potatoes are fork tender. Turn heat to low, dip out about 1 cup of mixture and place in bowl.
Allow to cool slightly.
When slightly cool, add evaporated milk to bowl. (This keeps the milk from curdling when it hits the hot soup.)
Stir together and then add back to the boiler.
Add cheese. Increase heat until mixture is at a slow boil, stirring constantly until cheese is melted through.

title: canadian war cake
directions: Mix sugar, crisco, butter, spices, salt, raisins and boil 5 minutes.
Let cool.
Add 4 c. sifted flour.
Add a heaping tsp. of soda dissolved in 2 Tbsp. warm water.
Bake at 375° until toothpick comes out clean.
About 30-45 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together the first 3 ingredients, then add the eggs and vanilla; mix together the next five ingredients.
Add chocolate chips and grated Hershey bar.
Add nuts.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 6 minutes at 375°.
Use dough in golf ball size and shape, place 2 inches apart.
Makes 24 dozen.

title: fried pie crust
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, sugar and salt into shortening and mix well.
Add 1/2 cup buttermilk (with soda added to it).
Mix all well.
Roll out and cut round with a saucer.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa for 1 minute.
Add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.

title: tortellini salad
directions: Cook tortellini.
Mix all ingredients together.
Use about 1/2 bottle of dressing to start.
Add more, if needed.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Cut Twinkies in half lengthwise. Place in bottom of 13 x 9-inch dish. Layer bananas on top of Twinkies. Prepare pudding according to package directions and pour on top of bananas. Top with well drained pineapple and Cool Whip.
Sprinkle nuts and coconut on top. Keep cold.

title: cow's tongue
directions: Put water to boil with some salt.
When boiling, put in the tongue and cook for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Take it out and peel off the skin and chop meat into small pieces.
In a skillet, add oil, onion, garlic and tomato.
Saute for 5 minutes, then add meat and peas on top of sauce.
Let cook for 5 to 10 minutes just to make sure meat is done.

title: marie's drop sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and shortening.
Add remaining ingredients gradually.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°.

title: cranberry pecan conserve
directions: Bring first 5 ingredients to simmer in heavy, large saucepan over medium heat, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Add cranberries and cook until they pop.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into bowl.
Cool and then cover.
Refrigerate until well chilled.
Makes 3 cups.

title: oatmeal chocolate cookies
directions: Beat together margarine, sugar, brown sugar, eggs, vanilla, flour, baking powder and baking soda, then next add oatmeal and chocolate morsels.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: chinese casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Mix rest of items except Chinese noodles.
Add meat.
Bake in 350° oven covered for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake for 30 to 40 minutes more.
Cover with Chinese noodles and continue baking 15 minutes more.

title: dip
directions: Mix sour cream and dip mix.
Chop lettuce on top of it.
Chop tomatoes; place on top of lettuce.
Chop cucumbers on top of tomatoes.
Add carrots, peppers and celery on top of cucumbers.

title: kraut noodles
directions: Cut cabbage in half. Remove core and put through food chopper with onion.
Put drippings in pan; add ground cabbage, onion and let fry until tender, stirring constantly.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cook noodles in salt water until done.
Drain and mix with cabbage.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: graham cracker dessert
directions: Line 2 cookie sheets with foil. Line graham crackers on foil: 48 sections on 1 sheet and 24 on the second. Melt butter and margarine; melt sugar and vanilla. Cook until syrupy. Spread on crackers, then sprinkle ground nuts on top. Bake in 350° oven approximately 10 minutes; remove as soon as baked.

title: stove top chicken stew
directions: Wash chicken and place in heavy fryer; cover with vegetables. Mix soup with water and pour over vegetables.
Add seasoning. Cover and simmer until chicken and vegetables are tender, approximately 35 to 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the milk and pudding mix. Beat for 1 minute (the mixture will be thick). Add pumpkin and spices. Beat 1 minute longer. Pour into pie crust. Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours or until firm. Yield: 8 servings.

title: million-dollar pie
directions: Cream milk and lemon juice with butter.
Add coconut, pineapple (drained) and pecans.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crusts.
Keep refrigerated.
It's delicious.
Enjoy!

title: chicketti
directions: Cook spaghetti as usual; drain.
Dice the chicken (or turkey), pimento, green pepper and onion; add these and all the other ingredients, saving some of the cheese to sprinkle on top.
Pour into buttered casserole dish and cook, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.
Enjoy!

title: rum balls
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add enough rum to be able to roll into balls.
Make mixture into small balls.
Roll in more powdered sugar.
Store in tight container to keep fresh.

title: mini phyllo cups
directions: Melt butterscotch chips and one tablespoon milk in saucepan. Stir until smooth. Whisk in cream cheese (cut into pieces). Evenly divide among phyllo shells, using about 1 tsp. per cup. Refrigerate. Melt chocolate chips and 1 Tbsp. milk in clean bowl over simmering water in saucepan. Dollop each cup with chocolate. Top each with a pecan half. Refrigerate until chocolate is relatively firm to the touch.

title: chili beans
directions: Heat beans, water and meats for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients and boil.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour (add extra water, if necessary).

title: mexican caldillo stew
directions: Cut meat into bite size pieces and brown with onion in a 4 1/2-quart pot.
Add salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Add chilies, tomatoes and potatoes.
Fill pot with water and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 2 to 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
When it starts to thicken, it is ready.
May be frozen.
Serve with flour tortillas.
Serves 8.

title: b. l. t. salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine lettuce, tomato, bacon, croutons, salt and pepper.
Add mayonnaise, a bit at a time, to taste gently tossing salad between additions.
Serve immediately.

title: kugel de lukshen
directions: Cook noodles according to directions. Add the butter and allow to melt into noodles.
Set aside.
Mix eggs (beaten), sour cream, sugar, milk, vanilla and salt, then add to noodles.
Mix well and fold in the cottage cheese.
Pour into greased 10 x 15 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Cut into squares when warm.

title: pepperoni dip
directions: Mix in crock pot until melted, may keep warm on low.
Serve with breads or crackers.

title: supreme round steak
directions: Place steak in baking dish.
Pour on soup, diluted with wine. Bake at 325° for 3 hours (or put in crock-pot on low for the day).

title: chicken oregano
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.

Mix egg and milk together in small bowl. Dip chicken into egg/milk mixture, then coat with bread crumbs. Fry chicken in butter and oil just until brown. Remove chicken from pan. Saute onion until clear.
Add garlic. Fry for 5 minutes. Remove garlic.
Add 1/4 cup cooking wine to hot oil.
Let it steam for 30 seconds. Add 1/2 cup water and oregano. Stir and simmer 5 minutes. Add mushrooms and chicken. Serve over egg noodles or rice. Serves 5.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Boil peppers about 5 minutes in boiling salted water.
Drain. Cook meat and onion until meat is lightly browned.
Drain off fat. Add tomato paste and tomato sauce.
Simmer until thick.
Cook rice according to package directions.
Drain.
Mix with the hamburger mixture.
Stuff mixture into bell peppers.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes a very pretty dish to serve.

title: tomato soup
directions: Combine
all
ingredients
in
container of an electric blender or food processor;
process until smooth.
Pour into a small
saucepan and cook over medium heat until mixture boils. Cover, reduce
heat
and
simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot. Yields 4 cups (50 calories per 1 cup serving).

title: favorite divinity
directions: Mix sugar, water and syrup.
Cook over medium heat to soft ball stage.
Pour half over beaten egg whites and beat.
Cook remaining mixture to hard ball stage.
Add to egg white mixture. Add vanilla.
Beat until mixture begins to harden.
Add nuts. Drop by tablespoons onto wax paper.

title: big nut rolls
directions: Crumble yeast in small bowl; add 1/2 teaspoon sugar and 2 tablespoons lukewarm milk and set aside to raise.
In large bowl, combine the oleo, yolks, sugar, salt, milk and flour; mix well. Then add the raised yeast mixture and mix thoroughly.
The dough will be very sticky, but do not add any more flour.
Just pat the dough down and sprinkle the top lightly with flour and cover.
Put in the refrigerator overnight (at least 6 hours).
In the morning, turn the dough out on a lightly floured board and shape it in a jelly roll.
Cut this dough into 6 equal parts; roll it out thin and spread with nut mixture.
Set aside to raise 2 hours.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Brush top of the roll with beaten egg just before you put in oven.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Boil potatoes and drain.
Shape sausage into patties and simmer in 2 tablespoons of water in skillet for 15 minutes; drain water and brown patties on both sides.
Melt butter in saucepan. Stir in flour until a smooth paste is formed.
Add milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Lower heat and cook until thick. Add cheese and mustard.
Transfer cooked potatoes to greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Cover with sausage; cover and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and applesauce.
Set aside.
Mix flour, soda, cloves and cinnamon.
Combine the 2 mixtures.
Blend well. Add raisins, nuts and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour in well-greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in 2 (9-inch) cake pans.

title: hot dog chili sauce
directions: Place ground beef and onion in skillet and fry until well done. Drain.
Place tomato sauce, chili powder, salt, pepper and sugar into a heavy saucepan.
Add beef and onions.
Bring to a boil slowly, simmer for at least 2 hours.

title: anise biscuits
directions: Place sugar and eggs in bowl and beat well for 10 minutes. Add flour slowly and mix thoroughly.
Add anise seed.
Butter and flour
a 4-inch loaf pan and bake in moderate oven (375°) for 20 minutes.
Remove from pan and slice into 1-inch thick slices; place slices on buttered baking dish and return to oven and cook 5 minutes on each side until brown.
Anise seed have the flavor of licorice.

title: apple crisp
directions: Melt butter.
While butter is melting, mix oatmeal, brown sugar and flour until crumbly.
Stir crumbly mixture into butter until well coated.
Press 1/2 of mixture into 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Pour pie filling over bottom crust.
Sprinkle the rest of the crumbs over the pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until top is brown.
Serve with ice cream.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: brownies
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in 11 x 13 pan.
After baked, put 1 package miniature marshmallows over it; cover with foil until they are melted.
Let cool before frosting.

title: gazpacho
directions: Place in a blender.
Serve chilled.
If desired, serve with a dollop of sour cream.

title: coconut icing
directions: Allow cream cheese to come to room temperature.
Cream butter or margarine.
Blend all ingredients together; spread on cake layers after cooling.

title: sugar and spice pecans
directions: Combine the first 8 ingredients in a large bowl; mix well. Add pecans; stir until evenly coated.
Spread in a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 275° for 50 to 55 minutes. Remove to waxed paper while still warm.
Cool.
Store in an airtight container.
Yields 9 cups.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots until tender. Drain. Combine all other ingredients and bring to a boil. Remove from heat. Add carrots. Refrigerate for 24 hours before serving. Can be served hot or cold. Keeps for weeks in refrigerator.

title: georgia pecan bars
directions: Melt oleo and brown sugar together.
Cool, add eggs and vanilla.
Add sifted ingredients.
Add nuts last. Bake in greased flat pan for 35 to 40 minutes at 325° until batter shrinks from sides of pan. Do not overcook.
Cut into bars and roll in powdered sugar while warm.
Double recipe for 9 x 13-inch pan or larger pan for thinner bars.

title: english monkey
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk 15 minutes.
Melt butter and add cheese.
When melted, add bread crumbs and eggs, slightly beaten and seasonings.
Cook 3 minutes.
Pour over toast or crackers.

title: miss daisy's fried rockfish
directions: Wash and dry fish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper, then coat with breading mix.
In 12-inch frypan, heat approximately 1 inch shortening to 350°.
Fry fish, turning frequently, about 5 or 8 minutes for pan dressed fish. Fish is done when browned evenly on both sides and flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Do not overcook fish.
Remove from pan and drain on paper towel.
Garnish with parsley and lemon wedges.
Serves 6.

title: summer salad julienne
directions: For dressing, blend vinegar with oil, mustard and garlic. Cover dressing.
Chill.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine thawed hash browns and 1/2 cup melted butter in large bowl.
Add onion, sour cream, chicken soup and cheese.
Mix thoroughly and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a small bowl, pour 1/4 cup melted butter over the corn flakes.
Sprinkle corn flake mixture over the potato mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat eggs, water, butter, peanut butter and half of the dry cake mix until light and fluffy.
Stir in remaining cake mix and the chocolate chips. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2-inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes. Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: cabbage and beef soup
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown beef.
Add all remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 1 hour. This makes about 3 quarts and can be frozen in serving size portions to enjoy later.

title: powdered sugar icing
directions: Mix powdered sugar and vanilla.
Stir 1 tablespoon milk or juice 1 teaspoon at a time until of drizzling consistency.
Makes 1/2 cup or enough to drizzle over one 10-inch tube cake.

title: granny's pineapple cake(club member: jason baldwin)
directions: Mix and bake cake as directed. Make 3 or 4 layers.

title: elephant stew
directions: Secure a large elephant.
Kill, clean and cut in small cubes. (This takes 2 months.)
Put in large kettle and simmer over kerosene heat at 465° for 14 weeks.
Make gravy to cover.
If more meat is needed, add 2 rabbits but use only if necessary, as some people don't care for hare in their stew.
Serves 3,685.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Bring 2 cups water and butter to a boil.
Add broccoli and simmer 5 minutes.
Add rice.
Let set 5 minutes.
Stir in soup and cheese.
Bake 40 minutes at 325°.

title: mexican chicken(club member: brad smith)
directions: Cook chicken; debone and set aside. Brown onion in margarine. Add soups and tomatoes. Layer chicken, soup mixture, cheese and chips in casserole. Bake until bubbling at 300°.

title: party punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water in a large bowl. Add lemonade and stir until well mixed. Stir in cold water and cranberry juice cocktail.
Add ginger ale and ice just before serving.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Soften cream cheese in a large bowl. Add mayonnaise, celery and onion. Blend well. Dilute gelatin in pan with undiluted tomato soup. Bring to a boil.
Pour over cream cheese mixture. Mix well. Add shrimp.
Grease mold with mayonnaise.
Pour in mixture.
Chill until set, preferably overnight.
Serve on wheat crackers.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook whole chicken.
Peel chicken off bone and rip up in pieces in bowl.
Add chicken soup, Ro-Tel and onion with chicken. Mash chips up in bottom of baking pan.
Pour the stuff out of the bowl on top of chips.
Put in oven at 300° to 350° for about 35 to 45 minutes.
Take out of oven and put grated cheese on top of it. Put back in oven for about 20 to 25 minutes, then eat.

title: chinese chews
directions: Melt margarine; pour into large mixing bowl.
Add brown sugar and eggs; blend well.
Add flour, baking powder, pecans and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool; cut into bars.

title: pasta e fagioli(macaroni and bean soup)
directions: In a large pot, put oil, garlic and bacon.
Saute until bacon is partially crisp (not burned).
Add tomato sauce and saute over low heat for 30 seconds.
Add remaining ingredients except pasta. Bring to a boil and cook for approximately 30 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Thin soup with asparagus liquid.
Layer asparagus in bottom of casserole. Sprinkle with cracker crumbs, then cheese.
Dot with butter.
Pour same soup over layer.
Repeat two more times. Top with cracker crumbs. Bake at 400° until bubbly (45 minutes to 1 hour).
Serves 6 to 8.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Cook sweet potatoes until tender.
Peel.
Cut in half and place in greased baking dish.
Cook brown sugar, butter and water on stove until sugar and butter are melted.
Pour over sweet potatoes.
Bake 1 hour at 400°.

title: grilled vegetables
directions: Spray foil with cooking spray.	Layer vegetable in order listed above.
Add 4 to 5 dabs of butter.
Salt and pepper to taste. Sprinkle water over all.
Fold foil, sealing lightly. Grill on medium heat for 30 to 45 minutes.	Be careful of steam when opening.

title: reese's cup squares
directions: Melt margarine.
Add peanut butter.
Cool until lukewarm. Stir in graham cracker crumbs and powdered sugar.
Spread into 11 x 17-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and spread over mixture.
Cut into squares after pan has set.

title: beef oven rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Shake flour in a 14 x 20-inch oven bag. Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Add undrained tomatoes, soup mix, water and pepper to bag.
Squeeze bag to blend ingredients. Add beef strips to bag.
Turn bag to coat beef with sauce. Arrange ingredients in an even layer.
Close and tie bag.
Cut 6 slits in top; bake until beef is tender, 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve over hot rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: iceberg taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Add 1/2 Cheddar cheese.
Cut lettuce on plate, place tortilla chips on top.
Add meat.
Place remaining cheese and any extras on top.

title: tyo company soup
directions: Add the following herbs; parsley leaves, bay leaves, leaf oregano, sweet basil, chili powder, paprika, garlic salt, celery salt, regular salt and pepper plus small amount of red pepper and some wheat germ. Chopped beef is optional but not necessary. May freeze soup in 1/2-gallon milk cartons.
When you use it, add a small can of chili with beef to each carton.
Also 2 small cans beef broth.

title: manicotti crepes
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add remaining ingredients and beat until smooth.
Heat small frypan; add oil and wipe dry with paper towel (to season for frypan).
Use medium heat.
Drop batter until it runs smooth, about 5 or 6-inches.
Small bubbles will form in a minute, then flip crepe over until light tan.
Stack crepes.
Makes 24 crepes.

title: californian veggies
directions: Put frozen veggies in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Mix sour cream, onion soup mix, celery soup and drained water chestnuts. Pour over veggies.
Melt butter and pour over Rice Krispies. Spread the Rice Krispies mixture over the veggies.
Cover; bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: baked noodles
directions: Fry bacon until crispy.
Cook noodles and drain.
Mix noodles with bacon fat.
In casserole dish, place a layer of noodles, layer of sour cream and a layer of pot cheese.
Continue until dish is almost full or noodles are used up.
Break up bacon and place on top.
Cover and bake until cheese melts, about 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: peanut butter chews
directions: Mix Karo and sugar together in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute only, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter; mix well.
Add corn flakes.
Mix lightly until coated.
Drop on waxed paper quickly by tablespoons.
Makes approximately 36.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Mix bread stuffing, melted oleo and hot water.
Place half of the mixture in greased 12 x 8-inch dish.
Combine cooked chicken, onion, celery and mayonnaise. Place in dish over the bread mixture.

title: applesauce-raisin cookies
directions: Mix raisins and applesauce; set aside.
Combine sugar, shortening and egg; beat until fluffy.
Stir in applesauce and raisins.
Sift flour with salt, soda and spices.
Add to other ingredients and mix well.
Drop dough by teaspoons about 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 13 to 15 minutes.
Makes approximately 4 dozen.

title: stupendous strawberry cake
directions: Mix in order given and beat 3 or 4 minutes.
Bake in 3 greased and floured 10 x 13-inch cake pans at 350° until done.

title: pudding and jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O, pudding and water in saucepan.
Heat (stirring often) until almost clear.
Refrigerate overnight.
Next morning, beat with beater and fold in Cool Whip.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla to beaten eggs. Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Place in 2 greased and floured 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sugarplum spice cake
directions: Cream together sugar and lard.
Add milk and eggs alternately with sifted dry ingredients.
Pour into 9 (9-inch) layer pans. Bake in a 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: snack bar chocolate cake
directions: Mix together sugar, flour, eggs, vanilla extract and buttermilk. Bring to a boil the margarine, oil, water and cocoa. Mix liquid ingredients with dry ingredients and pour in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: warm cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Mix again, serve warm.

title: biscuit surprise
directions: Roll out biscuits; cut into small circles.
Place a Kiss in the center of each biscuit; wrap the biscuit up around the Kiss. Mix the sugar and cinnamon in a bowl.
Roll each biscuit in the sugar mixture.
Layer biscuits randomly in a greased tube pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Break apart and enjoy.

title: five hour stew
directions: Put all ingredients in covered pan. Bake at 250° for 5 hours.

title: almond puff
directions: Mix first three ingredients with a fork.
Divide in half and flatten on cookie sheet into two 12 x 3-inch strips for crusts.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until almost tender.
Drain. Saute onion in butter, stir in flour.
Add water and microwave for 30 seconds. Stir after 15 seconds.
Add Cheez Whiz and broccoli, then beaten eggs.
Place in 2 qt. casserole.
Mix 2 tbsp. melted butter and cracker crumbs and sprinkle over top.
Microwave at 70% for 15 minutes.
Turn twice, 1/2 turn.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco, egg and vanilla.
Sift remaining ingredients.
Roll into balls and place on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 300°.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix and spread in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 5 minutes in 350° oven.

title: catonsville united methodist potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes with skin on; cool, peel and dice.
Add celery and onions.
Sprinkle warm potatoes with sugar, salt and pepper. While still warm, gently mix dressing and add.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together sugar, cheese and peanut butter.
Add milk. Fold in Cool Whip.
Put into pie crust.
Sprinkle with crushed peanuts (optional).
Dribble chocolate syrup on top.
Freeze. Serve small portions.
It's rich!

title: potato-ham scallop
directions: Place half of the ham in a 2-quart casserole. Cover with half of the potatoes and half of the onion. Sift half of the flour over the ham, potato and onion mixture. Season with salt and pepper. Repeat layering of ham, potatoes and onion. Season with additional salt and pepper. Sift remaining flour on top. Pour milk over all. Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until the potatoes are tender. Uncover. Combine bread crumbs and melted butter; sprinkle on top the casserole. Bake 15 minutes more. Serves 4 to 6.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: In bowl, dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce and mix well.
Add pineapple, apple and peanuts.
Mix well and refrigerate.

title: southern corn soup
directions: Melt butter and stir in flour.
Add milk, bouillon or soup stock and corn.
Season with salt and pepper.
Boil 5 minutes and serve in bouillon cups with popcorn floating on top.
Croutons can be used in place of popcorn.
Serves 4.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Unroll crescent dough and pat into 9 x 13-inch pan, stretching to fit.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes or until golden brown. Mix cream cheese and Ranch mix.
Add milk to make a consistency that is spreadable.
Spread over cooled crust.
Sprinkle with vegetables and pat down lightly onto cream cheese.
Cut into 2-inch squares.

title: corn bread
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Add milk, egg and shortening. Beat until fairly smooth, about 1 minute. Bake in a greased square pan at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sesame chicken bits
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chicken and oil.
Bone chicken and cut into bite-size pieces.
Dip chicken in batter and fry in hot oil until golden.

title: cinnamon layered quick coffee cake
directions: Mix and set aside the 1/2 cup sugar, nuts and cinnamon.
Cream butter and add remaining sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla and lemon juice.

title: corn chowder
directions: Saute onion and celery in oleo in large saucepan.
Stir in next 7 ingredients.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add milk and half and half.
Cook, stirring constantly, until heated through.

title: potato soup
directions: Cover vegetables with water.
When all vegetables are tender (not soft; do not drain), add celery soup, evaporated milk, butter and potatoes to thicken.
Heat; do not boil.
Season to taste. Serves 4.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in large bowl.
Mix last 3 ingredients together and pour over mixture in bowl.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix all the ingredients, mixing well.
Put in airtight container. When serving, use about 2 tablespoons per cup of hot water.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together and add 1 quart of ginger ale. Makes 1 gallon.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Alternate adding whipping cream and flour to mixture. Add vanilla and beat well.
Flour and grease pan.	Bake 1 hour 15 minutes at 325°.

title: spiced apples
directions: Slice and peel apples.
Melt butter in a saucepan.
Add the apple slices.
Cook down slowly.
Add brown sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and vanilla.

title: old virginia pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening well, then add sugar and eggs slowly.
Add flour and milk and beat well.
Add baking powder, vanilla and lemon juice.
Mix well and pour into well-greased tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: pecan sandies cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Roll into small balls (about the size of a walnut).
Bake at 325° until light brown.
Remove from oven and roll in powdered sugar until coated.

title: tomato basil pasta
directions: In a large 8-quart pot, boil water with a pinch of salt.
In a separate large skillet, mince garlic in food processor.
Add to skillet with oil.
Dice tomatoes to small chunks. Heat oil and warm garlic.
Do not burn garlic.
Add tomatoes, basil, salt and pepper.
Toss lightly, about 2 minutes.
Tomatoes should just be heated through.
Set aside.
Cook pasta al dente.
Drain pasta, leaving about 1 cup of pasta water and add tomato/basil.
Sprinkle cheese and enjoy!
Serves 4 as an entree.
Great as a side dish. Serve hot or cold!

title: burger delights
directions: Cook crumbled beef, onions and green pepper in oil until browned, stirring frequently.
Add salt, pepper, dry mustard, corn and tomato sauce; simmer about 5 minutes.
Add grated cheese; heat until it melts.
Put a toasted open bun on each plate.
Put a slice of tomato on each half.
Serve cheese-burger mixture over each.
Makes 6 sandwiches.

title: carrot pineapple cake
directions: Preheat oven at 375°.
Grease 13 x 9 pan with vegetable shortening.
In a large bowl, cream sugar and oil.
Add 4 eggs; beat 1 at a time.
Beat well at high speed.
Add 8 oz. can pineapple plus juice.
Add vanilla.
Set aside.
In a medium bowl, combine flour, baking soda and cinnamon together with a fork. Add grated carrots.
Combine with egg mixture in large bowl. Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Do not overbake.
Best when moist.

title: hawaiian pineapple wedding cake
directions: Mix
with wooden spoon, not mixer.
Bake in 9 x 13 pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: holiday salad
directions: Drain, rinse and chop artichoke hearts.
Peel, seed and slice avocado.
Chop tomato.
Combine everything but avocado and tomato. Chill.

title: chocolate sugar cookies
directions: In bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
In another bowl, combine 1 cup of sugar and oil; mix well.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in chips; drop by tablespoon.
Shape into balls.
Roll into remaining sugar.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 325°.
Makes 5 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: homemade pizza
directions: In a bowl, combine the baking powder, salt and flour.
Mix the milk and Wesson oil.
Pour milk and oil mixture over flour mixture.
Mix with fork, then shape into ball.
Knead until smooth.
Roll out on 2 cookie sheets.
Put your favorite pizza sauce on top.
Add hamburger, cheese or sausage and onions or green peppers.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: tomato soup salad(serves 12)
directions: Soften gelatin in water.
Heat tomato soup in a double boiler. Add gelatin, stirring until it dissolves.
Remove from heat. Add cream cheese.
Beat with rotary beater until smooth. Cool.

title: rice krispies christmas trees
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until completely melted.
Remove from heat; add cereal and green food coloring to desired shade.
Mix well. Butter your hands while cereal is still warm and shape into Christmas trees (cone shape).
You must do this quickly before cereal cools.
For decorations, sprinkle powdered sugar or candy on trees.

title: quick dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and spread in bottom of baking dish. Spread chili over cream cheese and top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake or microwave until cheese melts.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: sausage casserole
directions: First you boil your lasagna noodles for about 2 seconds.
Then you cut your sausage halfway down the middle (lengthwise).
Add your cheese on top of the sausage.
Then roll your sausage in the noodles.
Stick the pan in the oven.
Leave in for about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pear salad
directions: Pour off juice from pears.
Add enough water to make 2 cups of liquid.
Heat liquid to boiling; add Jell-O.
Cool.
Blend pears (in blender or electric mixer) with room temperature cream cheese. Add to Jell-O.
Fold in Cool Whip, using a mixer.
Pour into Pam sprayed 9 x 11-inch dish or large ring mold.

title: tarte a la bouille pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and egg with a wire whisk. Add evaporated milk and whole milk. Cook until thick. Remove from heat. Add butter and vanilla extract. Pour into baked pie shell. Let cool.

title: texas fudge
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine cheeses with eggs and evaporated milk.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan with chilies and cover with cheese mixture.
Bake for 40 minutes.
Cool slightly and cut into bite size squares.
Serves 15 to 20.

title: black forest cake
directions: Bake cake following
directions on box.
Cut each layer in half horizontally.
Spread
each
layer
with Cool Whip and top with cherries.
Spread Cool Whip on top and sides of cake.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Blend together and beat at medium speed 2 minutes.
Pour into well greased pan. 2 small loaf pans.
Bake at 350 for 40-45 minutes. Cool 10 minutes and remove.

title: porketta
directions: Place roast on heavy duty foil.
Smear with the garlic, then sprinkle with remaining seasonings.
Seal the roast in the foil, making a tent on top.
Place in a pan and bake for 3 hours in a 300° oven.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in skillet.
Add cream of chicken, cream of mushroom, enchilada sauce and water in pan; heat and mix well.
Then add hamburger and onion to it.
Then you layer Doritos, mixture, then cheese, until you use all; end with cheese on top.

title: corned beef quiche
directions: Bake pie shell according to directions on package for 7 minutes.
Put corned beef in cooled shell.
Grate cheese and add to beef.
Combine milk, eggs and flour.
Pour over pie mixture. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Cool and serve.

title: portugese kale soup
directions: In a large stew pot or Dutch oven, saute onion in two tablespoons vegetable oil.
Add stew beef and brown.
Add water to half the volume of pan.
Add peeled and sliced potatoes.
Cook over medium heat for 30 minutes.
Add linguica and Chirico.
Add cleaned, trimmed, cut kale.
Continue cooking 30 minutes.
Add red kidney beans, undrained.
Cook until kale is done.
Cool; refrigerate.
(Soup will taste better with each reheat.)

title: million dollar pie
directions: Combine ingredients and pour into graham cracker crusts. Refrigerate 2 hours or put in freezer.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together and spread in pan the cheese, sour cream and Worcestershire.
Sprinkle taco seasoning on mixture.
Top with onions, tomatoes, cheese and lettuce.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Pour oil into 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a bowl, combine cake mix, eggs, water and 1 cup coconut; beat until smooth.
Mix in oil from pan, then pour mixture back in pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove from oven and punch holes all over cake.
In a small bowl, beat cream of coconut several minutes, then pour over hot cake.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Mix Cool Whip and remaining coconut.
Spread on cake.
Store in refrigerator overnight.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and margarine.
Press into bottom of oblong dish.
Mix milk and instant pudding.
Add to softened ice cream. Mix well but not until soupy.
Pour over crumb crust.
Top with Cool Whip and refrigerate at least 5 hours.
Do not freeze.

title: e'clairs
directions: Filling:
Prepare pudding as directed on package, reducing milk to 1 1/2 cups.
Add whipped topping and mix well.

title: banana slush punch
directions: Boil the sugar and water together a few minutes, then cool. Blend with next 4 ingredients and freeze.
To serve, take out of the freezer ahead of time for thawing.
Add pineapple juice to the slush and 7-Up or ginger ale.
Serve slightly thick.
