Serves 35 to 40 people.

title: pot roast
directions: Rub seasonings into meat.
Brown roast in oil over medium-high heat in a large, heavy Dutch oven.
Pour 2 cups of water around meat.
Arrange onion wedges on top of meat.
Cover tightly. Reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until meat is very tender.
Add carrots and potatoes to Dutch oven; cover tightly and simmer 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: apricot-coconut cheese balls
directions: Grind or chop fine apricots to thick paste.
Combine with coconut and condensed milk.
Mix ball.
Add Grand Marnier (1/4 to 1/2 cup) if desired; gives a fabulous taste.
Mix well.
Form into balls or log and roll in confectioners sugar.
Makes 50 to 60 pieces.

title: seven layer bars
directions: Melt butter; stir in crushed graham crackers.
Pat crumb mixture evenly in bottom of an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan (I use glass).
Layer in order the chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, coconut and nuts.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over all.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
(My oven seems to run hot, therefore I worked with a 325° to 335° temperature for 25 minutes.
Possibly the glass dish causes the bars to overcook too easily also.)
Cool 30 to 45 minutes before you cut into bars.
Any longer and you will be using a jackhammer.

title: stroganoff
directions: Cut meat into small pieces and brown with chopped onion and mushrooms.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Some people add tomato soup or paste.
Serve over egg noodles, rice or mashed potatoes.

title: smothered potatoes
directions: Peel and wash potatoes. Dice potatoes into pot; add chopped onions, salt and pepper, along with cooking oil and garlic. Stir to mix well and cook on low-medium heat until potatoes are tender. If needed, you can add a little water (maybe 1/2 cup) to finish cooking (like to steam them and make them creamy).

title: indian pinto beans
directions: Wash beans and place in a 6-quart kettle with 3 quarts of water and bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 4 hours until tender.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Slice Twinkies in half.
With filling up, place in pan and slice bananas lengthwise over Twinkies.
Beat pudding and pour over bananas.
Drain pineapple and put over bananas.
Top with Cool Whip and refrigerate for 1 hour before serving.

title: marilyn monroe pie
directions: Combine ingredients and press into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 16 to 20 minutes; let cool.

title: apple kuchen
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut margarine into cake mix until crumbly. Mix in coconut.
Pat mixture into ungreased oblong pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch, building up slight edges.
Bake 10 minutes.
Arrange apple slices on warm crust.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle on apples.
Blend sour cream and egg.
Then drizzle over apples. (Topping will not completely cover apples.)
Bake 25 minutes or until edges are light brown.
Serve warm.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream eggs, oil and sugar.
Add extract and cinnamon.
Beat in dry ingredients.
Fold in nuts and apples.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch greased baking pan for 40 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar before serving.

title: shortcake
directions: Sift flour with baking powder.
Beat eggs until mixed.
Add slowly in order listed.
Add hot water slowly.
Bake approximately 20 minutes in 9 x 9-inch pan in 350° oven.
Serve with crushed sweetened strawberries.

title: surprise carrot cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add combined oil and 3 eggs, mixing until moistened.
Fold in carrots and nuts.
Reserve 2 cups of batter.
Pour remaining batter into greased and floured 9-inch Bundt pan.

title: stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Brush both sides of chicken with sour cream.
Coat both sides with stuffing.
Roll each one and hold together with toothpicks. Refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Melt butter and drizzle on top of each chicken breast.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked potatoes and eggs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Scrub potatoes and pierce with a fork several times.
Bake for 1 hour or until potatoes give slightly under pressure when squeezed.
Slice tops off baked potatoes and scoop out 3/4 of potato and set aside in medium bowl.
Sprinkle salt and pepper inside each potato skin and drop 1 raw egg into each skin.
Bake potatoes 15 minutes in oven or until egg yolks are set.
While eggs are cooking; heat margarine in pan; add onion. Cook for 5 minutes over medium heat.
Add cooked onion, milk, salt and pepper to scooped out potato and mash.
Remove potato skins from oven and stuff mashed potato mixture back in and reheat.

title: chocolate toffee bar dessert
directions: Mix flour, pecans, sugar, butter and 1/2 cup of the toffee bits in large bowl until well mixed.
Press firmly onto bottom of 13x9 inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool. Pour milk into large bowl.
Add pudding mixes and stir with wire whisk for one minute or until well blended.
Spread 1 1/2 cups pudding on bottom of crust. Gently stir 1/2 of the whipped topping into remaining pudding.
Spread over pudding in pan.
Top with the remaining whipped topping.
Sprinkle with remaining toffee bits. Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute green pepper and onion in margarine.
Add to other ingredients and mix well.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake in covered casserole at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: iranian chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken and cut into small pieces.
Cook potatoes with skins on; cool, then peel.
Shred eggs, potatoes and pickles.
Mix all ingredients together and add a little lemon juice.
Put mixture into pita bread halves.
Serving Size:
Preparation Time:

title: pineapple nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together with a spoon.
Put in ungreased baking dish or pan (9 x 13-inch) and bake about 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
It can be iced with any kind of frosting.
Sprinkle top with nuts, if desired.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken; let cool and pull apart.
In pan, melt butter. Add broth and milk.
Slowly add flour; cook until thickens.
Add chicken, onions, peas and carrots.
Cook until boils.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Stretch biscuits and put over mixture.
Put in oven for 20 or 25 minutes, or until golden brown at 350°.

title: white christmas cookies
directions: Beat butter and sugar together until creamy.
Beat in vanilla and egg.
Combine the flour and baking soda; beat into butter mixture.
Stir in the coconut and white chocolate.
Form a dough. Drop by teaspoons onto a buttered cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Sift powdered sugar over cookies once cooled to look like a "blizzard of snow."

title: grape-nuts custard
directions: In deep mixing bowl, place all ingredients.
Beat at medium speed until completely mixed.
Place mixture in a medium sized pan, then put this pan into a large sized pan.
Add hot water to bottom pan only and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cauliflower marranca(from moosework cookbook, a family favorite)
directions: Saute 1 pound mushrooms, sliced
and 1 large onion (chopped) in butter with juice of 1 lemon.

Saute 1 large head of cauliflower in flower pieces with 3 cloves crushed garlic, basil, salt and pepper. Combine 3 cups cooked brown rice, salted and buttered, and 2 1/2 cups grated cheese with the rest of the ingredients. Bake covered 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all in baking dish.

title: souperburgers
directions: In frying pan, saute onion, green pepper and chili powder in oil until tender.
Add beef and cook until brown, stirring.
Add soup, water, salt and pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes, stirring often. Serve on toasted, warm buns.
Serves 6.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until it sets and is browned.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: simply elegant steak and rice
directions: Cut steak into strips and brown in oil.
Add onions and saute. Add other ingredients except rice.
Simmer 1 hour.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Steam breasts (do not overcook).
Let cool.
Cut chicken in bite-sized pieces.
Cook broccoli until barely tender.

title: perfect peach cobble up
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. In a large mixing bowl, combine biscuit mix, brown sugar, nutmeg and cinnamon. Using an electric mixer on low, mix in softened margarine until mixture is crumbly. Add milk and blend thoroughly. Spread batter evenly on bottom of an 8-inch square pan coated with cooking spray. Place peach slices on top of batter. Pour reserved juice evenly over peaches. Bake for 30 minutes. Slice into 9 equal squares. Refrigerate leftovers, then reheat before serving. Makes 9 servings.

title: hot spinach artichoke dip
directions: Cook spinach and drain well.
Mix with chopped artichoke hearts and rest of ingredients.
Put in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve with chips.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Don't use mixer.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake in unbaked pie shell at 350° until firm in the middle.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Wilt cabbage in boiling water to which juice of 1 lemon has been added.
Drain cabbage leaves; cut heavy rib out.
Combine meat, onion, rice and seasoning.
Spread leaf with 2 tablespoons of mixture.
Fold opposite and roll.
Place in pan.
Add 1 cup hot water and 1/2 cup tomato juice.
Cover; simmer in oven at 325° for 2 hours.
Serve with boiled potatoes and string beans.
Delicious!

title: old fashioned salmon patties
directions: Make simple corn bread batter.
Drain can of pink salmon.
Fork the salmon until torn apart.
Add to corn bread batter and add egg. Salt and pepper to taste and add chopped onion, if you like.
Drop by double tablespoons into hot oil in cast-iron skillet.
Turn when brown.

title: mango jello pie
directions: Dissolve
jello
in hot water;	chill
until
partially set. Combine fruits
and
marshmallows.	When
jello
is half set, fold in fruit mixture.
Whip cream; add to jello mixture. Pour into a baked crust; chill until firm.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown chuck; top with Spanish rice, Mexican beans and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: grandma lyla's norwegian potato lefse
directions: Mash potatoes and add Crisco and salt while hot.
Cool before adding 1 cup flour.
Use the remaining 1/2 cup flour for pastry board to keep from sticking as you roll fist size balls into thin pancake shape.
Bake on top of stove or ungreased griddle on medium heat, turning when brown.
Store in cloth to prevent drying.
Excellent served hot, buttered, sprinkled with cinnamon sugar and rolled up tortilla style.

title: curtis' peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix flour, salt, baking soda and baking powder and set aside. Cream butter and peanut butter together in food processor.
Add white and brown sugar and process until smooth.
Add egg and vanilla and process until well blended.
Add flour mixture and blend until the mixture forms a ball.
Break off 50 to 60
pieces and form balls.
Place on cookie sheets and crisscross with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: lemon lollipops
directions: You will also need wax paper and sticks.

title: the best cake you ever ate
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Soften margarine and cream with sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well after each addition.
Add 1 cup flour and baking powder; mix well.
Add milk.
Add rest of flour; mix well.
Add vanilla.
Beat on medium for 2 more minutes.
Pour into 2 greased and floured (I use Baker's Joy) 8-inch round pans or a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes, until toothpick comes out clean.
Good by itself, with fruit topping or your favorite icing.
Serves 12.

title: bacon-cheese fingers
directions: Mix together ingredients and spread over 10 slices of sandwich bread, crusts removed and cut in thirds.
(Party rye or pumpernickel can also be used.)
Bake "fingers" on lightly greased baking sheets at 325° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: mrs. mann's biscuits
directions: Cut shortening into flour until coarse like crumbs.
Add milk; work dough quickly.
Turn onto lightly floured surface.
Roll or pat dough to desired thickness.
Cut and bake in hot 450° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: anise drops
directions: The day before, in a large bowl, with mixer at medium speed, beat the eggs until light.
Gradually add the sugar, while beating.
Beat 10 minutes. Sift the flour with the baking powder. Add to egg mixture with the vanilla extract, while beating at low speed until well blended.
Stir in the anise seed. At once, drop by heaping teaspoonful on greased cookie sheets.
Let stand out overnight, uncovered.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Wash tomatoes.
Cut out stem ends, then halve crosswise.
Arrange, with cut sides up, in baking pan. Spread with prepared mustard.
Top with minced onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Then add crumbs.

title: snickers bar cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a food processor, grind cookies into fine crumbs.
Add butter and process until well blended.
Press into bottom and about 1-inch up sides of 9 1/2 x 1-inch spring-form pan.

title: macaroni with tomato sauce and peppers
directions: Chop pepper and onion.
In medium saucepan, fry pepper and onion 10 minutes.
Add tomato sauce.
Cover and cook on low for 1 hour.
Serve over cooked macaroni.

title: three pepper meatball stew
directions: Meanwhile, place the rice and water in a Dutch oven or soup pot; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer until rice is tender, 13 to 14 minutes.
Add meatballs to rice and water.
Also stir in the sugar, cider vinegar, peppers and pineapple juice. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
In a small bowl, combine the cornstarch and soy sauce; mix well. Stir into meatball mixture.
Cook over medium heat until mixture thickens and boils.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Cool jello until just ready to set, then mix in the rest of ingredients.
Set in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put in the refrigerator to set.
Looks nice served on a lettuce leaf.

title: no egg oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add sifted flour, soda and cinnamon along with milk and vanilla.
Add raisins and oats.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes in 375° oven.
Can flatten with a floured glass.

title: skillet spanish rice
directions: Combine oil, rice, onion, pepper and beef in skillet.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes.

title: catherine harvey's sweet pickles
directions: Dump pickles in drainer; rinse and drain.
Slice half of the pickles into 1/2-inch slices.
Put back in jar.
Add 1 cup sugar. Slice remaining pickles into 1/2-inch pieces and add remaining 1 cup sugar, mustard seed, celery seed and vinegar.
Screw lid on tightly; set aside for 1/2 hour.
Turn jar upside-down 4 to 5 times or enough to more thoroughly dissolve sugar.
Put in refrigerator.
Wait 3 days before eating.
They're even better after a couple weeks.
Juice leftover after pickles are eaten is good as a salad dressing.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: In skillet, cook 1 tablespoon oil and half the chicken until browned.
Remove.
Repeat with remaining chicken.
In remaining 1 tablespoon of oil, stir-fry vegetables with ginger and garlic powder until tender-crisp.
Add soup, soy sauce and vinegar.
Heat to a boil; return chicken to skillet.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.
Serve over rice.

title: foolproof dark chocolate fudge
directions: In a 1-quart microwave-safe bowl, combine chocolate chips, sweetened condensed milk and salt.
Cook on High for 3 minutes, or until chips melt, stirring after each 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread evenly into wax paper lined 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Turn fudge onto cutting board.
Peel off paper and cut into squares.
Store, loosely covered, at room temperature.
Yields about 2 pounds.

title: goulash
directions: Brown meat with onion and garlic. While browning, put noodles on in plenty of water with 1 tablespoon Wesson oil and 1 tablespoon salt. Drain noodles and drain meat. Combine all ingredients and put in large casserole. Before baking, sprinkle 1/2 cup evaporated milk and grated cheese over top. Bake in 350° oven for approximately 45 minutes.

title: missi's layered salad
directions: Mix creamy buttermilk Ranch and cucumber Ranch together until creamy.
Layer the lettuce and the 2 jars of bacon bits in bottom of casserole.
Add the other vegetables and then top with tomatoes (optional).
Mix the 2 cheeses and top the salad with cheese.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Combine ingredients and stir well.
Pour in pie crusts and refrigerate approximately 12 hours.
Makes 2 pies.

title: thunder roll-ups
directions: Spread the coconut on a sheet of waxed paper.
Mix everything else together in a medium bowl.
Roll a spoonful of the mixture into the coconut. Chill for 1 hour. Stomp around like a thunder-lizard while you eat them!

title: cheese appetizer
directions: Pull wax covering from cheese.
If using mustard, spread thin layer over cheese.
Open rolls, do not separate.
Make 2 rectangles from rolls.
Place cheese in center of one rectangle and wrap the rolls around the cheese.
Wrap remaining rolls around cheese, completely covering and sealing seams.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes, or longer if dough does not appear done.
Serve with fruit (apples, pears, grapes, etc.).

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix together and bake until set at 350°.
Double this recipe if desired.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, shortening, sugar and brown sugar.
Add flour, Bisquick, eggs, vanilla, milk, soda, chocolate chips and nuts. Bake at 375°.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Mix all together, except potato chips and paprika.
Put in greased 9 x 12 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Cover with potato chips; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until golden brown.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: spanish rice
directions: Place butter, onion, green pepper and celery in 3-quart microwave dish.
Cook 5 minutes on High.
Stir in rice, water, tomato sauce, tomatoes and chillies.
Cover and cook 25 minutes. Let stand, covered, 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Total Cooking Time: 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream the cream cheese and peanut butter.
Add sugar; mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Place half of mixture in each pie shell.
Chill.

title: cocoa fruit breakfast drink
directions: In blender container, place all ingredients; cover.
Blend until smooth.
Yields about five 6-ounce servings.

title: marmalade cookies
directions: Beat eggs lightly. Add sugar gradually, then other ingredients except flour and baking powder. Sift flour with baking powder and add mixture, stirring thoroughly a few minutes. Drop by spoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet.
Pat down a little with a spoon, moistened with milk to form a glaze.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 20 minutes.
Low calorie.

title: nachos
directions: Brown the hamburger meat.
Drain it; pour taco sauce into ground beef and let it simmer.
Put Doritos on bottom of dish. Pour hamburger meat onto Doritos, then put cheese on top of it and it's ready to serve.

title: glorified dessert
directions: Mix all together.
Makes a wonderful dessert.

title: missy's hush puppies
directions: Mix ingredients together and drop by spoonfuls in deep, hot grease.

title: quick sandwiches
directions: Mix well and spread on bread or crackers.

title: hot fruit casserole
directions: Arrange fruit in large casserole with apple rings on top. Pour Cream Sauce over the fruit.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Soften cream cheese and cream with powdered sugar.
Add Cool Whip and
divide
between
pie shells.
Mix both puddings together.
Add milk
and mix until smooth.	Divide between pie shells.
Refrigerate.
Easy and delicious.

title: bean taco
directions: Heat bacon grease in heavy skillet; add onions, brown and then add the beans and mix well.
Cook over low heat for a few minutes. Add all other ingredients, except Cheddar cheese; mix thoroughly and simmer.
Gradually add Cheddar cheese.
Cook until cheese is melted and blended well with the beans.
Correct seasoning as needed.
Serve in crisp taco shells as with other tacos, but do not use taco sauce.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Mix and bake in 3 layers at 350° for 25-30 minutes.

title: crab mousse
directions: *I suggest using the 1/3 less salt type of soup.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together the butter, shortening and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time.
In another bowl, mix dry ingredients. Add dry ingredients to other mixture. Add milk and flavorings.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Melt butter and mix with crumbs.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix ice cream, milk and pudding together and pour over crumbs.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Top with Cool Whip before serving.

title: corn relish
directions: Place lids on jars and tighten.
Heat in water bath up to neck of jar until pickles change color.
Heat pickles thoroughly so that jars will seal, but do not overcook!
If a jar fails to seal, place another lid on it and reheat.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix well by hand.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Soak gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water.
Heat soup to boiling point.
Dissolve cream cheese thoroughly in soup.
Add gelatin and cool.
Add mayonnaise, celery, onions and seasonings.
When it begins to thicken, pour a layer of mixture into oiled mold, follow with a layer of shrimp and continue until used.
Chill.
When ready to use, unmold with hot water.
Serve with crackers.

title: saltine cracker candy
directions: Combine sugar and milk and slowly bring to boil.
Stir constantly.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well and pour into an 8-inch square dish.
Let cool.
Then cut into squares.

title: no knead water-rising twists
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Add yeast; mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Blend in flour.
Dough will be quite stiff.
Let rise by placing covered dough in warm place (80° to 90°) for 1/2 hour.
Or, tie in tea towel leaving space for rising dough.
Place in large bowl and fill with water (75° to 80°).
Let stand until dough rises to top of water, about 30 to 45 minutes. Remove from water.
Will be soft and moist.

title: crisp onion roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Place in roasting pan.
Pour ingredients over potatoes.
Bake 60 minutes.
Garnish with parsley, if desired. Makes 8 servings.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Brown beef with onion and garlic.
Chop tomatoes coarsely and add to remaining ingredients. Simmer on top of range for 1 hour or in slow cooker for 2 1/2 hours on medium.
(Much better than Shoney's.)

title: manhattan (4th of july) clam chowder
directions: In large saucepan, cook and stir bacon and onions until bacon is crisp and onions tender.
Stir in reserved clam juice, potatoes, celery and water.
Cook, uncovered, until potatoes are tender, about 10 minutes.
Add clams, tomatoes and seasonings. Reheat to boiling.
Serves 6.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Spread rice and combined soups and water in 9 x 13-inch pan. Place pieces of raw chicken on top (single layer).
Sprinkle with 1/2 package dry onion soup mix.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Easy and very good.

title: ham and scalloped potatoes
directions: Put half of ham, potatoes and onions in crock-pot.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper then half of grated cheese.
Repeat with remaining half.
Spoon undiluted soup over top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and cook on low, 8 to 10 hours or on high for 4 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Make a sauce using remaining ingredients.
Mix with broccoli and pour into greased dish. Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Heat sugar and cocoa over low heat for 1 minute, then add cream and butter.
Boil 1 minute.
Add vanilla.
Good for cake and ice cream.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: In a paper bag, add dry ingredients to enough flour to cover the meat, plus 1/3 cup leftover to use for gravy.
Add the meat and shake well until completely coated.
Brown the meat in Crisco. To the browned meat, add the remaining 1/3 cup seasoned flour mix and 2 1/2 cups water to make the gravy.
Add Worcestershire sauce and mushrooms with juice.
Simmer 2 to 3 hours.

title: corn casserole
directions: Brown green pepper, onion and ground beef in melted shortening in heavy frypan.
Stir in corn, tomatoes and seasonings.
Cover and simmer over low heat for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. Uncover, stir in macaroni; simmer an additional 10 minutes or until macaroni is tender, stirring occasionally.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: orange glaze sweet potatoes
directions: Peel and bake potatoes in a 350 degree oven for an hour or so until just fork tender.
Mix all other ingredients in a small saucepan and bring to a boil over medium heat.
Boil until it begins to thicken about 1-2 minutes.
Cut cooled cooked potatoes up into large chunks.
Place pieces in an 8 x 8 baking dish and pour orange juice mixture over the top.
Return to the oven for about an hour for flavor to permeate potato.

title: quick fudge
directions: Combine in saucepan or double boiler the pudding, butter and milk.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and blend in sugar.
Stir in nuts and vanilla. Pour into buttered pan.
Refrigerate until hardened.

title: noodle squeal
directions: Cut and cook sausage, pepper and onion together until brown. Cook noodles and drain.
Mix noodles and sausage mixture and tomato soup together.
Put a layer of noodle mixture, layer of cheese alternately until used up ending up with cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Mix orange Jell-O and crushed pineapple together in pan and heat until Jell-O melts; cool.
Stir in buttermilk and place in freezer for 45 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip, celery and nuts.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch Pyrex container and refrigerate until time to serve.
(Delicious and I hate buttermilk.)

title: lightly lemon chicken
directions: Mix bread crumbs and parsley.
Dip chicken pieces into Egg Beaters original, then coat with bread crumb mixture.
In skillet, over medium-high heat, cook the garlic in margarine for 1 minute. Add chicken and brown on both sides.
Cut half the lemon into thin slices; arrange over chicken.
Squeeze juice from remaining lemon half into chicken broth.
Pour into skillet.
Heat to boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 10 minutes or until chicken is tender. Makes 4 servings.

title: christmas coke-cherry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in juice heated from cherries and pineapple. This is all the liquid.
Add coke, cherries (or grapes), pineapple and nuts.
Grate frozen cream cheese on top.
Place in refrigerator.
Serve cold.

title: italian nut balls
directions: Combine first three ingredients on medium speed; blend well. Add egg yolks, vanilla, and almond.
Gradually add flour to ingredients and roll into 1-inch balls.
Dip balls into 2 reserved egg whites (slightly beaten) and then roll in nuts.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Make deep depression in center of each cookie with finger.
Add jelly.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Do not overbake.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Yields 36 to 40.

title: crab quiche
directions: Blend mayonnaise, flour, beaten eggs and milk, in blender.
Add meat, Swiss cheese and green onions after blending.
Blend all together.
Pour into Mrs. Smith's 9-inch pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Check for doneness by inserting knife. Comes out clean when done.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
If too stiff, add milk to make thinner.
Cook in greased pan in medium oven until firm. Break into small pieces; pour stock over it.
Add enough chicken stock to make a soft batter.
Bake in a 375° oven until brown. May be used for stuffing turkey.

title: breakfast frittata
directions: In 10-inch skillet, cook hash browns in margarine until browned, stirring occasionally.
Add eggs and ham.
Cook over medium-low heat for 9 to 10 minutes, lifting edges to allow uncooked portion to flow underneath.
Continue until mixture is almost set.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 3 to 4 minutes.
Cut into wedges.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into baking dish and bake 45 minutes at 400°.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Measure salt and
sugar
into
a large bowl.
Scald the milk and mix well
with	salt and sugar.
Add the water.
When cool enough add	yeast.	Let
dissolve.	Add
the oil and mix. Beat in the egg and half the flour.
Beat well.
Add remaining flour and beat
again.
Brush the top with oil.
Cover tightly with foil. Refrigerate overnight about 2 hours before baking, shape into rolls on
a floured board.	Let rise until light in a warm place. Bake in 425° oven 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes good cinnamon rolls.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Dissolve Kool-Aid in water with sugar; combine.
Add juice.
Pour all in punch bowl.
Add 7-Up.
Add sherbet in punch bowl to keep punch chilled when serving.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Melt butter with garlic in frying pan.
Saute chicken for about 1 minute in garlic butter.
Add lemon juice and cook about 5 minutes longer or until meat is white.
Add mushrooms.
When everything is cooked, add Parmesan cheese and keep stirring.
Add wine.
Serve over pasta.

title: frozen fruit slush
directions: Stir together all ingredients, except use only half of the 7-Up.
Freeze in small containers, 1-quart or 1/2-gallon capacity. Thaw 2 to 4 hours before serving.
Add the remainder of the 7-Up and stir.
Serve while still icy and slushy.
The unused portion may be refrozen.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon together.
Roll biscuits in cinnamon-sugar mixture.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
If dressing is too thick, add a little milk.

title: sugar-free pineapple pie
directions: Mix ingredients together. Pour into pie crust. Chill and top with lite Cool Whip.

title: whole wheat waffles
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients together into a large bowl.
Stir in whole wheat flour and wheat germ.
In another bowl, beat eggs. Blend milk and oil into beaten eggs.
Add milk mixture to the dry ingredients, stirring only until dry ingredients are moistened. Bake in a hot preheated waffle iron until steaming stops.
Serve warm with honey-butter.
Makes 3 waffles.

title: pistachio pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients into a serving bowl.
Chill overnight.

title: cornflake candy
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil. Mix in the ingredients. Make balls and mash flat on wax paper.

title: mini pecan sandwiches
directions: Spread cheese on pecan half.
Top with another pecan half.

title: vermicelli cooked in tomato sauce
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet set over medium-high heat.
Add the undrained tomatoes, broth, wine, sugar, cayenne and basil. Bring to a boil and add the pasta.
Cover and cook at low boil, about 8 to 10 minutes, stirring often, until the pasta has softened.
Season with pepper.
Garnish each serving with Parmesan cheese.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients well.
Shape into 4 patties.
Melt butter in skillet.
Cook patties 4 or 5 minutes on each side. Serve on buns.
If desired, serve with slice of tomato and lettuce.
Yields 4 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add oil, water and eggs. Beat and add pumpkin, raisins and nuts.
Pour into 2 well-greased loaf pans. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: christmas corn
directions: Boil the sugar, corn syrup and margarine for 3 minutes exactly. Pour over popcorn that is plain or has gumdrops, peanuts or marshmallows.

title: sausage squares
directions: Brown sausage and onions in skillet.
Add cheeses and stir until slightly melted.
Stir in remaining ingredients; mixture will be thick.
Pour into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; spread evenly.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 25 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Can serve with jalapeno jelly.

title: chocolate dainties
directions: Melt the margarine and chocolate chips in a double boiler. Beat the 4 egg whites until stiff and add the 3 cups powdered sugar, pinch of salt and vanilla.
Stir in the melted chocolate mixture, marshmallows and nuts.

title: corn oysters
directions: Mix all together well and fry.

title: nutty pineapple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pie shells.
Chill several hours.

title: bleu cheese dip
directions: Combine equal amounts of dressing and cream.
Serve with crackers or chips or raw vegetables.

title: hot choco mocha mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store in airtight container.
Stir 6 tablespoons mix in cup of hot water.

title: twinkie dessert
directions: Cut Twinkies lengthwise and place in bottom of 9 x 13 in. pan with the filling side up.
Mix together Cool Whip, cream cheese and condensed milk.
Spread this mixture over the top of the Twinkies.
Combine the sliced strawberries and strawberry glaze. Spoon the strawberry mixture on top of the Twinkies.
Store in refrigerator.

title: noodle souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in greased casserole. Put casserole in pan of warm water and bake for 1 hour at 375°.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Combine first five ingredients and mix well.
Spread on six slices of bread.
Cover with remaining slices and place in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine soup and sour cream; spread over top layer of bread.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for
20 minutes.
Add
cheese
and
bake until cheese melts.
Serves 12.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Combine beans, onion, catsup and mustard.
Pour into large casserole dish.
Top with bacon slices.
Bake at 350° until bacon is done.

title: fruity punch
directions: Mix thoroughly and chill.
Serves approximately 15 people.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and lemon peel.
Gradually add sugar, creaming all until light, about 6 minutes at medium speed on electric mixer. Add vanilla and then eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Sift together dry ingredients.
Stir in.
Grease bottom only of a 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Turn in batter.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan.
Sift confectioners sugar lightly on top.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Start water boiling in a medium saucepan.
Add turkey parts, bits of turkey, celery, onion and bell pepper.
Let boil for 45 minutes or until vegetables are soft.
Remove turkey parts. Crumble cornbread in a large baking pan, then add vegetables and broth (if the mixture is too dry, add water until it's semi-sloshy), then add seasoning and 3 raw eggs.
Mix well.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour or until top is light brown and dressing is moist.
Serves 8.

title: easy pepperoni-cheese rolls
directions: Allow dough to thaw.
Mix pepperoni and cheese and wrap up in dough.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: date pudding (cake)
directions: Use 8 x 12-inch pan.
Cut up dates.
Add soda to 1 cup boiling water.
Mix (little pan).
Set aside.

title: velveeta dip
directions: Pour milk into saucepan with cheese; stir constantly until thick.
Sprinkle with seasoning salt.
Great with chips or vegetables.

title: applesauce pineapple salad
directions: Combine Jell-O and hot applesauce; let cool.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well (add 7-Up last).

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into buttered dish.

title: cool salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl. Chill and serve. Mixture will thicken as it sets.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and cornmeal in a large bowl.
Toss lightly with fork to mix.
Add eggs, butter, milk, lemon peel and lemon juice.
Beat with rotary beater until smooth and thoroughly blended.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes until top is golden brown.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl. Add oil, coffee and milk. Mix at medium speed for 2 minutes. Add eggs and vanilla; beat 2 more minutes. Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans (or two 8-inch cake pans). Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: beef in casserole
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients together in skillet over low heat until done.
Combine rice, sour cream, cream cheese and onions.

title: baked hush puppies
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a bowl; make a well in center of mixture.
Combine milk, egg substitute, oil and pepper in a small bowl.
Stir well.
Add to cornmeal mixture, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.

title: egg and lemon soup(greek)
directions: Bring chicken stock to a boil; remove from heat.
In a separate bowl, beat the eggs well until mixture looks thick.
Add the lemon juice "slowly" while beating constantly with a whisk. Pour 1 cup of hot soup into the egg mixture, stirring quickly. Add another cup.
Pour the egg mixture into the soup, stirring until well mixed.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Cook all ingredients 5 minutes from time it boils.
Beat a long time.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together.
Add 1 cup nuts and keep 1 cup to roll ball in.
Chill 2 hours.
Form ball and roll in nuts.
Makes 1 large ball or 2 small ones.

title: homemade cracker jacks
directions: Remove any unpopped kernels.
Add peanuts and set aside.
In saucepan, combine brown sugar, butter, corn syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil and boil for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Turn off heat.
Quickly stir in baking soda.
Add popcorn gently with caramel.
Divide caramel corn between two 9 x 9-inch pans.
Place in preheated 250° oven and bake for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove and immediately spread on wax paper to cool.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Wash tomatoes. Cut into thin slices. Cook tomatoes, water and lemon until tomatoes are almost tender.
Drain.
When the tomato liquid has cooled, add the mixture of sugar, cornstarch and salt. Cook until thickened.
Add tomatoes, cinnamon and butter.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour the hot mixture into a pastry shell. Add the top sheet of dough and bake in moderately hot oven at 375° to 400° for about 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: meatballs
directions: Combine ingredients and make meatballs. Make your sauce separately by combining ingredients until smooth in a separate bowl. Put your meatballs in a large broiler pan or cookie sheet; pour half of your sauce mixture over them and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cover meatballs with remaining sauce when you put them in a crock-pot on low.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Sift flour, then resift with 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1 teaspoon ginger.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add flour mixture to cream mixture alternately with soda that has been dissolved in hot water.
Spoon onto greased cookie sheet and bake 15 minutes at 350° to 375°.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar, salt and Crisco.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add soda dissolved in water.
Add mashed bananas and nuts.
Add flour; beat thoroughly.
Bake in loaf pan at 350 degrees for 1 hour, or until done.

title: western skillet noodles
directions: In medium skillet, brown beef; drain.
Add water and bring to a boil; stir in noodles and beef flavor sauce and
chili powder. Continue boiling over medium heat, stirring occasionally, for 7 minutes.
Add corn and cheese.
Simmer for 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.
tags: whole kernel corn with sweet peppers

title: bean soup
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and garlic.
Add rest of ingredients and heat thoroughly.
Makes 12 servings.

title: gramma's chocolate fudge
directions: Melt chocolate, butter, sugar, Karo syrup and milk.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Cool until lukewarm.
Add vanilla and nuts. Beat until it starts to lose its gloss.
Pour into buttered 8-inch square pan.

title: pierogi and filling
directions: Mix flour with salt.
Add warm water until it becomes doughy; knead with hands, adding flour if needed until it is a soft rollable dough.
Roll dough on floured board or counter until 1/4-inch thick.
Make circles with cutter dipped in flour about 2 to 3-inches in diameter.
Place 1 tablespoon of filling in center. Fold over, pinching edges together, and pinch to seal.
Drop the pierogi into boiling salted water and gently stir so not to stick together.
Cook until they float to the top and continue for 5 minutes.
Do not place on top of each other.
To prevent sticking, brush with vegetable oil when cool.
To serve, fry in margarine until golden brown.
Serve with sour cream.

title: crunchy chicken bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
In a bowl, blend cup-a-soup with water.
Dip chicken in soup mix then into crumbs; place in shallow baking dish then drizzle with butter.
Bake 45 minutes or until tender.
Makes about 2 servings.

title: crab aspic
directions: Combine 1 cup V-8 juice and garlic; bring to a boil.
Add jello; remove from heat and stir until jello is dissolved.
Add remaining V-8 juice and remaining ingredients except crab.
Stir well.
Add crab.
Pour into mold and chill until set.
Garnish with parsley, lemons, etc.
This is a delicious holiday salad that goes well with turkey.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix butter, sugar, flour and pecans together and spread into a 13x9 pan.
Cook at 350 degrees for 15 mins., cool.
Mix powdered sugar, 1 c. whipped topping and cream cheese, spread onto crust. Mix milk and pudding together spread on top of cream cheese mixture, spread on remaining cool whip.
Chill.

title: grilled catfish cajun-style
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a small bowl. Sprinkle lemon juice and seasoning mixture on both sides of fish.
Spray a fish basket with cooking spray.

Place fish in basket. Grill fish, covered, over medium coals (400°) for 7 to 10 minutes on each side or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork. Remove fish from basket; place on a serving platter.
Garnish, if desired. Yields 4 servings.

title: grandma adams' sugar cookies
directions: Blend shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and soda and add to shortening mixture.
Add sour cream last.
Chill overnight.
Roll out thin and cut as desired. Bake at 350° until just lightly browned.

title: apple torte
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Set aside.
Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg; beat until fluffy.
Gradually add dry ingredients to butter, sugar and egg (batter will be stiff).
Stir in apples.
Pat into lightly greased small pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pumpkin bread(makes two loaves)
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat until well blended.
Pour into 2 aluminum pans and bake at 350° for 45 - 55 minutes, or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: uncle alfred's vinegar
directions: Mix together and let stand and ferment for 3 weeks and it will be the best of vinegar.

title: italian beef gravy
directions: To roast beef drippings, add water plus 1 bouillon cube for each cup of water.
Add marjoram, thyme, oregano, Tabasco, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, garlic and green pepper.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Add thinly sliced beef and marinate in gravy in refrigerator for 4 to 5 hours or overnight.
Take meat out to heat gravy, then put beef back in.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil sugar, cocoa, butter and milk for 1 1/2 minutes.
Add vanilla, rolled oats and peanut butter.
Drop on waxed paper and chill.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake for 8 minutes at 350°.

title: buster's oklahoma brown candy
directions: Put 2 cups sugar into a heavy skillet.
Melt over low heat, stirring with a wooden spoon as it melts slowly and becomes a syrup (about the color of light brown sugar).
Be careful not to let it smoke or turn dark brown.
Dump 4 cups sugar and 2 cups milk into a large deep kettle.
Place over low heat and simmer as you continue to stir the melting sugar.
When sugar in skillet has melted, pour in a fine stream into the mixture in the kettle, stirring all the time to blend.
Cook and stir until it reaches firm ball stage (244° or 248°).
Remove from heat.
Add soda and stir as it foams.
Set aside for 20 minutes.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and beat until candy becomes thick.
Fold in the broken pecans.
Pour into buttered pan and cool.
Freezes well and is delicious.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake in ungreased casserole dish at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fried apples with bacon
directions: Place apples in bowl.
Add sugar, lemon juice, nutmeg, cinnamon and cloves; toss to coat.
Saute bacon in large skillet until crisp.
Transfer bacon to paper towels to drain.
Add apples to pan drippings and saute until tender, about 10 minutes.
Transfer apples and juices in skillet to bowl.
Sprinkle with bacon.
Serves 4.

title: weight watchers pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and honey together.
Add Rice Krispies and mix with spoon.
Spread in bottom of pie pan.
Prepare pudding and pie filling according to box directions and spread on crust. Chill.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar, add milk and vinegar mixture, beaten eggs, vanilla and cocoa.
Put soda into boiling water, add dry ingredients.
Mixture will be thin, pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: ricotta cheesecake
directions: Beat Ricotta and cream cheese at high speed until well combined.
Gradually beat in sugar; beat in 1 egg at a time at low speed.
Add cornstarch, flour, vanilla, melted butter and sour cream.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into large greased and floured spring-form pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Take out of oven immediately and cool on top of stove for 2 hours. Refrigerate overnight.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion with oleo.
Cook broccoli and drain. Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cold chicken curry salad
directions: Combine ingredients and serve over lettuce with fresh fruit.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Melt oleo in large, heavy pan over medium heat.
Mix salt and flour; stir into melted oleo, making a white paste.
Gradually add milk.
When this thickens (not too thick), add the cheese, then the broccoli.

title: sweet bread(bread machine)
directions: Put dry yeast in inner pot.
Add all ingredients, except water.
Carefully pour in warm water.
Press the select button for "light".
Press the start button.
After taking out the baked bread from the bread oven, let cool, then slice as desired.

title: recipe for living
directions: I love its every nook,

title: 14 day cucumber pickles
directions: Cover cucumbers and salt with water; let cucumbers sit in water for 9 days.
Drain off water and then cover with boiling water with blue stone for 1 day.
Drain off and cover with boiling water and alum for 1 day.
Drain off and cover with vinegar, sugar and spice; heat to boiling.
Cover for 3 days and put in jars and seal on third day.

title: bread sticks
directions: Mix and knead until smooth.
Let rise once.
Punch down.
Roll dough in rectangle about 1/2 inch thick.
Cut in strips 3/4 inch wide or so.
Twist and place on greased baking sheet.
Brush with 1 beaten egg with 1 Tbsp water.
Add a sprinkle of seasoning salt or garlic salt, which ever you prefer.
Bake right away at 350° till light brown.

title: strawberries
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients in a bowl and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Form into balls like strawberries.
Put sugar in a bag or bowl and color red.
Roll strawberries in colored sugar.
Put slivered almonds in bag or bowl and color green.
Use the almonds as stems.

title: mary adams' no cook ice cream
directions: Beat eggs; gradually add sugar.
Add half and half milk as you
continually
stir.
Add
whipping cream;
beat again. The mixture appears thick.
It means you're doing a good job. Pour
in cylinder.	Add
homogenized
milk	in
the ice cream cylinder until
it fills to the top.
Do not allow the milk to overflow. You will need rock salt and ice to freeze.

title: crusted lime snow
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water. Chill until partly set. Beat stiffly until frothy; fold in egg whites. Pour into 9-inch square pan. Top with 1/3 of wheat germ flakes and crumbs. Chill. When chilled, cut into cubes. Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.

title: strawberry rhubarb pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt and sprinkle a small amount in unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Combine remaining sugar mixture with rhubarb and strawberries.
Put in pie shell and dot with butter. Bake in preheated 425° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: fluffy strawberry pie
directions: Chill the can of evaporated milk for 1 hour.
Beat egg yolks and combine in a heavy 1-quart saucepan with strawberries, water, sugar, salt and lemon juice.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a full, all-over boil.
Remove from heat and add Jell-O, stirring until dissolved.
Chill until mixture is thick but not set.
Beat egg whites until stiff; set aside.
Beat evaporated milk until stiff.
Combine with egg whites and fold into the chilled strawberry mixture.
Pour in crusts and chill until ready to serve.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Mix together.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes. Uncover last 20 minutes.

title: matzo apple pudding *
directions: Stir sugar with the beaten yolks.
Add apples, lemon rind, meal and lastly, stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in greased souffle dish at 350° for 3/4 hour.
Sprinkle chopped almonds on top and bake until brown.

title: quick mexican casserole
directions: Spread Fritos in cake pan.
Sprinkle on grated cheese.
Cover with heated chili.
Broil until cheese melts (not long).
Cover with lettuce, tomatoes, etc.
Serve with salsa and guacamole.

title: stewed okra and vegetables
directions: Thoroughly rinse okra; drain well.
Combine okra, corn, tomatoes, butter, salt and pepper in large skillet.
Cover; simmer for 15 to 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle with bacon. Makes 8 servings.

title: stuffed zucchini(serve as a main dish.)
directions: Wash zucchini well and cut off stem end.
Using apple corer, hollow zucchini; be careful not bo bore to the skin, then put in a salty water for 5 minutes.
Then drain it.
Soak rice in hot water for 1/2 hour.
Mix meat, rice, onion, parsley, spices, vegetable oil and salt.
Fill zucchini with stuffing.
Arrange zucchini with stuffing.
Arrange zucchini layer in a based pan. Put a plate over the zucchini.
Add tomato, water and tomato puree.
When it starts boiling, cover and put it on medium heat for 1 hour or until tender.
Cover the pan.
When it is cooked, add crushed garlic and sprinkle over the dry mint.
Let it boil for 2 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6 persons.

title: corned beef
directions: Put first 5 ingredients in heavy roaster and simmer one hour per pound.
When nearly done, add the vegetables.
To serve, slice beef and place on platter putting vegetables around the meat.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Place each chicken breast half between two pieces of wax paper. Use a meat mallet to flatten each piece to 1/4-inch thickness. Salt and pepper chicken.

title: chewy brownies
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar, cocoa, flour and vanilla.
Add eggs and mix well.
Stir in nuts.

title: sugar-free pie
directions: Combine cream cheese and equal.
Add 2 cups milk, then add sugar-free pudding.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill.

title: garden pea mixture
directions: Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Spread peas and soup evenly in casserole.
Crumble crackers in butter to absorb.
Bake at 325° until brown.

title: pineapple crunch
directions: Use an 8 x 11 1/2-inch glass baking dish.
Pour pineapple in bottom of dish. Sprinkle dry cake mix over pineapple.
Melt butter. Sprinkle over cake mix.
Bake at 350° until brown. Shake the dish during baking to blend the cake mix.
When cool, spread Cool Whip over top. Garnish with pecans.

title: chicken curry
directions: Combine soup, broth, cheese, mayonnaise, curry powder and lemon juice; cook until cheese melts.
Place broccoli in bottom of dish.
Put chicken on top.
Pour soup mixture over all.
Sprinkle dressing on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: classic pecan pie
directions: In medium bowl, combine eggs, sugar, corn syrup, butter and vanilla.
Add pecans and pour into unbaked crust.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Add no seasoning.
Drain and add 1/2 stick butter and Velveeta cheese.
Stir all together.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Top with 1/4-inch of rolled Ritz cracker crumbs. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: pizza(kids kitchen)
directions: Sauce and cheese and put it in the oven and it comes out a pizza.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix and pour into a greased 8 x 8 x 2 dish.

title: mexican stew
directions: Mix ground beef, meal, onion, salt and pepper.
Shape into small balls about the size of a quarter.
Brown in oil.
Drain off fat.
Add chili mix and stir.
Add rest of ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Turn down and simmer for 1 hour.

title: coconut chess pie
directions: Bake pie crust 4 to 5 minutes at 425°
with aluminum foil over piecrust and pie weights in crust.
Take weights and aluminum foil off crust and continue baking until golden.
Cool completely. Stir sugar and next 7 ingredients until blended.
Add eggs, stirring well.
Stir in 1 cup toasted flaked coconut before pouring into piecrust.
Bake at at 350° for about an hour.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream butter and cheese.
Add other ingredients.
Make into balls and press cookies onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Makes 20 servings.

title: potato cheese puff
directions: Chop onion finely. Beat eggs.
Mix all ingredients and pour into baking pan. Bake at 375° for 50 minutes or until the blade of a knife sticks in the center and comes out clean. Serve at once. Makes 6 servings.

title: hot fruit drink
directions: Combine
water, brown sugar, cinnamon sticks and cloves in large
Dutch oven.	Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer 10
minutes.
Stir mixture, discarding cinnamon sticks and
whole cloves.
Add
pineapple, orange and lemon juice to sugar
mixture in
Dutch	oven.
Cook
over medium heat until mixture is thoroughly heated.	Serve hot.
Yields 6 cups.

title: pasta pizza
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
Mix in eggs, milk and Cheddar cheese.
Spread macaroni mixture in bottom of buttered pizza pan.
Brown beef with onion; drain.
Add sauce and spices.
Spread over macaroni base.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and green pepper.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: smoked sausage supper
directions: In medium-sized skillet, cook onion and green pepper in butter until tender; do not brown.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste and seasonings.
Simmer on low for ten minutes.
Cook sausage at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Cover beans with cold water in a large mixing bowl.
Let soak overnight.
Drain beans and discard soaking water.
Place in large cooking pot with sausage slices, onion, celery, pepper, garlic, parsley and bay leaves.
Cover with water and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add salt, black pepper, hot pepper sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook 30 minutes longer or until beans test done.

title: chicken crescent wreath
directions: Arrange crescent rolls on a 12 inch pizza pan, forming a ring with pointed ends facing the outer edge of the pan and wide ends overlapping.
Combine the remaining ingredients; spoon over wide ends of rolls.
Fold points over filling and tuck under wide ends. (Filling will be visible.)
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water and let cool. Add remaining ingredients and pour into mold. Allow to gel.

title: creamy chocolate frosting
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa in saucepan.
Add milk.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly until it begins to boil.
Boil for 3 minutes, or until a teaspoonful will form a soft ball in cold water.
Add vanilla.
Cool; beat until thick and creamy. Spread on cake.
This is enough for 3 layers.

title: pork chop and potato casserole
directions: Layer in pan or dish potatoes, bell pepper, onions and bits of butter and 1 teaspoon flour.
Repeat layers until dish is half full.
Salt and pepper each layer.
Place pork chops on top.
Pour enough milk in dish to cover half the layers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until the potatoes are soft.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown onion and ground beef in skillet.
Add tomato soup, mushroom soup, cooked rice, peas, salt and pepper; mix well.
Put into casserole dish.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.
You may sprinkle top with grated cheese, then return to oven until cheese melts.

title: tasty fruit drink
directions: Mix all juices together in a large glass with the soda.
Add ice to chill.
Makes a refreshing drink.
Combinations and amounts can be changed according to taste as it is mixed.

title: cherry cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar, add 1/8 cup flour, cherries and nuts. Stir slowly and
add
the
rest
of the flour and liquid mixture (milk and
juice).
Last,
fold
in beaten egg whites. Bake in a moderate
oven
at 350° about 25 to 30 minutes.
Ice with 7-Minute Frosting, tinted pink.

title: party punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid by package directions.
Add orange juice and sherbet.
Add 7-Up last.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Place in casserole dish.
Crush 1 cup cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Pour melted oleo on top.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 20 minutes or until light brown.

title: southern green beans
directions: String beans and break in 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Wash.
Fill a 3-quart saucepan with water and add meat.
Cook (covered) approximately 20 minutes.
Add beans, salt and sugar.
Cook about 45 minutes to an hour or until beans are tender and liquid is cooked down.

title: chicken vermicelli
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper and celery in oil. Add tomato sauce, mushroom soup and salt and pepper to taste.
Add red pepper, then cooked chicken.
Let simmer, then add Velveeta cheese and melt slowly.
Let simmer. Serve over spaghetti.

title: creamy baked cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine. Press firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Add eggs and Realemon brand; mix well.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 50 minutes or until center is set, top with sour cream.
Bake 5 minutes longer.
Cool.
Chill. Serve with raspberry topping, if desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: greek cookies
directions: Cream butter, margarine and sugar; blend in flour.
Roll each cookie into small ball about 1 teaspoonful, press down ball to make cookie; bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350° until brown.
Sprinkle sugar on cookies when they are cooled.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Layer half of peas, pimiento, cheese and eggs in casserole dish.
Repeat layers.
Cover with soup.
Top with buttered crumbs. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: biscuits
directions: Roll dough on floured board 1/4-inch deep.
Butter top of first layer of dough.
Roll second layer (or round); put on top of first layer.
Butter second layer.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until nicely browned.
Separate layers while warm.
Spoon strawberries between layers and over top.
Top with whipped cream.

title: picoso(hot sauce)
directions: Bring all ingredients to boil and cook for 5 minutes.
Put in sterilized jars and seal.
Process for 15 minutes in hot boiling water bath or in pressure cooker at 10 pounds pressure.

title: baked devil's float
directions: Boil together for 5 minutes the first 3 ingredients; place in casserole.
Cream the shortening.
Add sugar gradually and cream well.
Add vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Add nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on the liquid in the casserole.
Cover the surface of the liquid.
Cover and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: grandma's fasnachts
directions: Scald milk and let cool.
Dissolve yeast in warm water and add to sugar, milk, salt and 2 cups flour.
Mix well.
Cover.
Let rise in warm place overnight or until double in bulk.
Cream butter or shortening and sugar.
Add to the risen sponge with beaten eggs and nutmeg.
Stir in as much more flour as mixture will take up to make soft dough.
Let rise again until double in bulk.
Turn out on well floured board.
Roll to 1/2-inch thick. Cut with doughnut cutter.
Let rise again.
Fry in deep hot fat. Drain.
Shake in bag with confectioners sugar.

title: smoked sausage with peppers and onions
directions: Saute pepper and onion in oil until tender.
Add smoked sausage and brown about 10 minutes.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and stewed tomatoes; let simmer for 30 minutes.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Combine sugar, buttermilk and syrup; bring to a boil.
Add margarine and cook to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat; add soda. Use mixer at high speed.
Mix to cake icing stage.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Beat the mixture until it becomes glossy and starts to crystallize.
Drop by teaspoons on wax paper.
If candy gets too hard, place in a pan of warm water.

title: chicken tenders and rice
directions: Lay chicken in a greased baking dish. Mix the rest of the ingredients and pour over the chicken. Sprinkle with garlic powder and black pepper. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: old-fashioned oat cookies
directions: Custard may be made up to 2 days ahead.
Glaze keeps at least 2 weeks.

title: hamburger corn casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion until brown; drain.
Cook noodles by directions on package; drain.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Pour melted butter over bread crumbs and sprinkle over casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Can be halved and frozen.

title: purple punch
directions: Put ice cubes in a large bowl.
Add the grape juice, the orange juice and the ginger ale.
Mix well.
Stir orange slices into the bowl.
Serve in small glasses.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Chop cucumbers, onions, green peppers and pimentos.
Cover with water and pickling sauce.
Let set 2 to 3 hours.
Drain and mix in sugar, flour, celery seed, dry red pepper, turmeric and vinegar.
Heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Pour into hot jars and seal.
Makes 8 to 10 pints.

title: easy chicken with japanese vegetables(low in fat)
directions: Brown 2 cut up fryers in oil in a heavy skillet or Dutch oven. Drain well and blot dry.
Return to pan and add soy sauce.
Cook covered in oven at 325° (or simmer covered on top of range) for 30 to 40 minutes (until almost tender).
Add vegetables.
Cover and cook for additional 3 to 4 minutes.
Don't overcook vegetables; they should be Oriental-crunchy.

title: my favorite "2 of everything" cake
directions: Melt unsweetened chocolate with margarine.
Measure and place in sifter in large mixing bowl the flour, sugar and soda.
Break eggs into measuring cup and add enough milk to make 2 cups and the vanilla.
Add the melted margarine and chocolate and mix until all ingredients are well blended.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.
Frost with Easy Frosting or your favorite.

title: lemon poppy seed muffins
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Line 18 muffin cups with paper baking cups. Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In large bowl, combine flour and cake mix; blend well.
To prepare streusel, place 2/3 cup flour-cake mix mixture in small bowl; add margarine.
Blend with fork until mixture resembles coarse crumbs; set aside.
To flour-cake mixture in large bowl, add water, oil, eggs and poppy seed.
Stir 75 strokes by hand or until mixture is just smooth. Fill muffin cups 1/2 full, sprinkle each with 1 tablespoon streusel mixture.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove immediately from pan; serve warm.
Makes 18 muffins.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle coconut in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle pecans on top of coconut.
Mix cake mix according to directions on box; pour on top of pecans.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and softened margarine together with electric mixer or by hand.
Pour this mixture on top of cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: In ovenproof bowl, stir egg until yellow and creamy.
Stir in milk, sweetener (not Equal) and vanilla.
Break bread into small chunks.
Save 3 or 4 pieces to float on top.
Mix the remainder of the bread into egg mixture.
Float the rest of the bread on top. Sprinkle with nutmeg or cinnamon, if desired.

title: orange syrup
directions: Dissolve sugar and water.
Quarter orange (leave the peel on), but don't cut through the peel at the bottom; the orange will then open up like a flower.
Place the orange in a pan with the sugar and water.
Cook to a syrup (do not cook too long; it will go to sugar).
Serve over hot biscuits.

title: spinach dip(yields 5 to 6 cups)
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and chill 4 hours before serving.
Serve with Wheat Thins.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Spray or butter a shallow baking dish. Layer 1 1/2 cans green beans in the bottom of the dish and then lay cheese slices over the beans. Spread 1/2 the mushroom soup over cheese, then the rest of the green beans.
Mix remaining soup and milk; pour over mixture. Put the bread crumbs on top and dot with margarine. Bake, uncovered, at 350° until lightly browned, about 45 minutes.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Remove any damaged leaves and core from cabbage head and wash. Immerse head into boiling water to loosen leaves.
Steam leaves about 3 minutes.
Drain.
Cool.
Cut hard stem from leaves.
Brown pork and onion in medium skillet.
Drain.
In large bowl, combine celery, oat bran, egg whites, parsley, 1 teaspoon caraway seed, salt, pepper, 3/4 cup tomato sauce and pork.
Place 1/4 cup of mix at stem end of leaf.
Roll around pork mix.
Place in baking dish. Cover with remaining tomato sauce.
Sprinkle with reserved caraway seed.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Combine the sugar, cocoa, flour, and salt in a heavy saucepan. Mix well, using the back of a spoon to break up any small lumps of flour or cocoa. Add the yolks and gradually stir in the milk until the mixture is smooth. Place over medium to medium high heat and cook, stirring constantly, for about 5 minutes or until the mixture thickens. Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and butter. Pour into baked pie crust and top with meringue. Bake according to meringue recipe used for coconut cream pie.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Bring to boil the German Sweet chololate, oleo, water, and cocoa.
Add buttermilk and eggs.
Beat well and pour into greased and floured (1 in. high, 17 3/4 in. long, 11 3/4 in. wide) pan. The mixture will be liquid-like.
Cook on 400° for 20 minutes.

title: old-fashioned macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place macaroni, cheese, salt, pepper and ham in layers in a buttered casserole dish.
Pour milk over all.
Spread crackers over top.
Dot with butter.
Bake 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pioneer bread
directions: Pour cornmeal slowly into boiling water with 1 teaspoon salt. Stir until it cooks thick.
Pour into a large bowl to cool. Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water with 1 tablespoon sugar.
Add milk, shortening, brown sugar and salt to cornmeal mixture.
Add yeast and 2 cups flour.
Mix until smooth.
Add enough flour until dough can be taken out and knead on a floured surface.
Knead until smooth and elastic, about 10 minutes.
Place dough in a large greased bowl.
Cover; let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down and turn out onto floured surface.
Cut in 3 pieces; shape into loaves.
Let rise until almost double in bulk.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes and bread is nicely browned.

title: refrigerator cake
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugar until creamy.
Add the egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Lightly drain the pineapple.
Add the pineapple, vanilla and pecans; blend well.

title: very easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix peanut butter, oil, water and eggs.
Add cake mix and mix thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press top with fork.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes or until lightly brown. Bake at 350°.
Makes about 48 cookies.

title: beef mushroom
directions: Sprinkle meat with tenderizer; pierce each piece with a fork. Cover and put in fridge for 2 to 24 hours.
In large skillet, brown meat in oil over medium heat.
Reduce heat and stir in gravy. Cover lightly and simmer for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally. Cook noodles as directed on package; drain.
Serve beef and gravy on noodles with your favorite vegetable.

title: chocolate eauclaire cake
directions: Boil water and oleo.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flour, then add one egg at a time.
Spread in greased jelly roll pan (seems very thin).
Bake at 400° until browned, about 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: orange drop cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Mix shortening, sugar and egg thoroughly. Stir in orange juice. Stir dry ingredients together. Blend in. Drop rounded teaspoonfuls of dough about 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until slightly brown on edges.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Put sliced potatoes into 9 x 13-inch pan (sprayed with Pam first).
Salt and pepper to taste.
Slice butter on put on top of potatoes.
Pour milk over to cover potatoes.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes until done.

title: squash pats
directions: Cook squash according to package directions; drain well.
Mash squash and add egg; stir well.
Combine flour, cornmeal, baking powder and salt; stir well.
Add squash mixture and onion; stir. Drop squash mixture by heaping tablespoonfuls into hot oil.
Cook until golden brown.
Turn and flatten.
Drain on towel.
Yields 15 patties.

title: chocolate clusters
directions: Melt chocolate pieces, margarine and marshmallows in large saucepan over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Remove from heat; mix in vanilla, coconut, oatmeal and pecans thoroughly.
Spread on wax paper on cookie sheet.
Chill until firm.
Break in pieces.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream butter and peanut butter; gradually add sugars and beat well.
Add egg, milk and vanilla; mix well.
Blend in flour, baking soda and salt gradually.
Roll a teaspoon of dough into balls.
Roll balls in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and place a solid milk chocolate kiss on top of each cookie, pressing down so that the cookie cracks around the edge.
Return to oven; bake 2 to 5 minutes longer.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: crispy potatoes with bacon, garlic and parsley
directions: Put the potatoes in a saucepan and cover with cold water. Bring to a boil over high heat and simmer for 1 minute and then drain. Pat dry.

title: dog bones for pooch
directions: Mix all together.
Roll out on floured board.
Cut into shapes.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Dogs really do love these!

title: microwave instant oatmeal
directions: Put water in measuring cup.
Microwave 1 minute and 30 seconds. Pour oatmeal pack in bowl.
Pour hot water over and stir.
Serve hot.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Sprinkle the chicken pieces on all sides with salt and pepper. Heat the butter in a heavy skillet and when hot, add the chicken pieces skin side down.
Cook until browned on one side, about 5 minutes.
Turn the pieces and add the shallots and garlic.
Cook about 10 seconds, then add the lemon rind.
Cook about 2 minutes. Scatter the lemon slices over all and pour the wine over the chicken.
Cover and reduce heat to low.
Let simmer 10 minutes. Remove chicken pieces to a warmed platter and keep hot.
Let the sauce cook down over high heat until reduced by half.
Pour the sauce over the chicken and sprinkle with parsley.

title: pork balls
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients.
Shape into 16 balls.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix the brown sugar, mustard and vinegar. Cook over medium heat until boiling.
Pour over balls.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy mocha cheese cake
directions: Mix crumbs, sugar and butter thoroughly with fork in a 9-inch pie plate until crumbs are well moistened. Press firmly against sides of plate, first using finger or large spoon to shape edges. Press remaining crumbs firmly onto bottom, using measuring cup.

title: cap'n crunch clusters
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler; stir in nuts and Cap'n Crunch cereal.
Spoon out on waxed paper; let cool.

title: pantry coleslaw
directions: Blend together mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar and oil.
Add spice powders, pepper, lemon juice, half and half and salt.
Stir until smooth.
Pour over coleslaw in a large bowl and toss until cabbage is well coated.
Refrigerate.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cornflake treats
directions: Melt marshmallows with 1/2 stick of butter; slowly add cornflakes, then chocolate chips.
Add 1/2 cup pecan pieces (optional).
Mash into pan.
Refrigerate.
Cut and serve when cool.

title: strawberry divinity
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring	constantly.
Reduce
heat;
cook,
stirring occasionally, until
mixture
reaches hard ball stage or 260°. Beat egg
whites
until stiff.
Add jello to egg whites.
Pour thin stream
of cooked mixture over egg white mixture, beating constantly.
Beat
as
long as possible until mixture is stiff and loses gloss.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Makes 2 pounds.

title: cocktail oyster crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients
and pour over crackers. Stir until all crackers are
covered.
Bake
in a 250° preheated oven for 30 minutes, stirring often. Store in airtight container.

title: elderberry pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix sugar, flour, salt and cinnamon together.
Blend through berries using a fork.
Pour into pie shell.
Pour lemon juice over top and dot with butter.
Cover with top crust.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes at 425°.
Serve slightly warm.

title: south carolina macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on the box.
Do not overcook! Rinse with cold water and drain well.
Combine cheese, macaroni, pimento, onion and green pepper.
Stir in mayonnaise.
Add mushrooms and soup and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: cream cheese sweeties
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Unroll 1 can crescent roll dough; press into ungreased 8 x 12-inch baking dish, sealing perforations.
Beat cream cheese, sugar, egg yolk and vanilla until smooth.
Spread over dough.
Unroll remaining dough, sealing perforations.
Place over filling.
Brush with egg white.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Mix milk and confectioners sugar, stirring until desired consistency.
Spread over top.
Cut into squares.
Makes 16 servings.

title: garlic and tomato salad(russia)
directions: Put the chopped tomatoes in a salad bowl, add garlic and salt to taste. Allow to sit for a few minutes so the juices come out of the tomatoes. Add a small amount of oil, toss, and serve.

title: fideo pronto
directions: Heat bacon drippings in medium size skillet.
Add uncooked vermicelli; saute over medium flame, stirring constantly, until golden brown.
Add tomatoes and sugar.
Cover and steam for 8 minutes, or
until vermicelli is firm, but tender to taste.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle with Parmesan, if desired.
Serves 5.

title: frito black-eyed pea salad
directions: Mix beans, onion and green pepper and store overnight.
Add remaining ingredients before serving.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: polish potato and sausage soup
directions: In large pot, melt butter.
Add sausage, onion and celery. Cook until onion and celery are tender.
Add remaining ingredients, except potatoes.
Cover and cook for 1 1/2 hours. Add potatoes and cook 20 minutes longer.
Serve with hot rolls and salad.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Stir in eggs and vanilla. Sift flour with baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg. Gradually stir the flour mixture into the butter mixture.
On a lightly floured board, roll the dough out thin, about 1/8-inch and cut into fancy shapes.
Bake on lightly buttered cookie sheets at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes until cookies are a light golden brown.

title: brunch snack
directions: Spread chilies in bottom of a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Mix cheese and eggs; pour on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut in small squares and serve on Triscuits while still warm.

title: chilies rellenos
directions: Grease 8-inch square baking pan.
Drain green chilies and sprinkle evenly on bottom.
Pour eggs over chilies and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Cool 5 minutes and cut into squares.

title: peek-a-boo chicken
directions: Melt 1/2 stick of margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle uncooked rice over margarine.
Pour milk over rice.
In separate bowl, combine soups; spoon over rice.
Place chicken pieces over mixture and sprinkle dry onion soup on top.
Seal tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Do not peek!
Serves 4.

title: fudge sauce
directions: Heat butter over low heat until melted.
Stir in cocoa, corn syrup and sugar until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients; heat to boiling.
Boil and stir until sugar is dissolved and sauce is smooth, about 1 minute.

title: easy green bean casserole
directions: Mix the beans and mushroom soup in a baking dish.
Top with cheese, then onions.
Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Combine celery, onion and butter in microwave-safe dish. Microwave for 2 to 3 minutes on High.
In large bowl mix all ingredients together.
Pour in large baking dish sprayed with Pam. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Dressing should be lightly browned.
Serve immediately.

title: aunt mamie's strawberry shortcake
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
Let cool.
Thaw strawberries.
Combine sugar, butter and vanilla in mixing bowl. Add Pet milk until it is spreading consistency.
Frost cake; top with strawberries.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in casserole.
Mix chicken soup and wine and pour over the chicken. Top with Swiss cheese and cover with a thick layer of dressing.
Dribble some butter over dressing. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: ham and vegetable chowder
directions: In 2 qt. casserole, combine celery and butter.
Microwave at HIGH for 3 to 4 minutes, or until celery is tender.

title: chicken and stuffing casserole
directions: Place chicken breasts in greased flat casserole (9 x 13-inch) Pyrex dish.
Cover with sliced cheese.
Mix milk and soup and pour over chicken.
Mix stuffing mix with melted butter.
Pat down over chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Recipe can be doubled for large group.

title: sweet cream rhubarb pie
