directions: Melt butter and add rhubarb and 1 cup sugar.
Cook slowly 10 minutes.
Mix 1/4 cup sugar, cornstarch, egg yolks, cream and salt.
Add to rhubarb mixture and cook until thick.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with whipped cream or meringue.

title: stuffed chicken supreme(serves 6)
directions: Cut chicken breasts in half.
Place between two sheets of waxed paper and pound a little flatter.
Grate 1/2 cup of the cheese; cut the rest into six sticks, each of the size to fit into a chicken breast.
Place the chopped herbs on a plate and roll the cheese sticks around in them until they are coated.
Roll each 1/2 chicken breast around a cheese stick and place seam side down in a buttered 2-quart baking dish.
Top each chicken breast with 1/2 slice of bacon.
Blend together soup, tomato sauce, grated cheese and sour cream; spread over chicken.
Sprinkle with pimiento and chopped herbs, if any are leftover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix. Chill this together. When ready to eat, pour over the broccoli mix and toss.

title: chicken fried steak
directions: Heat oil in electric skillet.
Have oil 1/2-inch deep.
Heat to 400°.
Soak steak well in salted water.
Dip to coat well in flour.
Put in hot oil.
Turn only when edges are brown.
Lift from skillet with slotted spatula.
Serve with cream gravy.

title: creamy baked chicken breasts
directions: Arrange chicken in greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese slices.
Combine soup and wine, stirring well.
Spoon sauce evenly over chicken and sprinkle on stuffing mix.
Drizzle butter over crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: instant country apple tea
directions: Combine all ingredients in a tall glass and blend. Add ice cubes. Serves 1.

title: peanut butter zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Stir in zucchini.
Combine dry ingredients; add to mixture.
Blend well.
Stir in peanut butter, nuts and raisins (if desired).

title: jim wagner's microwave omelet
directions: Grease the bottom of a 2-quart microwave dish.
Lay the cheese slices on the bottom.
Mix everything else together and pour over the cheese.
Cover with Saran Wrap.
Microwave for 6 minutes on High.
Stir and rotate dish.
Bake 6 minutes longer on High (or longer if needed).
Enjoy!
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fresh strawberry cake
directions: Mix as directed on box and bake in 3 layers.
Cool completely.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Combine
cream	cheese, condensed milk, lemon juice and Cool Whip.
Layer
your	dish
with
vanilla wafers.
Combine strawberries and
pie
filling; then put a layer of strawberry mixture on	vanilla wafers.
Put a layer of Cool Whip mixture. Repeat the layers.	Chill.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain all liquid off of the green beans, Shoepeg corn, mushrooms and water chestnuts.
Mix with the soup, Cheddar cheese and sour cream.
Pour into casserole dish and top with the Ritz crackers (mixed with melted butter/margarine).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: golden cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in flour, 1/2 cup at a time.
Add flavorings.
Pour batter into greased 8-inch tube pan, greased and floured.
Sprinkle batter with nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: ooey-gooey butter cake
directions: In 13 x 9-inch pan, melt margarine.
Add 2 eggs and box of yellow cake mix.
Mix well in pan until lumps are gone.
In separate bowl, mix cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar. Spread over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Sprinkle powdered sugar over top.

title: squash apple casserole
directions: Make layers of squash and then apples in an 8 x 8-inch pan. End with a layer of apples.
Sprinkle cinnamon and nutmeg on top. Cover pan with foil and bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes. Remove foil and bake 10 to 15 minutes more.
Serves 4.

title: seafood queso
directions: Heat wine in a double boiler over low heat.
Place cheese in a plastic bag and sprinkle flour over cheese, shaking bag to coat all.
When wine gets bubbles forming on top, place one handful of cheese into wine.
Stir until melted and continue to add cheese until all is melted and smooth.
Keep warm.
Warm seafood and salsa in a fondue pot.
Pour cheese over hot seafood mixture and gently stir.
Serve with corn tortilla chips.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mexican rice
directions: In large skillet, pour in low-fat shortening.
Heat.
Add rice.
Cook over medium heat until brown.
Add 4 cups water, tomatoes, sliced onion and garlic sauce.
Stir well.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: german dinner
directions: Combine onions and margarine.
Cover and cook about 5 minutes over medium heat.
Stir in mustard.
Add the sausage.
Cook, covered, 10 to 12 minutes.
Serve with bread.

title: lasagne for two
directions: Saute beef and garlic in oil until meat is browned; drain. Add tomato sauce, salt, pepper and oregano; cover and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain.
Layer half of noodles, Mozzarella cheese, Ricotta, meat sauce and Parmesan cheese in a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Yields 2.
Double recipe for 4 or more people.

title: broccoli and mushrooms(microwave dish)
directions: In a 3-quart casserole, combine broccoli and water; cover and microwave for 1 minute on High.
Drain and rinse in cold water. In a bowl or plastic bag, combine broccoli, mushrooms and dressing.
Refrigerate at least 8 hours.
If using a bowl, stir several times.
With a bag, just turn bag over several times. Remove vegetables to serving platter with slotted spoon.

title: quick rice pudding
directions: Combine first three ingredients listed.
Mix pudding and milk; beat slowly until blended (about 2 minutes).
Stir in cool rice and chill.
Add a dash of nutmeg if desired on top.

title: ham hot dish
directions: Mix together in a large casserole dish the macaroni, bread, celery, onion, ham, eggs and cheese.
Heat together the margarine, soup and milk; pour over other ingredients.
Mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate yule log
directions: Whip chilled cream in deep bowl with chilled beaters.
Beat only until soft peaks form.
Do not overbeat.
Fold in extract. Spread the whipped cream on one wafer at a time, sticking together to form a roll.
Use the same serving dish you wish to use.
Save wafers for the "knot".

title: easy beer rolls
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add egg and vanilla and blend in the flour.
Divide into log shaped rolls.
Cover with plastic. Refrigerate or freeze until well chilled.
Slice rolls and place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Sprinkle with sugar while still warm.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand until well blended.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13 pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Frost in pan while warm.

title: quick fish soup
directions: Cook onions and garlic in oil in a large, heavy pan, until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until fish flakes easily with fork, about 5 minutes.
Makes 8 servings (about 1 1/4 cups each).
Contains 210 calories per serving.

title: golden carrot pie
directions: Combine carrots, eggs, salt and spices.
Mix well.
Add milk and honey.
Blend until smooth.
Pour in pie shells and bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with Pam.
Mix together all ingredients.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Store left over in refrigerator.
Based on 12 servings: 176 Calories, 11 g. Fat, 301 mg. Sodium and 73 mg.
Cholesterol.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients together slowly until 238° or soft ball stage in cold water.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and butter.
Let stand without stirring until lukewarm.
Beat until creamy and candy has lost all shine.
Pour onto a greased pan. Cut into squares.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread pie filling on bottom of greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Arrange pineapple chunks over cherries.
Sprinkle cake mix over fruit and dribble melted margarine over it.
Sprinkle coconut over top of margarine.
Nuts may be sprinkled on top, if desired.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar, molasses and eggs.
Mix together dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with water.
Stir well.
This makes a very soft dough.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake in 375° oven 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Wash and scrape carrots; cut in diagonal slices.
Cook, covered, in small amount of boiling, salted water until just tender, about 12 minutes.
Drain.

title: apple muffins
directions: Sift flour with baking powder, salt and spices.
Add cereal, walnuts, raisins and apple. Beat eggs well.
Add honey, milk and oil.
Add raised mixture all at once to flour mixture, stirring to blend.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full or use cupcake papers. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes, until golden brown.
Makes 18 muffins.

title: diabetic fruit cake
directions: Simmer-cook raisins in water until water is gone.
Remove from heat.
Add applesauce, eggs, sweetener and margarine; mix well. Sift the dry ingredients together.
Blend all together and add vanilla; pour into greased loaf or tube pan.
Add nuts if desired. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: parmesan party-rye rounds
directions: Combine cheese, mayonnaise, onion and cayenne.
Spread on 20 slices party-rye bread.
Put under the broiler just until bubbling. Serve hot.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken breasts, salt, pepper and oil until done; save the broth left over from boiled chicken. In a large bowl, mix together soups, Veg-All (drain most of the liquid off), chicken breasts (cut up) and broth. Pour into a 9 1/2 x 13 1/2 baking dish. Mix together Bisquick, milk and melted butter; pour over chicken mixture. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: sausage lasagna wraps
directions: Cook and drain lasagna noodles.
Divide sausage in 6 pieces; split lengthwise and stuff with 1/2 slice Mozzarella.
Wrap each piece in a noodle.
Place in baking dish.
Cover with sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate crinkle cookies
directions: Mix oil, chocolate and sugar.
Blend in 1 egg at a time until well
mixed.
Add
vanilla.
Stir
in
flour,
salt and baking powder.
Chill
for
several hours or overnight.
Heat oven
Drop teaspoonfuls of dough into confectioners sugar.
Roll around and shape into ball.
Place 2-inches apart on
greased cookie
sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes approximately 5 dozen cookies.

title: venetian cream torte(this is my favorite easter cake)
directions: Step One:
Lightly grease bottom of three 9-inch round cake pans.
Line with wax paper and cut to fit bottoms.
Grease wax paper.
Set aside.

title: low-fat tuna casserole
directions: Put soup in bowl; add enough milk to make smooth.
Cook noodles.
Drain.
Put noodles in casserole dish.
Add tuna.
Then pour soup over top.
Bake in a 325° oven for about 20 to 30 minutes or in microwave until nice and bubbly.

title: oreo cheesecake squares
directions: Finely roll 25 cookies; coarsely chop 15 cookies.
In bowl, combine finely rolled cookies and butter.
Press crumb mixture on bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan; set aside.

title: crabs with garlic and butter
directions: In large pot heat beer, vinegar and hot pepper seeds to boil. Add crabs, cover steam for approximately 20 minutes until bright red.
Remove crabs and allow to cool.
In large roaster pan put butter, garlic and paprika.
Heat slowly.
Remove shell and clean crabs of lungs and mustard, put crabs in roaster.
Baste crabs, garnish with Old Bay seasoning and fresh chopped parsley.

title: pumpkin walnut cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, oats, baking soda, cinnamon and salt. Cream the butter and sugar, beating until light and fluffy. Add egg and vanilla.
Mix well.

Add pumpkin and mix well. Add dry ingredients and then walnuts. Drop by heaping teaspoonful onto lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake 20 to 25 minutes until cookies are firm and lightly browned. Remove from cookie sheet. Cool on rack.

title: grenadine punch
directions: In a large bowl or pitcher, combine water and orange juice concentrate; stir to dissolve.
Stir in lemon juice, chilled grenadine syrup and light corn syrup.
Carefully pour over ice cubes in a punch bowl.
Slowly pour in the chilled ginger ale; stir gently to mix.
Makes about 22 (4 ounce) servings.

title: sweet potatoes roasted with garlic
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a small roasting pan, combine the oil and garlic and heat for 5 minutes.
Add potatoes and rosemary, turning the potatoes to coat well with oil.
Turning the potatoes frequently, roast them for 35 minutes or until tender and brown on all sides.
Sprinkle with salt.
Serves 4, 186 calories each.

title: cheese onion bake
directions: Line bottom of small rectangular Pyrex dish with croutons. Sprinkle cheese over croutons.
Sprinkle onions over cheese.
Beat eggs.
Add half and half.
Add salt and pepper to eggs.
Blend well.
Pour over ingredients in baking dish.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in oven preheated to 350°.
Cool somewhat and serve.

title: ice pickles
directions: Dissolve a tube of lime in 1 gallon of water.
Let cucumbers stand 24 hours in lime water.
Rinse 3 times and drain on cloth. Mix vinegar, sugar and seasonings together.
Put cucumbers in this solution and soak 12 hours.
Heat to boiling point.
Put in jars and seal.
Chill before serving.

title: old-fashioned tea cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Sift baking powder with 1 cup flour and add to creamed mixture.
Add enough additional flour to make dough the right consistency to roll.
Roll dough and cut into desired shapes.
Bake at 375°.

title: recipe for life
directions: Mix these thoroughly; add Tears of Joy and Sorrow and Sympathy for others.
Fold in 4 cups of Prayer and Faith to blend with other ingredients and raise the texture to great heights of Christian Living.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy, adding sugar gradually. Blend in vanilla. Add eggs, one at a time.
Combine flour and salt, adding a small amount at a time.
Add buttermilk. Pour filling into unbaked pie crust; bake in preheated 300° oven for 1 1/2 hours. Best served at room temperature. Serves 8.

title: quick scones
directions: Heat oil in a skillet.
Roll tube biscuits flat and fry in hot oil
until
puffy
and
golden
brown.
Place on paper towels. Serve with butter, honey, jam and a piece of bacon.

title: broccoli-cheese dip
directions: Saute celery and onion in margarine until tender.
Add Velveeta and stir over low heat until cheese is melted.
Stir in broccoli and rosemary.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Combine rolled oats and milk; let stand 15 minutes.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt into bowl.
Combine egg, oil and oatmeal mixture.
Add all at once to sifted dry ingredients, stirring just to moisten.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full. Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes about 1 dozen muffins.

title: date, nut & chocolate chip loaf cake
directions: Soak first four ingredients together in a small bowl (preferably over night). Then mix together margarine, sugar, & eggs in a large bowl. Blend into margarine mixture: 3 c. flour - alternate with date mixture, salt, nuts, vanilla, and chocolate chips. Place mixture into greased & floured loaf pans. Makes 2 large or 3 small loaves. Bake at 350° for about 60-70 minutes.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Grease a 5 x 9-inch loaf pan with margarine.
Put slices of 3 potatoes, chopped onion and salt and pepper.
Add 1 can undiluted cheese soup.
Repeat layers.
Dot with a generous amount of margarine or butter on top.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: pineapple and nut cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs, pineapple and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Drop by spoonful onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: little buckaroo snack
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store in tight container.
Yields 3 1/2 cups.

title: strawberry delight
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve jello in hot water.
Stir in pineapple and pie filling.
Add nuts and pour into long dish. Refrigerate until congealed.

title: corn dogs
directions: Sift together corn meal & flour.
Slightly beat egg and add 1 c. milk.
Stir in above ingredients.
Add 2 Tbsp.
melted fat. Dip wieners (1 lb.) in batter and deep fry in hot fat.
Drain on waxed paper.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar together until light.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Add buttermilk and canned milk alternately with flour.
Add flavoring; beat about 3 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake in preheated 300° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Place small can of water on bottom rack.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Scrub potatoes, but do not peel.
Cut each potato lengthwise (4 to 6 wedges).
Place in shallow pan with skin side down.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Brush 2 tablespoons on potatoes.
Bake for 45 minutes, brushing each 15 minutes.
Turn potatoes and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: cheese olive balls (3 day)
directions: Let cheese set until soft.
Mix in flour and seasoning.
Press bits of mixture around olives.
Bake on greased cookie sheet 10 minutes at 400°.
Serve hot with toothpicks.
Freezes well so can be made ahead.

title: applesauce fudgies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter together.
Mix applesauce, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients into applesauce mixture. Stir until blended; add chocolate and stir well.
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut and cool in pan.

title: cream cheese kiffles
directions: Cream softened cream cheese and butter together.
Add egg yolks and mix thoroughly.
Gradually add flour and mix by hand if you wish.
Divide dough into two large balls.
Wrap each in waxed paper.
Chill for several hours or overnight.
Roll out chilled dough very thin in powdered sugar.
Cut rolled dough into sections approximately 3 x 3-inches.
Fill each square with 1 teaspoon of the nut or fruit filling.
Roll up each square and place on a cold cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown. Roll cooled Kiffles in powdered sugar.
Yields 3 to 4 dozen Kiffles.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all together and boil 25 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Place 1 cup pecans in each pie crust.
Mix the remaining ingredients and pour equal amounts into each pie crust.
Bake at 375° about 50 minutes or until firm.

title: debbie north's delights
directions: In medium bowl combine 1 cup flour and sugar.
Cut in margarine until crumbly.
Press firmly on bottom of pan.
Bake 15 minutes. Meanwhile, in large bowl beat sweetened condensed milk, cocoa, egg, 1/4 cup flour, vanilla and baking powder.
Stir in milk chocolate chunks and nuts.
Spread over crust.
Bake 20 minutes or until center is set.
Store tightly covered at room temperature.

title: bean bread
directions: Combine all ingredients, beating just enough to make a smooth batter. Turn into a greased loaf pan and bake 45 to 50 minutes in a 375° preheated oven.
When top browns and sides pull away from the pan, turn out and cool on a rack.
Delicious warm with butter.

title: tunnel of fudge cake
directions: Generously grease 10-inch Bundt pan.
In large mixer bowl, cream butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Gradually add sugar, creaming until light and fluffy.
By hand, stir in flour, dry frosting mix and walnuts until well blended. Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.
Cool 1 hour; remove from pan. Cool completely before serving.

title: aunt di's pie
directions: Melt margarine; add coconut and pecans.
Toast lightly in oven.
Set aside to cool.
Combine cream cheese and condensed milk using a mixer.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put 1/4 of mixture in each pie shell.
Drizzle 1/4 of caramel on each pie.
Sprinkle with 1/4 coconut mixture; repeat layers.
Freeze well and serve frozen.

title: jeannie's mother's nut roll
directions: Melt margarine and cool.
Beat 5 egg yolks with salt. Dissolve yeast cakes in 1/4 cup warm water.
Mix all together and set aside.

title: potato goodie
directions: Blend all ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan or other desired shapes.
Bake at 350° until a toothpick comes out clean (about 50 minutes).
Sift powdered sugar on top when cake is cool.

title: classic pecan pie
directions: This recipe was taken from the back of a Karo syrup bottle. This pecan pie has been a favorite of my family and friends.

title: date-nut bread
directions: Mix dates, boiling water, butter, white sugar and salt and set aside to cool.
Add egg.
Sift together flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Add to cooled mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts; mix well. Put in greased loaf pan dusted with flour.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 350°.

title: finger jello
directions: In large bowl, mix unflavored gelatine with flavored gelatin. Add boiling water and stir until dissolved.
Pour into pan and chill until firm.
Cut and serve.

title: glazed donuts
directions: Make only 1 batch at a time.
We use 13-quart mixing bowl. Do not overmix.

title: cornish game hens with apricot chutney
directions: Rinse and dry Cornish game hens. Place in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Mix five other ingredients together and use to baste chicken, brushing on during final 10 to 15 minutes of cooking.
This glaze can also be used for lamb or pork.

title: coconut cake and nuts
directions: Cook cake mix in square pan.
Remove from oven.
While cake is hot, punch holes in cake.
Pour Eagle Brand milk on top.
Pour on cream of coconut.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Put in refrigerator and chill.
Use large tub of Cool Whip; put on top. Now, sprinkle with Angel Flake coconut.

title: children's thanksgiving turkey(non edible)
directions: You will also need round toothpicks.

title: crescent chicken
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Roll out crescent rolls thinner. Saute onion and bell pepper with celery.
Put 2 tablespoons of chicken, 2 tablespoons grated cheese and the onion and bell pepper mixture into center of each roll.
Roll and place in a
Pyrex dish.
Mix 1 can of soup, 1 cup milk and 1 cup of cheese; pour over rolls.
Bake covered for 30 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and bake another 20 minutes.
Sprinkle paprika and parsley on top before serving.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cut half the meat from bone and brown in a little hot fat. Add remaining meat and bone to 2-quarts cold water.
Add browned meat, onion and 1 teaspoon salt; cook slowly 2 hours.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook 1 hour longer.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: diet chicken pie
directions: Saute vegetables in margarine. Spoon flour over them.
Combine milk and seasonings.
Add to vegetables.
Place in an 8 x 8-inch dish.
Put chicken on top. Cover with biscuits.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until brown.

title: gingerbread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter and honey.
Add eggs; beat well.
Mix hot water and molasses.
Add alternately with dry ingredients.
Bake in greased pan for about 1 hour.

title: mexican delicious
directions: Cook meat and drain.
Crush chips into long cake pan.
Layer part of meat, 1 can of rotel tomatoes, 1 can cream of chicken, refried beans and 2 cups of cheese.
Bake in oven at 350 degrees until cheese is thoroughly melted, approximately 25 minutes.

title: linguini with clam sauce
directions: Heat margarine and peanut oil in a skillet over medium heat. Add garlic and saute 2 minutes or until tender.
Remove skillet from heat.
Stir in half and half, clams and salt.
Return skillet to heat and cook and stir until mixture is heated through.
Do not boil.
Toss clam sauce and parsley with drained hot linguini and serve.

title: creole-style soup
directions: Cut stew meat small; cook in tap water with tenderizer for about 1 hour or until tender.
Add sausage, beef broth, tomato sauce, chopped onions, tomato juice and red beans.
Add seasoning and red pepper to taste.
Continue to cook while adding ingredients.
Add Minute rice slowly to reach desired thickness.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Sift flour; measure and sift again with salt, baking powder and sugar.
Cut in shortening until the coarseness of meal.
Add enough milk to form soft dough, but firm enough to roll.
Cover bowl and let dough stand for 30 to 60 minutes, then roll 1/4 to 1/2 inch thick on lightly floured board and cut in diamond-shaped pieces.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar and Karo in medium pan.
Heat until smooth.
Add peanuts and cook 20 minutes on medium heat, stirring constantly. Peanuts will turn brown when cooked.
Turn off stove.
Add baking soda.
Stir fast and pour in pan.
Cool, then crack.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mix together flour and sugar.
In a saucepan, combine and bring to a boil, oleo, cocoa, Crisco and water.
Pour over flour mixture; stir well and then add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: mint meltaways
directions: Mix butter and cocoa in saucepan and blend in sugar, vanilla, egg, crumbs, coconut and nuts.
Mix well and press into ungreased 11 1/2 x 7 1/2-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Snap off tough ends of asparagus.
Remove scales with vegetable peeler or knife.

Cut asparagus diagonally into 1 1/2-inch pieces. Place asparagus pieces and broccoli flowerets in a vegetable steamer over boiling water; cover and steam 6 to 8 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Remove from heat; set aside.
Saute onion and garlic in oil in a large skillet until tender.
Add carrot and chopped peppers to onion mixture.
Saute until crisp-tender.
Remove from heat; drain.
Combine whipping cream, broth, green onions, basil and salt in a medium skillet.
Cover over medium-high heat; cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook linguine according to package directions.
Drain well.
Place in a large serving bowl.
Add reserved vegetables, whipping cream mixture and sliced mushrooms.
Toss gently.
Serve immediately.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Cook 1 large or 2 to 3 small potatoes in water enough to cover.
While potatoes are cooking, measure out butter, sugar and salt; dissolve yeast in the warm water. Pour off and save 1 cup hot potato water.
(Discard remaining potato water.)
Mash potatoes thoroughly with mixer; add butter, sugar, salt, eggs, yeast each separately and mix well before adding the next ingredients.
Add potato water last and mix well.
Add enough flour to make stiff dough (approximately 7 1/2 to 9 cups).
Turn out on lightly floured surface and knead well until elastic.
Put dough in a buttered bowl and cover well (butter cover also).
Keep in refrigerator.
Dough will keep at least 1 week and must be punched down regularly or bread will sour.
When ready to use, remove amount needed, shape into rolls, place in buttered (or pan greased with shortening) baking pan and let rise in warm place until doubled (1 1/2 to 2 hours).
Bake at 400° until brown and done, approximately 20 minutes.

title: traditional egg nog
directions: Beat yolks until light.
Add sugar until thick.
Stir in milk and rum.
Chill 3 hours.
Fold in whipped cream and chill another hour.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Put all ingredients in large bowl and beat 5 minutes.
Bake at 350° in tube pan (greased and floured) for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Combine sugar, cream and syrup in saucepan.
Bring to boil and cook 10 minutes or until sauce is slightly thickened and light tan in color; add butter and vanilla.
Reheat before serving.
Cut up some apples and dig in!

title: "easy" chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Put the first 7 ingredients together and beat about 2 minutes at high speed.
Put in greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Top with the chocolate chips and walnuts. Bake at 350° for about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: princess di's royal fudge
directions: Butter an 8-inch square
pan.
Place
butter, water and sugar in a heavy saucepan
over
low
heat.
Stir
with wooden spoon until sugar dissolves.
Add milk.
Turn heat to high and bring to boil.
Turn heat to
low and simmer for 40 minutes or until firm ball is achieved.
Stir
from time to time.
Remove from heat. Pour in bowl
over	larger	bowl
with
ice.
With electric beater, beat 10 to	12
minutes until fudge is creamy and holds it shape.
Pour into
pan.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours before cutting into squares.

title: double time cherry slices
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add the dry ingredients and spread all except 1 1/2 cups of batter in a jelly roll pan that is greased.
Add the can of cherries to the top.
Dabble the remaining 1 1/2 cups batter over the cherries. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Drizzle thin powdered sugar frosting over the top when cool.

title: taco salad
directions: Add all ingredients in large bowl and stir together.
Chill for 1/2 hour.

title: ground hog dip
directions: Brown sausage.
Drain.
Mix remaining ingredients and heat until cheese is melted.

title: snickers salad
directions: Combine apples, Snickers and Cool Whip.
Chill for several hours before serving.

title: chicken nicoise
directions: In a frying pan, saute the green pepper, onion and garlic in the oil.
When onions are softened, chop the tomatoes coarsely and add.
Add the tomato paste and use the rest of the liquid from the canned tomatoes to dilute.
Add some of the chicken broth and the bay leaf, thyme, parsley, salt and pepper.
Simmer.

title: chocolate sour cream pound cake
directions: Beat batter at medium speed about 2 minutes or until soft and creamy.
Add sugar, beating at medium speed 5 to 7 minutes.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat until yellow disappears.
Combine flour, baking soda and cocoa.
Add to cream mixture.
Stir in vanilla. Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut beef across grain into thin strips 1/8-inch thick. Combine soy sauce, garlic and ginger.
Add beef; toss and let sit for at least 30 minutes.
Heat oil in large frying pan or wok. Add beef and toss over high heat until browned.
Turn heat up and add vegetables until tender-crisp (about 10 minutes).
Mix cornstarch with water; pour over beef and vegetables and cook until thickened.
Add tomatoes and heat thoroughly.
Serve with your favorite rice.

title: cheese ball
directions: Bring cheese to room temperature.
Mix well and add green onions and parsley.
Roll into 2 balls and roll in paprika. Refrigerate.

title: fudge striped cookie salad
directions: Mix pudding and buttermilk until well blended. Add Cool Whip and mix well. Open oranges and fruit cocktail and drain off juice. Add into pudding mixture. Crumble up cookies and add to salad when you are ready to serve salad. Some cookies can be used to garnish the top of the salad.

title: three-fruit sherbet
directions: Peel and mash small, ripe bananas.
Add the juice of oranges and lemons.
Add sugar and water.
Stir until the sugar is dissolved.
Pour into 2 refrigerator trays and freeze, setting up refrigerator to coldest position.

title: mocha coffee
directions: Combine all ingredients. Double the normal strength. Works better if you use a percolator but can be made in a coffee maker, but will have to be stirred to get cocoa through the filter. Yields about 12 cups brewed coffee.

title: sally morton's chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Sift flour, cocoa, soda and salt.
Add alternately with milk (start with flour) and flavoring to creamed mix.

title: hot dog relish
directions: Grind vegetables using coarse blade.
Sprinkle the salt over the vegetables that were ground and let stand overnight.
Rinse and drain.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over vegetable mixture.
Heat to boiling.
Simmer 3 minutes.
Seal in hot, sterilized jars.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer first five ingredients in salad bowl; dot mayo and sugar over salad, spreading carefully to each side.
Sprinkle cheese over top, bacon bits on cheese if desired.
Make night before (needs to set).

title: applesauce jello
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Add applesauce last and taste.
You may have to add a little more applesauce.
Pour in dessert cups and chill overnight.

title: dump cake
directions: Arrange peach slices evenly on bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour crushed pineapple with juice evenly over peaches. Sprinkle cake mix evenly over the fruit.
Layer nuts on top of cake mix.
Melt butter or margarine and drizzle evenly over the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: spunky vegetable pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Spoon on pizza sauce to crust after putting on pizza or cookie sheet.
Arrange vegetables over sauce. Sprinkle on the cheese.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: cynthia's pound cake
directions: Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
Separate eggs.
Beat egg whites and 6 tablespoons sugar; let stand.
Cream butter and sugar; add yolks, one at a time.
Cream together.
Add vanilla and lemon flavoring.
Mix well.
Add flour, salt and milk; beat.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours or until done.

title: topping for apple walnut cake
directions: Combine above ingredients in saucepan, and simmer until margarine and sugar are melted.
Pour over warm cake.
Place cake under broiler until topping is lightly browned.

title: chicken breasts with broccoli
directions: Butter baking pan.
Brown chicken lightly in pan.
Place 3 broccoli spears with 1/2 chicken breast on top.
Combine other ingredients in bowl.
Cover chicken and broccoli with mixture. Sprinkle cheese and buttered bread crumbs.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve over egg noodles.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: no peek cookies
directions: Beat salt and egg whites.
Gradually add sugar and beat until whites are stiff and form peaks.
Mix in the chips.
Put teaspoon size on cookie sheets.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Turn off!
Place cookies in oven and leave overnight! Don't peek in the oven! Makes 3 dozen.

title: country braised pork chops
directions: Coat pork chops in flour.
Brown onion in oil in skillet until tender.
Add pork chops and brown on both sides.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 1 hour or until pork chops are tender.
Stir occasionally.

title: orange cream biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450. Mix baking mix, orange peel and orange juice until soft dough forms.; beat vigorously 30 seconds. Turn dough into surface generously dusted with baking mix; roll in baking mix to coat. Knead 10 times.

title: hummus
directions: Cook garbanzo beans well and drain.
Process all ingredients in blender until absolutely smooth.
Serve as a dip with pita bread or crackers for scooping.
Or use as a sandwich filling with lettuce leaves and tomato slices.

title: paradise pumpkin pie
directions: My grandmother, Neta Yantis Dove, knew what to do with those leftover candy canes!

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook the carrots until crisply done, about 5 to 6 minutes. Drain. Add the onion and green pepper.

title: cinnamon butterfly rolls
directions: In bowl mix first 3 ingredients plus 1 cup flour.
Heat milk and 1/2 cup butter until very warm (125°).
With a mixer a low beat, beat liquids into dry ingredients at medium 2 minutes.
Beat in vanilla, 1 egg and 1 cup flour; beat this 2 minutes, then stir in 2 cups flour.

title: orange french toast
directions: In a small mixing bowl, stir together eggs, juice and brown sugar.
Beat with a fork until combined.
Dip bread into egg mixture, turning to coat on both sides.

Let bread stand in egg mixture about 30 seconds on each side or until thoroughly soaked. In a skillet or a griddle, cook bread in hot oil over medium heat for 2 to 3 minutes on each side or until golden brown.
Serve with syrup.

title: seven seas casserole
directions: In saucepan, combine soup, water, salt, pepper and onion. Bring to a boil.
Pour half of mixture into casserole.
Make layers of rice (from box), peas and tuna.
Add other soup mixture. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes, cutting through with knife after baking 10 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Bake the pie crust and let it cool.
Mix the sugar, cocoa, salt, flour, milk and egg yolks in heavy saucepan.
Cook on low heat until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and pour into the pie crust.

title: greek bread
directions: Melt butter, mayonnaise and cheese in a saucepan.
Add garlic, olives, onion tops and peppers.
Spread on halved French bread loaf.
Broil in oven until cheese is bubbly.
Serve hot.

title: holiday salad
directions: Boil pineapple and sugar together for 5 minutes.
Dissolve 1 box of strawberry Jell-O in 1/2 cup boiling water.
Stir into pineapple mixture and chill until partly set.
Fold in Cool Whip and chopped pecans.
Refrigerate overnight or until firm.

title: vichyssoise(french tradition made easy with instant potatoes)
directions: Combine onion, bouillon cubes, water and salt in large saucepan.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for about 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add 1/2 cup of the milk. Stir in potato puffs; whip with fork until fluffy.
Gradually stir in remaining 1 1/2 cups milk; heat just to boiling.
Cover; chill thoroughly.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into four quarters.
In saucepan mix butter, brown sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Heat on low until dissolved; set aside.
In a plastic bag mix 1 cup sugar and 3 teaspoons cinnamon. Take a few quartered biscuits at a time and put in bag and shake to coat.
Grease a Bundt cake pan and put the biscuits into pan.
Pour sauce over quartered biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: nancie's chicken calupa
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan and line with mashed corn chips.
Put chicken over chips.
Mix soups, bouillon, sour cream, green chilies and onion.
Spread mixture over chicken and top with grated Longhorn cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: apple nut stuffing
directions: Cut squash in half lengthwise; remove seeds and fiber.
Place squash, cut-side down, in large microwavable dish.
Cover loosely. Microwave on High 10 to 12 minutes or until squash is tender.

title: karo pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs until frothy; add sugar, syrup, vinegar, melted butter and pecans.
Pour into 9-inch pie crust.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then 45 to 50 minutes at 325°.

title: pumpernickel bread dip
directions: Mix and fill scooped out bread.
Cut scooped out bread in chunks for dipping.
You can use any bread you prefer.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan. While cake is still hot, punch holes all the way to bottom with a fork.
Pour jar of caramel sauce over cake, then pour can of Eagle Brand milk over the sauce.
Cover and cool overnight in the refrigerator.
Next day, frost with Cool Whip.
Break Heath bar into small pieces and sprinkle over top of Cool Whip.

title: southwest chicken and dumplings
directions: In large saucepan, boil chicken, onion, salt and pepper in water over medium heat until chicken is done and onion is clear. Remove chicken from water and cut in 1-inch cubes.
Return chicken to boiling water.
Cut tortillas into 2-inch triangles and drop in boiling mixture.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Cook for 10 minutes, stirring often.
Stir in remaining 7 ingredients one at a time, stirring after each addition.
Remove from heat after cheeses are melted.
Serve immediately in soup bowls with Old El Paso Nachips.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Have partially baked pie shell ready. Melt butter in heavy skillet and add onions and saute until tender.
Put in pie crust.
Beat eggs, milk and salt in a medium bowl.
Season with pepper; sprinkle cheese over onions.
Pour egg mixture over onions and cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake pie for about 35 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Garnish with parsley.
Stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugars.
Beat in eggs, vanilla and salt. Stir in 1 1/4 cups flour and soda.
Stir in remaining flour. Add chocolate and nuts.
Roll in balls and flatten with fork.
Place on foil lined cookie sheets. Bake at 375° about 12 minutes.

title: mexican drumsticks
directions: In a 9-inch square dish, combine sauce and oil.
Add drumsticks and turn to coat with sauce.
Cover and marinate 1 hour. Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Place corn chips in plastic bag and crush. Shake drumsticks in crushed chips to coat. Place in baking dish and bake for 45 minutes.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Combine and cook oleo and flour 1 minute, forming paste.
Add chili powder, mustard, cumin, paprika, cayenne pepper, milk and Velveeta cheese.
Stir until melted, then add Ro-Tel tomatoes.

title: salty hugs and kisses
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.

Lay out pretzels in rows on a cookie sheet. Place either one Hershey's Hug or Kiss on each pretzel square. Bake until chocolate is soft (not melted). Remove from oven and quickly place another pretzel square on top of the soft Hug or Kiss.
Press down gently. Allow to cool at room temperature until chocolate is hard again, refrigerate or freeze.
You can make only as many as you plan to eat, or you can make the whole bag and share!

title: chicken elegante
directions: Place contents of vegetable seasoning packet and 2 tablespoons of the margarine in a large bowl.
Add hot water. Stir to partially melt margarine.
Add stuffing crumbs and stir to moisten.
Let stand until water is absorbed.
tags: Stove Top chicken flavored dressing mix

title: cinnamon sticks
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolk.
Add flour, salt and cinnamon.
Use hands to mash together.
Spread on cookie sheet. Pour egg white over mixture.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: You will need a large shallow baking dish.

title: rosy fruit cocktail slices
directions: Blend all ingredients well.
Pour into two 1-quart containers (round cans will do).
Freeze firm.
To serve, let stand at room temperature a few minutes.
Remove from container, slice and place on lettuce.
Trim with cherries.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries in blender.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.

title: chicken and broccoli italiano
directions: Season chicken breasts with garlic powder and onion powder. Place broccoli and chicken in baking dish.
Pour tomato sauce on top. Bake 4 minutes in a 325° oven. Cover each chicken breast with 1 slice Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Cook 2 additional minutes or until cheese has melted.
Serve immediately. Serves 4.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: Cook bacon in nonstick pan until browned.
Pour off fat. Drain on paper towel.
Crumble and reserve.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil in pan.
Add tortillas, one at a time, cooking for about 30 seconds or until softened, turning halfway through cooking.
Drain on paper towel.
Beat eggs and pepper in small bowl.
Heat remaining 1 tablespoon of oil in pan over medium heat.
Add eggs and cook, stirring just until set.
Sprinkle cheese down center of tortilla.
Top with eggs and bacon.

title: frozen pineapple and cheese salad
directions: Mix first three ingredients to a paste.
Mix together next four ingredients and add to paste mixture.
Add whipped cream and freeze in refrigerator tray.

title: baked steak
directions: Roll steak in flour and seasonings.
Brown in oil; transfer meat to casserole dish and top each layer with onion and green pepper.
Pour tomato sauce over meat and add more onion.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: amazing raisin cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl mix flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon, pumpkin pie spice and salt.
Add milk, eggs and mayonnaise.
Beat with electric mixer at low speed about 2 minutes (batter will be thick).
Add apples, raisins and walnuts.
Mix with a wooden spoon.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes.
Remove cake from oven and cool for 10 minutes. Serve with whipped topping or your favorite frosting.

title: 57 cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form into a ball and roll in chopped pecans or walnuts to cover.
Chill and serve.

title: decadent fudge pie
directions: Partially bake the pie crust and cool about 15 minutes before filling.
Combine butter and chocolate in a heavy saucepan over low heat; cook, stirring occasionally, until melted.
Remove from heat to cool.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, lightly beat the eggs.
Add the sugar, flour and salt.
Beat until well blended.
Add the cooled chocolate mixture and vanilla.
Stir until smooth.
Pour into the cooled pie shell.
Bake until a knife inserted into the center comes out a little gooey, about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: skillet sandwiches
directions: Mix corned beef, Swiss cheese, salad dressing, pickle and onion together.
Mixture will be thick.
Spread evenly on 6 slices of bread; top with remaining 6 slices.
Heat oil in a skillet. Beat eggs lightly.
Stir in the milk.
Dip sandwiches in egg mixture.
Brown on each side 2 to 3 minutes.
Cut in half and serve.

title: pasta shrimp mold
directions: Cook pasta per package directions; drain well.
Cool. Sprinkle gelatin over cold water in small bowl.
Combine celery, onion, shrimp and cooled pasta in large bowl.
Heat tomato soup until steaming; do not boil.
Add mayonnaise and cream cheese; stir constantly until cheese melts and mixture is smooth.
Pour over shrimp mixture in bowl; blend well.
Add gelatin and water; blend throughly.
Pour into oiled 6 cup mold; chill at least 4 hours.
Unmold onto serving plate; slice and serve on lettuce leaves.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and Wesson oil with sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add lemon extract; add flour and 7-Up alternately, beating after each addition.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: In 13 x 9 pan, melt butter.
Sprinkle crumbs over butter. Pour Eagle Brand milk evenly over crumbs.

title: cheese boat
directions: Mix all ingredients together; add tomato at end.
Hollow out loaf of bread and fill with mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt oleo and peanut butter together.
Pour in vanilla and stir.
Add powdered sugar; mix together.
Put in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan; refrigerate.
When cool, cut into squares.
Keeps better in refrigerator.
Makes about 3 to 4 pounds.

title: rhubarb meat sauce
directions: Cook the rhubarb and vinegar for 20 minutes.
Add the remaining ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.
Makes 7 pints.

title: breaded shrimp
directions: Beat the eggs well and add a little water.
Flour shrimp. Then dip in egg and water.
Then in bread crumbs.
Deep-fry shrimp in hot oil about 375°.
Put on paper towels.
Eat with cocktail sauce.

title: apricot glazed parsnips
directions: Saute thin slices of parsnips in butter until tender, then add apricot jam and continue to cook until jam thickens.

title: green beans and kielbasi
directions: Prepare beans and potatoes for cooking; cook until almost done.
Add the kielbasi the last 30 minutes of cooking time, season to taste.
Canned beans and potatoes can be used as effectively when preparing this recipe.

title: stuffed pizza pie
directions: Spray pie pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Spread pizza crust in pie pan, leaving half of it overlapping on side.
Spread sauce on top of crust in pan.
Add other ingredients on top of each other, making cheese last thing.
Pull overlapping crust over filling.
Crimp edges together.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes or until top gets browned.
Pour heated pizza sauce over individual servings to suit taste.

title: heavenly jam
directions: Mash peaches with potato masher or cut in small pieces.
Add the sugar.
Let stand overnight.
In the morning, add the orange. Put on stove and cook for 1/2 hour.
Add cherries (cut in halves) and juice. Cook 1/2 hour more.
Add the Certo. Put in jars and seal.

title: cindy hyatt's cheese fondue
directions: Rub the inside of the fondue pot with the cut clove of garlic. Mix the cornstarch with the brandy.
Add cheese, wine and cornstarch mix.
Do not boil.
Stir constantly, until melted and well mixed.
Keep warm to serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: butterscotch apple cake
directions: Mix flour, salt, soda and cinnamon together.
Set aside. Cream eggs and sugar together.
Add apples and oil; mix well.
Add dry ingredients and mix.

title: million dollar fudge(martha washington's)
directions: Blend thoroughly with hands.
Roll into balls size of walnuts. Refrigerate 2 hours to firm.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in a greased casserole dish. Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes or until done.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix and serve on a fresh fruit platter.
Use pineapple chunks on platter.

title: chef's salad
directions: In small bowl, whisk together vinegar, mustard, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Slowly whisk in oil, then stir in cream; set aside.
Line a salad bowl with several leaves of lettuce.
Tear remaining lettuce into bite-size pieces.
Toss with radishes and half of dressing.
Arrange ham, chicken or turkey and cheese on top of salad.
Place tomatoes and eggs around outer edge.
Season with remaining 1/4 teaspoon each salt and pepper. Spoon remaining dressing over salad.

title: egg-ham casserole
directions: Cook ham in butter until lightly browned.
Add the beaten eggs and scramble.
Put into greased 14 x 18-Pyrex pan.
Make a white sauce of the flour, butter and milk.
Add cheese and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until cheese is melted.
Pour over the eggs-ham in casserole.
Sprinkle buttered crumbs on top and a dash of paprika on all.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
This may be made the day before and baked at breakfast time.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and spoon into a well-greased casserole pan.

title: hash brown quiche
directions: Grease 9-inch glass pie plate with solid shortening.
Press hash browns into pie plate making a solid crust.
Brush with melted butter including top edges.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes. Remove from oven and fill with layers of cheese and ham.
Beat eggs and salt with milk.
Pour over cheese and ham.
Return to oven and then reduce heat to 350°.
Bake until knife inserted near edge comes out clean (about 30 to 40 minutes).

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together!!!
To serve:
Use 2 teaspoons of mix per 1 cup hot water.

title: home prepared bisquick mix
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then cut in shortening until mixture is fine as corn meal.
Store, tightly covered, in refrigerator (keeps well).

title: nutty peach crisp(great dessert or breakfast)
directions: Arrange peaches in an ungreased 9 x 13 inch baking dish. Sprinkle dry cake mix over the top.
Drizzle with butter.
Sprinkle with coconut and pecans.
Bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: In a 10 x 10-inch casserole dish, place the potatoes, onions and crumbled corned beef.
Pour undiluted soup on beef.
Sprinkle with pepper.
No salt.
Cover.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, or until potatoes are done.

title: rhubarb pineapple preserves
directions: Combine all but jello and cook 20 to 25 minutes.
Take from stove and slowly mix jello into hot mixture.
Keep refrigerated up to one year unless opened, then keeps up to 4 weeks.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix and bake until golden brown at 350°.

title: raspberry jello salad
directions: Prepare Jell-O per package instructions, using juice from pineapple to make correct amount of cold liquid (add water, if necessary).
Add sugar and salt.
All to set until slightly thickened.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: far east celery
directions: Cook celery slices until still crisp (about 8 minutes). Drain.
Mix with water chestnuts, cream of chicken soup and pimentos.
Put in casserole.
Toss bread crumbs and almonds added to melted butter and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° about 35 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Put all in roaster and cook 2 hours at 250°.

title: zucchini walnut bread
directions: Chop walnuts into medium sized pieces.
Beat eggs; gradually beat in sugar, then oil.
Combine dry ingredients and add to first mixture alternately with zucchini.
Stir in raisins, walnuts and vanilla.
Turn into 2 greased and lightly floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Let stand about 10 minutes.
Put on wire rack to cool.
If you want, glaze the top.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak beans all night in water.
Cover with water in morning. Bake in oven at 350° for 2 hours, then add salt, pepper and molasses.
Place bacon on top and bake 3 to 4 hours or until soft. Add water as needed.

title: curried rice pilaf
directions: Mix together and cook rice in broth.

title: spice baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large ovensafe bowl, mix beans, diced onion, catsup and brown sugar.
Roll pieces of sausage into several 1/2 to 1-inch balls.
Put them into mixture.
Stir and bake approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Can be served warm or cold.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in pie shell.

title: denise's white chocolate cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese at high speed of an electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add the melted white chocolate.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into prepared graham cracker crumb crust in spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes; turn oven off and partially open oven door.
Leave cheesecake in oven for 30 more minutes.
Remove from oven and cool.
Chill at least 8 hours.

title: amanda's zucchini pie
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Grease pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Insert toothpick to see if it's done.
Enjoy!

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreos.
Cream cream cheese, confectioners sugar and oleo. Mix pudding, milk and Cool Whip.
Mix cream cheese mixture and pudding mixture together.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Warm butter, cream cheese and eggs to room temperature. Grease and flour a tube or Bundt pan.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix butter and cream cheese then cream with sugar (this batter should be treated gently). Then add salt and vanilla and mix.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing after each.
Gently mix in flour until just blended then pour into prepared pan and bake for 1 1/2 hours or until the cake pulls away from the sides of the pan (I start checking at around 1 1/4 hours).
Cool cake in pan for 10 minutes then invert onto wire rack.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cool.
This is an extremely rich, dense and heavy cake (not healthy but heavenly)!

title: chicken a la crescent
directions: Mix together stuffing mix and pecans and set aside.
Mix together cream cheese dip, margarine, lemon pepper and chicken. Spread mixture on wide end of roll and seal.
Melt 3 tablespoons margarine.
Dip each roll in margarine then in stuffing mixture. Place in baking dish and bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
You can use cream of chicken, cheese or broccoli cheese soup for gravy.
Just heat soup, undiluted, and spoon over baked rolls before serving.

title: slushes
directions: Boil 7 cups of water and the sugar in a large pan, then cool. Boil 2 cups of water and tea bags, then cool, leaving tea bags in to get strong.
Add orange juice and lemonade.
Stir and freeze for 24 hours.
Can eat as is or can pour 7-Up over it.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and most of stuffing (save small amount for top).
Dot with butter and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cream puff shells
directions: In small saucepan combine water, sugar, salt and butter. Bring to boil.
Add flour all at once.
Stir quickly to form large ball.
Remove from heat.
Cool 2 minutes.
Put mixture in medium sized bowl and add eggs one at a time beating well after each addition.
With small ice cream scoop measure a mound of dough on a nonstick baking sheet 3 inches apart.
Bake 10 minutes at 400° and lower to 350° and bake 25 minutes more.
Cool completely.
Cut off 1/3 top and remove any soft part.
Can be filled with pudding for dessert or chicken salad or tuna salad.

title: snow ice cream
directions: Collect snow in a Dutch oven.
Add evaporated milk, sugar and vanilla.
Mix until ice cream-like consistency.
Ear right away!

title: nana's jelly tots
directions: Mix ingredients together well, but not too long.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet and make a depression in center of each ball with your thumb and in each, place jelly or preserves of your own choosing.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and enjoy.

title: bacon pancakes
directions: Prepare
pancake mix by instructions on package and set aside. Cut
of a pound of bacon in 1/4-inch pieces.	Fry bacon pieces
until
crispy.
Remove bacon.
Drain and remove grease from
pan.	Pour 1/4 cup pancake mix in frying pan and sprinkle with
some	of
the
bacon pieces.	Cook until done. Spread margarine on warm pancake and serve with pancake syrup. Repeat until
pancake
mix
and bacon pieces are gone.
Great with coffee or milk.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Mix all ingredients together leaving no lumps.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix together cream cheese, brown sugar, and vanilla. Top with caramel topping and pecan.

title: crisp cookies
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and powdered sugar together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop in balls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Mix crushed flakes with other ingredients.
Roll chicken breast in mixture.
Spray pan with Pam. Place chicken on pan. Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: poison-ends candy
directions: Mash banana to puree.
Mix in enough powdered sugar to make a stiff dough.
Using more sugar, roll out 1/2 dough into a rectangle 1/4-inch thick.
Spread thickly with peanut butter almost to edges.
Roll tightly from long edge to make a pinwheel log.
Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Slice from end 1/4-inch thick pieces.
Cook gets to sample ends of log "to make sure it's not poison" as my mother always said! Store in refrigerator.

title: my grandma's butter crescents
directions: In blender or food processor blend nuts and sugar until finely blended.
Cream butter in large bowl and add almond-sugar mixture. Beat until fluffy.
Gradually add flour and salt.
Wrap and refrigerate until firm.
Working with 1/4 of dough at a time, shape into 3/4 inch balls.
Roll and shape into crescent shapes. Place on unbuttered cookie sheet and bake 14 to 16 minutes at 325°.
Cool for 10 minutes; dip into sugar to coat.

title: english walnut pie
directions: Put in pie shell. Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: oyster pie
directions: Crush saltines and put in a layer in dish.
Dot with butter. Layer with oysters and sliced eggs.
Repeat, ending with eggs. Pour over with evaporated milk to cover.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, approximately 30 minutes.
Will set up while cooling.

title: punch
directions: You will need 4 or more 1 gallon Ziploc freezer bags.

title: florence's beans
directions: In a crock-pot mix all ingredients together and turn heat on high until beans start to boil.
Turn to low for 4 to 4 1/2 hours. To bake in oven, mix all ingredients together and place in 350° oven.
Lower heat to 300° and bake covered for 3 hours.

title: sin or chocolate delight
directions: First Layer:
Mix flour, 1 package nut topping and oleo; pack in bottom of 13 x 9-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: apple dumplins
directions: Mix sugar, water and butter in pan.
Heat oven to 325° and set pan in hot oven to heat mixture.
Peel and cut several tart apples into thin slices.
Using the can of biscuits, roll each biscuit out the size of a saucer, but not too thin.
Place the rolled out biscuit in palm of hand and fill with apples.
Add 1 teaspoon sugar to the apples and bring biscuit up around the apples.
Pinch edges together.
Set in pan of hot mixture.
After all dumplins are placed, sprinkle with 1 cup sugar, cinnamon and dot with butter.
Place in oven and bake until golden brown and apples are soft, about 1 hour.
Add a little hot water if more liquid is needed.

title: cheesy chicken wings
directions: Wash chicken and pat dry.
In a bowl, combine cracker crumbs, herbs and Parmesan cheese.
Add seasonings and mix well to blend. Melt butter.
Dip chicken into melted butter, then into crumb coating.
Arrange chicken in lightly oiled baking dish. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned and done. Good served with broccoli or fried rice.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Drain shrimp and rinse.
Mix remaining ingredients, except shrimp, then add chopped shrimp.
Serve with crackers.

title: lemonade
directions: You will need a 1-gallon jug half full of water, finish filling the jug with ice.

title: make-ahead layered salad
directions: Combine spinach and lettuce; place half of salad greens in large clear glass salad bowl.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and salad dressing mix; stir well and spread half of mixture evenly over salad greens.
Layer (in order) the egg slices, peas, 1/2 cup green onion, 6 slices crumbled bacon and remaining salad greens. Spread remaining sour cream mixture over top, sealing to edge of bowl.
Cover and chill overnight.
Garnish with additional onion and bacon.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Mix crumbs with melted butter.
Put layer in bottom of dish; cover with oysters.
Have only 2 layers of crackers and oysters. Cover with cream and oyster liquid.
Bake 1/2 hour at 400°.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Mix flour, salt, pepper and paprika; put in bowl.
Mix egg and milk; put in another bowl.
Mix cheese and bread crumbs.
Coat chicken with flour, dip in egg mixture and roll in cheese crumbs. Melt butter in pan.
Place chicken skin side down.
Bake 30 minutes on each side.
May use boneless chicken.
Bake 20 minutes on each side at 400°.

title: sausage cornbread bake
directions: Brown sausage and onion; drain.
Combine rest of ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sausage 'n sauerkraut
directions: Cut sausage into 1-inch slices and saute in a Dutch oven until fully cooked and brown.
Drain.
Add sauerkraut, tomatoes with liquid, celery, onion, green pepper, brown sugar and seasonings. Mix well.
Cover and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve over mashed potatoes if desired.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: pear mincemeat
directions: Using knife blade in food processor bowl, add 1 cup pears and process until finely chopped.
Repeat with the rest of the fruit.

title: tortilla soup
directions: In a saucepan, combine first 5 ingredients; simmer 5 to 7 minutes.
Arrange a shallow layer of chips in serving bowls. Ladle in soup; top with cheese and avocados.
Serve immediately.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Place butter in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan in preheating oven just to melt, about 3 minutes.
Beat eggs in large bowl; mix in flour, baking powder and salt.
Squeeze thawed spinach very dry and add to egg mixture along with melted butter, chillies and cheeses.
Pour mixture into pan; bake 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350°; bake an additional 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes to set.
Cut in 60 squares for hors d'oeuvres.

title: red salad
directions: Mix jellos and 1 cup boiling water.
Add 1 1/2 cups cold water.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and pineapple. Add dry ingredients that have been sifted together.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: donna's no confectioners sugar frosting
directions: Beat all ingredients for 5 minutes.

title: garden vegetable dip
directions: In bowl, heat cheese until fluffy.
Blend in chili sauce and remaining
ingredients. Cover and chill.
Serve with chilled fresh vegetables.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Beat until thick.
In another bowl, mix margarine and cream cheese, then mix all ingredients together with Cool Whip.
Start with layer of cookies and then layer of pudding mixture, then another layer of cookies and layer of pudding.
End with layer of cookies.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar well together.
Add unbeaten egg and chopped apples.
Mix well together with spoon (not electric mixer).
Sift flour, cinnamon and soda and add to mixture.
Nuts may be added.

title: turkey and stuffing bake
directions: Combine oleo and water; stir until oleo melts.
Put over seasoned bread crumbs; toss lightly.
Stir in 1/2 can onions. Spoon stuffing mixture into a 9-inch shallow baking dish (1 1/2-quart).
Press stuffing across bottom and up sides of dish, forming a shell.
Combine soup, milk, turkey and peas; pour into stuffing shell.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 35 minutes.
Top with remaining onions and bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.

title: supreme scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to350°.
Slice potatoes in very thin slices. Spray casserole dish with cooking spray (use a deep casserole dish).
Alternate in 3 layers:
potatoes, dot with butter, cheese, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix cream of celery soup and milk and pour into casserole until liquid shows around the edge of potatoes.
(Do not completely cover potatoes with milk mixture.) Sprinkle with paprika, cover and bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Add salt to cabbage and set for 2 hours.
Boil sugar and white vinegar for 3 minutes.
Pour over cabbage mixture after vinegar cools.
Cover and store in refrigerator.

title: tossed salad
directions: Toss and serve with favorite dressing.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix pie filling and pineapple together in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix evenly over top.
Melt butter and drizzle over cake mix. Top with nuts and bake for 45 minutes to an hour at 350°.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Grease two nonstick pans (10 1/2 x 15 3/4 x 3/4-inch).
Mix sugar, syrup and water and cook until 275° (use a candy thermometer), stirring constantly.
Add peanuts and cook until 290°.
Add butter and vanilla.
Cook until 300°.
Mix thoroughly and pour into the two buttered pans.
When cool, break into pieces.
Yields 3 1/2 pounds.

title: pears with mint chocolate
directions: If using fresh pears, cook in water with sugar until soft to the touch; drain well.
Drain canned pears well.
Place on an ovenproof plate.
Put one chocolate covered mint on top of each pear half.
Broil or bake pears in oven at 375° to 400° for 10 to 15 minutes, until chocolate is melted.
Remove from oven.
Garnish with grapes or walnut halves.
Serve with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: sauteed mushrooms
directions: This recipe can accomodate any amount needed.
There are no measurements, all ingredients are added to taste.

title: rice con queso
directions: Mix together rice, beans, garlic, onion and chili.
Set aside. Mix together Jack and Ricotta cheeses; thin with yogurt or milk until spreadable.
Repeat layers of rice and bean mixture, then cheese mixture, ending with rice mixture, in a casserole.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese and black olives.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until browned and bubbly.
Or can bake in microwave for approximately 15 minutes on "High."

title: italian vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground round in large heavy kettle; drain if necessary. Add rest of ingredients except cabbage, green beans and macaroni. Bring to boil and simmer 20 minutes, covered.
Add rest and bring to boil, then simmer until all is tender.
If you like thinner soup, add more water.
Makes 12 servings.

title: new england boiled dinner
directions: In a large pot, cover meat with cold water.
Bring to boiling. Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 2 hours.
Add boiling water, then turnips and carrots.
Cook 15 minutes.
Add parsnips.
Cook 15 minutes.
Add cabbage and cook 25 minutes longer.

title: sour cream plain cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat 1 minute.
Blend in sour cream, sifted flour and flavoring.
Pour into two well-greased and lightly floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: waldorf salad
directions: In a salad bowl, blend mayonnaise, lemon juice, and salt. Add apples, celery, nuts, and raisins.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add pizza sauce, water and macaroni, cooked.
Mix thoroughly.
In greased 8 x 10-inch casserole, put 1 layer of bread mixture, 1 layer of cheese, then layer of beef mixture, then layer of cheese.
Top with pepperoni slices.
Bake 15 or 20 minutes at 375° or until cheese has melted well.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Scald milk over hot
water
in	top of double boiler or over very low
heat.
Cool
to
lukewarm.
Add crumbled yeast, sugar, water and egg
to
milk;
beat with rotary beater until blended. Add 3 1/2 cups flour, fat and salt to yeast mixture. Stir until blended
and
add
remaining
flour, stirring until blended. Place dough
in greased bowl; grease top.
Cover and store in refrigerator
overnight
or at least 3 hours.
Remove dough from refrigerator and
shape
into rolls;
place in 8 to 9-inch cake pan and
brush
top with fat.
Let double in size. Bake rolls at 425°
for
to
minutes.
Very, very good rolls.

title: apple strudel pastry squares
directions: In large bowl, sift flour and salt.
Cut in butter with pastry blender until crumbly.
Beat egg yolk, add enough milk to egg to make 1/3 cup.
Stir milk into flour mixture, stirring until mixture holds together and cleans sides of bowl.
Divide in 1/2. Roll out 1 part to line 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan. Sprinkle with corn flakes.
Combine apples, sugar, ginger and cinnamon. Stir and spread onto first dough.
Roll out 2nd part dough and place over apple mixture and pinch together sides.
Brush beaten egg whites over top of crust.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes.

title: old fashion butter cookies
directions: Cream the butter.
Add sugar and vanilla and continue creaming until light.
Add beaten eggs; blend well.
Add flour, sifted with salt, using more flour if necessary to make a stiff dough.
Chill dough for 20 to 30 minutes, then roll out to 1/4-inch thickness and cut with cookie cutters.
Bake on lightly greased baking sheets at 375° for about 10 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: hot christmas punch
directions: Bring to boil water and sugar.
Add cloves.
Add cherry Jell-O.
As mixture is heating, mix orange juice (as directions on can) and lemonade and pineapple juice together.
Put this into hot mixture and bring to boil.
Let boil for 5 or 10 minutes.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: asparagus hollandaise dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl of food processor.
Process until smooth.
Refrigerate.
Makes about 3 cups.
Good with chicken tenders or nuggets.

title: tortilla casserole
directions: Combine ground beef, onion, salt and pepper. Cook and drain. Add cream of mushroom soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes and mix well. Lightly grease a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.

Layer corn tortillas, then half of the sauce, another layer of corn tortillas and remaining sauce. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes. Top with cheeses and put in broiler until cheese is melted. Can be served with picante sauce, sour cream or guacamole.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Fill
baked	9-inch pie shell with 1 quart of sliced unsweetened
strawberries.	Bring
to
a
boil
and cook until thick
and	clear,	stirring
constantly:
sugar, water, cornstarch	and salt.
Remove from heat and add a few drops of red food
coloring
and
package (1/4 cup) strawberry Jell-O. Stir in and let cool.
Pour cooled sauce over strawberries and refrigerate
at least 4 to 6 hours.
Serve with whipped cream. Peaches
can
be
substituted
for	the strawberries and peach Jell-O.

title: carrot casserole("pretty and good company fare.  people can't believe it's
directions: Slice and cook carrots; drain.
Make a sauce with all remaining ingredients, except the cheese slices and the bread crumbs.
In a 1-quart casserole, layer carrots with cheese slices, ending with a carrot layer.
Pour the sauce over top; sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Stir together and refrigerate until completely chilled.

title: mom's (goldia dyer) chocolate pie(as taught to me)
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cocoa and salt in saucepan until well blended.
Add milk.
Add egg yolks after mixture starts to cook. (Add pudding mixture to egg yolks in separate bowl, then return to mixture.)
Cook until thick.
Add vanilla and butter.
Cool before pouring into baked crust.

title: rich fudge brownies
directions: Combine sugar and softened butter; add eggs.
Add vanilla, melted chocolate or cocoa and nuts; beat until smooth.
Sift cake flour and salt together.
Add gradually to chocolate mixture. Beat until smooth.
Turn into greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 20 minutes.

title: clear-toy candy
directions: Spray molds with cooking spray.
Combine sugar, corn syrup and water in a heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Stir until well mixed.
Before putting pan on stove, remove sugar crystals on sides of pan with a brush in water.
Sides must be perfectly clean above water level. Begin cooking.
Cook to 300°.
Do not stir while cooking.
Add desired food coloring when the liquid reaches 265°.
Do not stir it in.
Boiling will distribute color.
Pour finished syrup (at 300°) into oiled molds and let cool.
Remove from molds before the candy sticks to the mold.
Syrup can also be poured into well oiled flat pans, scored and broken into pieces.
Store candy in a cool, dry place.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Mix pineapple juice & soy sauce & use for marinade for chicken breasts marinade the chicken for several hours in the refrigerator Cook on barbecue brushing on marinade while cooking to keep moist
Serve with Uncle Ben's wild rice & Gram's wonderful salad SOOOO GOOD!

title: shortcake
directions: In a large bowl, place all ingredients and mix together. Grease a baking dish and pour mixture into it.
Bake for 35 minutes in a 350° oven until done.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Slice sausage into small pieces.
Brown in skillet with onion. Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and water.
Salt to taste.
Simmer for 5 to 10 minutes, then mix with rice in a casserole dish.
Top with black olives.
Bake at 350° covered for 30 minutes until rice is done.

title: parmesan pull-apart bread(weight watchers)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Brush 1 teaspoon of margarine over bottom and sides of 7 1/2 x 3 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch nonstick loaf pan. Spoon cheese into small bowl. Cut each biscuit into quarters. Dip each biscuit quarter into remaining margarine, then into Parmesan cheese, turning to lightly coat all sides. Use all margarine and cheese. Layer coated biscuit quarters with edges touching. Bake 30 to 35 minutes. Invert loaf pan onto platter; let stand in pan for 1 minute. Carefully remove pan. Makes 10 servings.

title: hamburg casserole
directions: Cream of celery soup may be substituted.

title: cream cheese pudding dessert
directions: Combine crumbs, 1/4 cup of the sugar and the butter; mix well. Press firmly into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill 15 minutes.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Slice and slightly cook potatoes; slice onions.
Layer potatoes, onions and corned beef in greased baking dish; cover with cream of celery soup and salt and pepper to taste.
Bake one hour at 350°.

title: hawaiian casserole
directions: Drain the cans of tuna and place in a bowl.
Mix into small pieces.
Pour the can of pineapple over tuna, including juice.
Add the cooked rice and soy sauce, mix well.
Pour into casserole dish and bake in a 325° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 5 servings.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Beat eggs; add oil, onion, cheese, parsley, salt, oregano, seasoned salt, pepper and garlic.
Stir in biscuit mix and fold in zucchini.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Serve hot or cold.
Serves 30 to 40 as appetizer.

title: butterscotch oatmeal cookies
directions: In large bowl, beat margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add vanilla.
Combine flour, oats, baking soda and salt; add alternately with water to creamed mixture.
Stir in butterscotch morsels and nuts.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes until edges are lightly browned.
Yield:
about 6 dozen cookies.

title: company nestle toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large bowl, beat eggs until foamy. Beat in flour, sugar and brown sugar until well blended.
Blend in melted butter; stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Remove from oven; serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix 1 cup Bisquick and water to make a dough.
Knead vigorously.
Roll dough to fit a 9-inch pie plate. Cook ground beef, onion and drain.
Stir in salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and remaining Bisquick.
Pour into crust.
Mix cottage cheese and eggs and pour over the top.
Arrange tomato slices on top.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: lo-cal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: deep dish salmon-cheese pie(from 1975 edition)
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Saute onion in butter.
Remove from heat; blend in Bisquick.
Slowly stir in milk.
Bring to boil over low heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Stir in rest of ingredients, except Biscuit Dough.

title: siesta salad
directions: Spread bean dip on bottom layer of serving dish.
Combine sour cream or cream cheese with mayonnaise and taco seasoning.
Spread on top of bean dip layer.
Mash avocados, black pepper, salt and lemon juice.
Spread on top of second layer.
Chop lettuce, tomatoes, onion and olives.
Sprinkle on top.
Cover with cheese. Serve with Doritos.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until done, do not overcook.
When potatoes are cold, remove skins and dice into large bowl.
Dice onion and celery fine and add to potatoes.
Salt and pepper well and mix very, very well and taste to see if more salt and pepper is needed.
Do not add mayonnaise until seasoning is complete.
When you're sure enough salt and pepper has been added, then add only enough mayonnaise to coat the potatoes.
