Turn over and over until throughly mixed.
Taste to see if more salt and pepper is needed at this point.
Then drain the pimento and add to potato salad.
Fold into potato salad until well mixed.
Chill until ready to serve. Garnish top with hard-boiled eggs if desired.

title: grandma's eggless cookie
directions: Cream lard and sugar.
Add soda to buttermilk.
Sift flour and alternate milk mixture and flour and salt.
Last, add drained raisins.
Roll out.
Cut in shapes desired.
Bake at 375°.

title: italian eggplant
directions: Dip eggplant in butter, then bread crumbs.
Fry until brown on both sides.

title: wild rice hot dish
directions: Pour boiling water over the rice and let stand 15 minutes. Drain.
Brown hamburger with diced onion and chopped celery, add beef stock, soup, mushrooms and seasoning. Mix together and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Sprinkle Accent and paprika on top.
Bake 3 hours at 300°, covered.

title: champagne punch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve in a large punch bowl.
Enjoy!

title: easy cheese bread
directions: Combine
biscuit
mix, cheese and poppy seed in a large bowl. Combine
egg
and
milk;
add
to biscuit mixture.	Mix vigorously for 1 minute.
Spoon into a lightly greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake bread at 350° for 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: italian zucchini crescent pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In 10 inch skillet, cook zucchini and onions in margarine until tender, about 10 minutes.
Stir in parsley and seasonings. In a large bowl blend eggs and cheese. Stir in vegetable mixture.
Separate dough into 8 triangles. Place in ungreased 10 inch pie pan.
Press over bottom and up sides to form crust.

Spread crust with mustard. Pour vegetable mixture evenly into crust. Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out cleanly. (If crust becomes too brown, cover with foil during the last 10 minutes of baking.) Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Serves 6.

title: barbecued beans
directions: Brown bacon in frying pan.
Remove and drain fat, then brown hamburger and onion.
Fry until beef is fully cooked.
Drain off fat.
Drain liquid from butter beans and kidney beans only.
Blend seasonings, catsup and barbecue sauce.
Add to hamburger mixture, then add beans.
Bake in large casserole for 1 hour at 350°. Serves 10 to 12 (freezes well).

title: brandied fruit
directions: Drain cans of fruit and place in a large casserole dish.
Mix melted margarine with brown sugar, flour and sherry.
Pour over fruit.
Heat at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease 3 loaf pans.
Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all the ingredients together. Add 1/2 cup crushed nuts and/or 1/2 cup raisins.
Pour into greased pans.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: lemon jell-o salad
directions: While Jell-O is thickening, grate other ingredients medium-fine.
Mix all ingredients into semi-formed Jell-O.	When Jell-O firms, cut into squares.
Put in center of crisp lettuce leaf.
Add one dab of mayonnaise or yogurt.
Sprinkle dab with a little paprika for color.
I usually prepare this salad in the morning to save time later.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese.
Pour half of mixture in large baking dish.
Top with nacho or taco chips and 1/2 pound Velveeta cheese which you have chopped up.
Repeat same again and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
This makes a large casserole.
You can divide it into two and freeze one for later if you wish.

title: carrot-pineapple layer cake
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients in order listed, mixing after each addition.
Pour batter into 3 greased layer pans.
Bake at 350° until done.
Cool before frosting.

title: italian chicken bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large pan, put water and skinless chicken pieces.
Cook, over medium-high heat, until chicken falls off bone.
Remove chicken from bone and place in a bowl.
Pour of Italian dressing over chicken until covered.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Next day, place chicken in a baking dish. Baste chicken with dressing, then bake until chicken is warm. Serve with rice and vegetables.

title: pralines
directions: Use large, heavy pan, Dutch oven size. In this pan, combine sugar, soda, buttermilk and salt. Cook on moderately high to 210° on candy thermometer, stirring constantly. Add butter and pecans. Continue cooking, stirring constantly, until candy reaches soft-ball stage, 234° on candy thermometer. Remove from heat and cool slightly. Beat with spoon until thick and creamy. Drop from spoon onto waxed paper and let cool. Makes about 18 (2-inch) pralines.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Cut rhubarb into small pieces; place in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour sugar over rhubarb; sprinkle Jell-O over sugar and add marshmallows.
Cream the sugar and Crisco.
Add egg and beat well. Add the milk, flour, salt and baking powder.
Drizzle over top. Bake 50 minutes at 300°.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Layer sausage, potatoes and sauerkraut, alternating proportionately in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Mix all ingredients (except 1/2 cup sugar) in large bowl. Combine separately 1/2 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Pour 1/2 of batter into greased spring-form tube pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 cinnamon mixture on top.
Follow with remaining batter, then remaining cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for an hour or so.
Should be moist, but not gooey.

title: egg bake(this is really good for a brunch.)
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Beat eggs.
Mix all ingredients together; leave in refrigerator overnight.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Bake covered with foil.

title: pig pen cake
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake at 350° until done (about 35 minutes).

title: golden summer punch
directions: Add water to concentrates as directed.
Combine with apricot nectar and pineapple juice.
Float ice ring in punch bowl.
Pour in juices and serve.

title: apples, sweet potatoes and ham
directions: Place potatoes in greased 2-quart casserole; cover with ham. Combine the apples, brown sugar, pineapple juice, mustard and vinegar.
Bring to boil and then simmer 10 minutes.
Pour over ham and sweet potatoes in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour. Serves 4.

title: corn fritters
directions: Put 1/4 inch oil in a fry pan on medium heat.
Drop by tablespoon into hot oil and cook until brown.

title: meat pies fried
directions: Saute sausage, beef and onions until done.
Set aside and drain well.
Mix flour, egg, salt, milk and water.
Pinch off, roll out and cut with saucer.
Put small amount of meat mixture on shell and fold over.
Pinch together.
Fry in hot oil until golden brown.

title: instant hot chocolate
directions: Mix all the preceding ingredients.
Store in a tightly sealed jar.
Use 1/3 cup in 1 cup hot water.

title: bailey's irish creme
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender and mix until well blended. Refrigerate for up to 5 days.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Peel onion; cut into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Separate into rings.
Beat eggs and milk in large bowl.
Add flour, baking powder and salt until blended.
Pour 1 inch oil in large skillet; heat to 375°.
Dip rings, a few at a time, in hot oil.
Fry, turning once 3 or 4 minutes or until golden or crisp.
Drain on paper towel.
Add salt if you wish.
Serve hot.

title: williamsburg corn chowder
directions: Fry the salt pork until brown.
Add the onion and saute over medium heat 5 minutes, stirring often.
Add the celery, potatoes, chicken broth and 1 cup of water and simmer until the potatoes are done.
Add the corn and simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Heat the milk and butter and add to the soup.
Add salt and pepper to taste and serve hot.
Serves 6.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Boil chopped onion and zucchini in small amount of salted water until tender.
Drain well.
Combine soup, sour cream and carrots.
Fold in zucchini and onions.
Melt butter and toss with stuffing mix.

title: contemporary strata
directions: Place 2 cups bread crumbs in dish.
Add meat, green pepper and onion in dish.
Top with another 2 cups bread.
Beat eggs; combine with soup, milk, mayonnaise and seasoning.
Pour over other ingredients.
Cover and chill 1 to 3 hours.
Toss 1 cup bread with melted butter.
Sprinkle atop.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes. Seasoning optional.

title: stuffed baked chicken
directions: Wrap chicken breast around 1 slice spiced beef. Cut bacon strips in half.

Place half slice around each piece of chicken. Place individual chicken pieces in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Mix soup and sour cream together and pour over chicken pieces. Sprinkle almonds on top of each chicken breast.
Bake at 275° for 2 hours.

title: milky way cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour angel food cake pan. In a small pot over low heat, melt candy bars with 1/2 cup butter. Cream sugar with remaining 1/2 cup butter until light.
Add candy mixture and blend well.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, mixing well after each.
Dissolve baking soda in buttermilk and add alternately with flour to candy mixture, ending with flour.
Beat egg whites to stiff peaks and fold into candy mixture with chopped pecans.
Bake 1 hour 10 minutes.
Cool and frost with melted semi-sweet chocolate.
Very Rich!

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Put in a greased casserole and bake until thickened, about 20 to 30 minutes, at 350°.

title: triple bean salad
directions: Heat green beans and yellow beans until hot, not boiling. Cool and add drained red beans, then add all other ingredients. Mix well so oil doesn't stay on top.
This can be done night before and should set at least 3 or 4 hours before serving.
But mix several times as this helps flavor the beans.
Chill in refrigerator until serving.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish. Melt 1/4 cup butter and pour over 2 cups corn flakes.
Mix and pour on top of first 8 ingredients.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken salad
directions: Simmer whole fryer. Cook minced onion. Combine chicken, onion and chicken stock. Add cheese, egg and pimientos. Sprinkle with garlic powder and pepper, if desired. Add mayonnaise and mix carefully.

title: potato cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Dip in flour and brown in medium-hot skillet in cooking oil or margarine for about 5 minutes on each side.

title: chicken jambalaya
directions: Place chicken and sausage in large pot and cover with water. Boil until tender.
Drain chicken and sausage, preserving the liquid.
In a large pot saute chopped onions, pepper, celery and garlic in light olive oil until tender.
Bone and cut up chicken and sausage.
Add chicken and sausages to vegetables, also adding tomato and tomato paste.
Season to taste, cook for 30 to 40 minutes over low heat.
Add 2 to 2.5 cups reserved liquid and rice.
Cook until liquid is absorbed.

title: creole seasoning
directions: Mix well and store in shaker or covered container.
Good on meats, fish, poultry, pizza, salad, etc.

title: almond crescents
directions: Add all ingredients and then chill.
Roll out on rolling board and then cut and shape like a shrimp.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: little pizzas
directions: Butter English muffins and brown slightly in broiler.
Brown ground meat adding spices.
Empty tomato sauce into small bowl, stir in same spices as in meat.
Spoon tomato sauce over English muffins, adding as mush or as little as you want.
Put ground meat on sauce, then top off with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake in oven at 350° for 5 minutes or until cheese is slightly brown and melted.

title: blueberry breakfast cake
directions: Blend shortening and 1/3 cup sugar; add egg and beat well. Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and 1/2 teaspoon nutmeg. Add to shortening mixture, alternately with milk, being careful not to overmix.
Fold in blueberries.
Spread in a greased 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Mix together brown sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and melted butter.
Toss with cereal and sprinkle over batter in pan. Bake in moderately hot oven (400°) about 25 minutes.
Best served warm.

title: passover sponge cake
directions: Beat egg yolks with water, lemon juice and sugar until light and fluffy.
Gradually add cake meal, potato starch and lemon rind; mix well.
Beat egg whites with clean and dry blades until they are stiff (just until they leave peaks when blades are lifted).
Do not overbeat.
Fold into other ingredients very well; do not beat.

title: nut bread
directions: Mix all together; place in greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Brown
chicken in oil.
Remove from pan.
Lightly brown onion, green pepper, garlic and mushrooms.
Return chicken to pan. Combine
tomato
paste with remaining ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Simmer, uncovered, 35 to 45 minutes.

title: cooked frosting
directions: Cook flour and milk to a paste, stirring constantly so it doesn't lump.
When it is thick and leaves sides of the pan, set aside to cool (must be cool).

title: microwave christmas confections
directions: Beat brown sugar, peanut butter and margarine in medium bowl until fluffy.
Blend in egg.
Mix in remaining ingredients and shape in 12-inch roll.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Line microwave baking sheet with waxed paper and place 12 slices on top.
Microwave at Medium-High 1 minute.
Turn, microwave 1 minute, turn microwaving 1 minute.
Let stand 3 minutes, then remove.
Repeat until all slices are baked.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Rinse mushrooms well.
Break stems from caps.
Chop stems; add bread crumbs, cheese, onion, egg and sausage.
Mix together.
Add salt to taste.
Stuff in mushroom caps.
Bake in buttered casserole at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: mike's pork medallions dijon
directions: In frying pan, brown pork in vegetable oil or margarine. Remove to a shallow baking pan.
Into frying pan, mix mustard, preserves and vinegar.
Simmer over low heat for 1 minute.
Pour over chops.
Bake chops for 35 minutes, uncovered, at 325°.
Serve with sliced peaches, arranged on platter.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple and add salt.
Heat juice and add sugar and flour until thickened.
Set aside to cool.
Combine pineapple and marshmallows.
Grate cheese on top.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Dissolve cornstarch in juice.
Combine with apples, salt and spices.
Simmer until thickened.
Pour in pie shells; dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: no-bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, butter, milk and cocoa.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour into long pan and cut, or drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Cool.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1/4 cup nuts.
Lightly grease bottom of baking tube pan for microwave and sprinkle with 1/4 cup nuts.
Pour batter over nuts.
Microwave 10 to 12 minutes on 70% power.
Give dish 1/2 turn 2 times during cooking.
Cool 10 minutes and invert on serving dish.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring to a rolling boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat. Add 1 quart jar marshmallow.
Add peanut butter.
Blend and pour into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.

title: bavarian pot roast
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Dredge pot roast in seasoned flour.
Brown in lard or shortening.
Pour off drippings.
Add remaining ingredients (except water and flour).
Cover tightly and cook slowly 3 to 3 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Take out bay leaf.
Thicken.
Cooking liquid for gravy.

title: chicken breast casserole
directions: Boil chicken; pull off skin and take off meat.
Grate block of cheese.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place pieces of chicken in bottom of pan; cover with grated cheese.
Cover with soup, undiluted.
Cover with stuffing (use more if you'd like).
Add butter to top.
Bake in a 350° oven approximately 30 minutes or until it looks bubbly.
Serve with vegetable and rice or potato. Serves 4 to 5 people.

title: russian salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water; cut cheese into small pieces.
Add marshmallows.
Cook, but do not boil.
Let cool.
Add remainder of ingredients.
Chill until set and serve.

title: fruit punch(weddings and parties)
directions: In large container, mix ingredients with appropriate amount of water for Kool-Aid.
Sweeten to taste.
(Save 7-Up until ready to serve, then pour in bowl to taste.) Place in punch bowl with spoonfuls of sherbet.

title: pepperoni frittata
directions: In medium skillet, saute onion in oil until tender.
Add zucchini (or broccoli) and cauliflower in bowl.
Beat eggs and cheese until blended.
Add pepperoni.
Pour over vegetables in skillet.
Cook over low heat about 15 minutes until set.
When only surface is moist, run skillet under broiler one minute or until surface is set.
Serve from skillet or on a serving plate.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Peel and mash avocados with lemon juice, salt and pepper in a medium bowl.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning in another bowl.

title: spud supreme
directions: Crumble cornflakes and saute in melted butter.
Boil potatoes in skin.
Cool and slice thin in small pieces.
Heat 1/4 cup butter with soup.
Blend in sour cream, cheese and onion.
Bake in 9 x 12-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350° covered.
Sprinkle cornflakes on top and bake 15 more minutes.

title: mexican stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells; set aside. Cook ground beef; drain. Salt and pepper. Add tomato sauce, chillies, picante sauce and 6 ounces cheese. Melt cheese, stirring constantly. Add 8 ounces Durkee onions. Stuff pasta shells with meat mixture.
Top with remaining cheese and onion rings. Heat oven to 350° until bubbly.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream the sugar, butter and eggs well.
Add syrup, vanilla and salt.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Cover with pecans.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: crock-pot candy
directions: Melt chocolate in slow crock-pot.
When completely melted, add box of Bugles, then stir in nuts.
Drop by tablespoonfuls on waxed paper.
Cool and eat.

title: pecan crunch cake
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix and place on buttered pan, 9 x 13-inches cake mix, butter and egg.

title: peppermint popcorn balls
directions: Pop corn in large pan, 1/2 cup at a time, and set aside in large
bowl.
Melt	together over low heat butter, crushed peppermint	 sticks
and
marshmallows.
Pour
over
popcorn. Butter
hands
and make into balls, putting a peppermint stick in each ball.

title: easy coffee cake
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups cake mix with yeast, flour, eggs and 2/3 cup water.
Mix for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons of sugar over batter.
Mix remaining cake mix with butter.
Crumble over filling.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Drizzle with confectioners sugar icing.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with the skins on.
When cool, peel and dice in small pieces.
Add salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Add onion (diced in small pieces) and diced bell pepper.
Mix this all together well.

title: atlanta gas light deviled pecans
directions: Melt butter; add salt, onion salt and chili powder.
Stir in pecans, coating well.
Spread in 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan. Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Drain and cool on paper towels.
Makes 4 cups.

title: amazing raisin cake
directions: Grease and flour 13 x 9 baking pan. In large bowl with mixer at low speed, beat first 10 ingredients 2 minutes or 300 strokes by hand. (Batter will be thick.) With spoon, stir in apples, raisins and nuts. Spoon batter into pan. Bake in 350° oven 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes and remove. Frost with 2 cups whipped cream.

title: apple dip
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients (mix well); bring to a boil. Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with sliced apples.

title: golden ham casserole
directions: Cook potatoes, carrots and celery in boiling unsalted water until tender but crisp.
Drain and set aside.
In 3 tablespoons butter, saute ham, green pepper and onion until ham is golden brown.
Put ham mixture and vegetables in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Melt 1/4 cup butter in heavy saucepan over low heat. Add flour stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly, until thick and bubbly.
Stir in cheese, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat until cheese is melted and slightly thickened.
Pour cheese sauce over ham and vegetables.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over top.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hot potato salad
directions: While still warm, cut potatoes in 1-inch cubes.
Gently toss together potatoes, onions and salad dressing. Dust with paprika and pepper. Garnish with fresh chives. Serve warm or at room temperature.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: easy five vegetable casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter and then add soup.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into 2 1/2-quart greased casserole baking dish. Can sprinkle with more grated cheese if desired.
Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes or until hot.

title: goody bars
directions: Melt margarine, add 1 egg and beat. Add cake mix.
Press into bottom of pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch), lightly greased.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and spices.
Add butter.
Blend in potatoes. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.

title: chuck wagon chow
directions: Put into crock pot.
Cook on low for about 8 hours.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients well and add enough whole milk to fill ice cream freezer.
Freeze in electric ice cream freezer or hand ice cream freezer.

title: mexican salad
directions: Tear lettuce.
Add cheese, beans (washed, drained and chilled), onion and dressing (chilled).
You can add the tomatoes and Fritos, but I usually add them just before serving to keep Fritos crisp.

title: turkey barley soup
directions: Combine all ingredients except peas.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add peas and simmer 5 more minutes.
Contains 150 calories per cup.

title: frozen corn
directions: Mix well.
Let set 5 minutes before putting into bags to freeze.

title: trucker's beans
directions: Brown beef with water (do not drain); place in roaster or very large casserole. Swirl to coat sides with drippings.
Add remaining ingredients and stir to combine well. Do not drain beans. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, uncovered. Makes about 30 servings.

title: chocolate macaroons
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons about 1 inch apart onto well-greased pan.
Press down ends of coconut with back of spoon.
Bake 10 minutes or until brown. Remove from pan.
Cool.

title: baboon butter
directions: Mash together the peanut butter and banana in mixing bowl with fork.
Add cinnamon, coconut and raisins.
Mash again until everything is well blended.

title: confetti cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Stir in gumdrops and nuts.
Drop on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Soften cream cheese. Whip the cream.
Add cherries and liquid. Cut cherries into small pieces.
Add cream and pineapple.
Mix together and freeze.

title: hard teething biscuits
directions: Break eggs into bowl, stir until creamy.
Add sugar and stir. Gradually add flour to make stiff dough.
Roll out between 2 sheets of lightly floured wax paper, 3/4 inch thick.
Cut in round shapes or roll into "snakes" or "donuts."
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Let stand overnight (10 to 12 hours).
Bake at 325° until brown and hard.
Makes about 12 durable and almost crumb-free teething biscuits.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all the ingredients with a spoon. Use 2 tablespoons of oil to grease the pan or your choice of how much oil to grease the pan. Bake until golden brown.

title: yum-yum salad
directions: Mix first four ingredients together well and refrigerate until partially set, then add remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and refrigerate until set.

title: tuna dip
directions: Break tuna into small pieces.
Add sour cream and dressing mix.
Stir until blended.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight. Serve with corn chips.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: artichokes milanese
directions: Heat butter and saute mushrooms until crisp and tender.
Mix bread crumbs, garlic and lemon juice.
Arrange artichokes in buttered, shallow baking dish.
Spoon mushroom mixture over artichokes and sprinkle cheese over all.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: shrimp fettucine
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan.
Add chopped onions, celery and bell pepper.
Cook 10 minutes until clear.
Add flour; blend in well.
Cover and cook 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add chopped parsley and shrimp.
Cook, stirring often, until shrimp are pink.
Add cream, cheese and garlic.
Mix well.
Add salt and pepper.
Cook covered on low heat, stirring until cheese melts. Pour cooked sauce over cooked noodles in 3-quart casserole dish and stir.
Bake in 350° oven until hot.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
(Can use crawfish instead of shrimp.)

title: no fail pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 3 small loaf pans. Cream oleo.
Add sugar; beat well.
Add remaining ingredients. Beat at highest speed for 10 minutes.
Bake 45 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: zucchini and tomato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese, together in a large casserole.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on mixture.
Spread grated Cheddar cheese over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: roast chicken glazed
directions: Cook rice, using chicken broth instead of water.
Saute onion lightly in 3 tablespoons butter.
Add to cooked rice, along with celery, water chestnuts and 2 tablespoons of soy sauce, mix lightly.
Stuff into roasting chicken, skewer openings.
Melt remaining 2 tablespoons butter and brush a little over skin of chicken.
Place chicken in roasting pan, cover loosely with foil and bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: onion sticks
directions: Soften margarine until spreadable.
Mix in soup.
Take crust off bread.
Spread mixture evenly over bread.
Cut each slice into 4 strips.
Bake at 400° until browned and crusty.
Serve hot.

title: modeling candy
directions: Melt candy disks in double boiler or in microwave.
Heat corn syrup over low heat or in microwave until warm, but not hot.
Add corn syrup to melted candy and stir until thoroughly mixed.
Put mixture in an airtight plastic bag for at least 24 hours or up to one week.
Candy becomes easier to work with as it sets.
When ready to use, knead a small amount until it reaches a workable consistency.
(If it's too hard, warm first in microwave on Defrost only just until slightly softened.)
The heat from your hands will cause the candy to become like play dough.
Mold into edible flowers, fruits, whatever!
Candy will "set" again when cool.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour, margarine and pecans.
Press mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: new rolls
directions: Mix water and yeast; then rest of stuff.
Let rise 2 1/2 hours; then make into rolls and let rise again.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: porcupines
directions: Mix all ingredients except tomatoes.
Shape into balls.
Place in baking dish.
Pour tomatoes over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix by package directions.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 1/2 of batter at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: thanksgiving apple cake
directions: Combine
all ingredients in order; spread evenly in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pineapple pudding
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Add beaten egg yolks, pineapple and nuts.
Layer of vanilla wafers.
Layer of pineapple mix.
Cover with Cool Whip.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake mix in two round 9-inch layers.
Cool cake completely.
Prepare instant pudding following box directions. Refrigerate to jell.
Place one layer of cake in bottom of large punch bowl and add in layers: 1/2 pudding, 1/2 pie filling, 1/2 fruit cocktail, 1/2 pineapple, 1/2 cup nuts and 1/2 coconut.
Then add one bowl of Cool Whip.
Repeat the layers, beginning with the other cake layer.
Decorate the cake with cherries, nuts and coconut.

title: morning mix-up
directions: In a large skillet saute potatoes, ham and onion in oil for 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
In a small bowl, beat eggs, salt and pepper.
Add to skillet; cook, stirring occasionally until eggs are set.
Remove from the heat and gently stir in cheese.

title: dill pickles
directions: Use only fresh firm cucumbers.
Wash thoroughly and pack whole or sliced in jars.
Add 1 pod hot pepper, 1 clove garlic and either fresh dill or 1 teaspoon dill seed per jar.

title: brownies for the crowd
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake in an 11 x 15-inch pan at 375° until done. Don't overbake. Frost if desired.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt oleo in dish.
Mix in the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: overnight dinner rolls(chill overnight)
directions: Combine yeast, sugar and warm water and dissolve.
Add melted margarine, milk, egg, salt and part of flour.
Mix until smooth and add rest of flour.
Cover mixture and refrigerate overnight.
Roll or pat out dough to about 1/2-inch thick on a lightly floured board.
Cut out with round cutter or shape into 1 1/2-inch balls. Place close together on greased pan (muffin pan).
Let stand in greased pan about 3 hours or until doubled.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Mix ground beef, rice, salt and chili.
Make into small balls. Brown and place in casserole dish.
Saute onions and pepper.
Add tomato sauce and pour over balls.
Cover and bake in 305° oven for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: oatmeal drop cakes
directions: Blend together the sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add the salt, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg; mix.
Stir in the oatmeal.
Sift together the flour and baking powder.
Stir the soda into the sour milk.
Add the flour and baking powder alternately with the soda and sour milk to the creamed mixture.
Add the raisins and nuts. Drop by teaspoons onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.
These freeze well.

title: baked ziti
directions: In a large bowl, combine ziti, butter and pepper.
Mix well and add 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese and 1/4 cup Romano cheese.
Mix well.

title: lasagna
directions: Place noodles in large pan of boiling water.
Brown ground beef; drain.
Add spaghetti sauce to ground beef.
Simmer until bubbling.
Drain noodles; cool in cold water.
Place 1/2 ground beef in a 10 x 13-inch baking dish.
Put 3 noodles on top of ground beef.
Cover ground beef with 1/2 package of Cheddar and Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat last three steps for second layer. Place in oven at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until cheese has melted.

title: sweet 'n sour chicken
directions: Mix all together, except chicken.
Dip chicken in mixture. Put extra on top and around.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine and cook until sugar dissolves.
One hour before meat is done, baste with sauce.
Continue to baste every 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve meat with the remaining sauce.

title: barry barry pie
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Prepare pie crust according to package directions for unfilled 1-crust pie (refrigerate remaining crust for later use).
Bake at 450° for 9 to 11 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.

title: tuna macaroni salad
directions: Mix dressing, macaroni, tuna, celery, green pepper, onions and pimento.
Season to taste with salt and black pepper. Refrigerate.
Serve on lettuce lined plate.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken on the ritz casserole
directions: Boil chicken; cut up and layer in 10 x 14-inch dish.
Mix sour cream and soup.
Spoon over chicken.
Crush Ritz crackers over top of mixture.
Melt butter and pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sicilian-style meatballs and fettuccine
directions: Cook fettuccine to desired doneness as directed on package; drain.
Keep warm.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Pour crushed pineapple in a sheet cake pan.
Add pie filling. Sprinkle with the cake mix.
Melt butter and pour over the cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serve with or without whipped topping.

title: jacques junque
directions: Heat oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Saute onion and green pepper.
Add seafood and sprinkle with herbs, celery seed, salt and pepper.
Add clam juice, wine and cream.
Simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Put mustard and arrowroot in a cup.
Add 1/2 cup sauce from pan.
Blend and return to pan, stirring until thick.
Do not boil.
Serve over rice.
Makes 10 servings.

title: southern oatmeal
directions: Mix oats and raisins in square baking pan. Add enough milk so that mixture is
covered.
Refrigerate overnight.
The next morning, peel and grate apple.
Mix into oats.
Add enough Cool Whip to make mixture creamy.

title: bean soup
directions: Bring water and ham to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add beans and simmer 1 hour.
Stir in potatoes and all else.
Cook 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve with warm cheese bread.

title: strawberry fruit salad
directions: Mix hot water and Jell-O together and put in ice cubes and let jell.
Drain pineapples and slice bananas and apples into juice (will help them from turning brown).
Mix the remaining ingredients together.

title: chicken
directions: Place both Cup-a-Soups, cream of mushroom soup and 1 cup boiling water in a bowl and mix.
Add 3/4 can of boiling water. Mix thoroughly.
Place 2 cups Minute rice in pan to use in microwave; pour liquid mixture over rice.
Cover tightly and let stand for 5 minutes.
Place chicken parts on rice mixture; sprinkle top of chicken with paprika.
Cover tightly.
Microwave on 40% power for 35 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, cook onions and water; bring to boil. Add all other ingredients.
Simmer, covered, about 20 minutes, until onions are tender.

title: home-style banana bread(diabetic)
directions: Banana bread is a welcome addition to any meal.

title: calico bean salad
directions: Fry bacon, hamburger and onion. When cooked, drain. Stir in all beans, ketchup, mustard, vinegar, brown sugar and chili powder. Pour in casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: perfect turkey in 1 hour
directions: Rub salt and oleo into turkey inside and out.
Cut celery, onion and apple into medium pieces and stuff into turkey cavity. Place turkey into pan with hot water.
Cover pan tightly and place in a preheated 450° oven for 1 hour.
Important:
Do not open oven, leave overnight.

title: baked stuffed flounder
directions: Season fish and place in shallow baking pan.
Melt butter, add seasonings and cook until wilted.
Add shrimp and crabmeat and season to taste.
Cook until shrimp are pink.
Add enough bread crumbs to hold stuffing together.
Stuff each fish with a mound of stuffing.
Dot with butter and bake at 350 degrees until fish flakes with a fork. This recipe may also be prepared with red snapper or redfish.

title: cream of coconut cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed on package.
Bake in a large Pyrex dish.
Remove from oven when done and make holes in entire cake with a spoon.
While cake is hot, pour can of milk and cream of coconut over top of cake, allowing it to fill holes.
Cool 3 to 4 hours.
Spread with Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut. Refrigerate for keeping.

title: gumbo
directions: Saute okra,
onion, garlic and green peppers in oil and butter.
Sprinkle with flour and continue cooking until brown; keep
turning.
Add tomatoes, broth, water, bay leaves, thyme, Tabasco,
Worcestershire
and
salt.
Cover
and simmer for 45 minutes.
Add shrimp.
Cook 5 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: black raspberry squares
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Beat the yolks, vanilla and milk together.
Add yolk mixture to flour mixture and mix well.
Let stand in refrigerator for one hour.
Roll 2/3 chilled dough out and lay on a greased cookie sheet.
Put 1 1/2 to 2 cans Thank You brand black raspberry or blackberry filling on top; take remaining dough and cut in strips to crisscross top.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: barbecued meat balls
directions: Mix ground beef, bread crumbs, milk and salt.
Shape into small balls and place in baking dish.
Mix catsup, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, sugar, onion and hot sauce.
Pour over meat balls.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: quick 'n easy cheese muffins
directions: Whisk flour and milk together.
Add mayonnaise, salt and cheese.
Spray muffin tins with Pam.
Bake 20 minutes in a 375° oven.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: fast brownies
directions: Beat eggs with mixer.
Add other ingredients with spoon and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: french toast
directions: Combine eggs, milk and salt.
Dip bread in milk and egg mixture.
Fry in small amount of hot oil.

title: banana nut cake with icing
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks.
Combine milk and vanilla.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Alternately add to butter mixture.
Pour into 10 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In 1-quart casserole, stir soup, milk and soy sauce until smooth.
Mix in 1/2 can onions, beans and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbling.
Top with remaining onions. Bake 5 minutes more.
Serves 6.

title: herbed beef-n-vegetable stew
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Coat meat.
Shake off excess.
Heat oil in 5-quart Dutch oven on medium-high heat.
Brown \beef in 2 or 3 batches.
Return all meat to pot.
Stir in tomatoes, broth, garlic, herbs, pepper and bay leaves.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover. Simmer 1 1/2 hours, stirring 3 or 4 times.
Add carrots, mushrooms, green beans, celery and parsley.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes longer, stirring once or twice until meat and vegetables are tender.
Makes 12 cups (8 servings).

title: easy pecan pie
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Stir in pecans.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Outer edge of filling should be set, center slightly soft.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Gradually add flour to mixture until an elastic dough is formed.
Knead on a floured board approximately 3 to 5 minutes. Place in a lightly oiled bowl to rise for 1 hour.
Allow 1 hour to rise, then shape and rise again for 1 hour.
Then bake, if desired.

title: meat loaf for 50 people
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk.
Add meat, eggs, onion and seasonings.
Mix well.
Form into loaves in 6 loaf pans.
Cover with Piquant Sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple dumpling cake
directions: Beat together eggs, oil, and sugar. Sift together flour, cinnamon, soda and salt. Stir
all together. Gently fold pie filling. Pour into 13 x 9 cake pan and bake at 350 degrees for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cut chicken to the best of your knowledge.
Cook chicken in large pot of water.
Remove scum from top as chicken cooks.
Add water as needed.
Remove chicken.
Add onions to boiling broth. Flatten biscuits by hand (flour hands to keep biscuits from sticking to hands).
Add to broth.
Stir so biscuits won't stick together.
Cook until biscuits are done.
Add water as needed. Don't let biscuits stick to the bottom of pot.
They sink when done.
Lower heat.
By now chicken has cooled enough to skin and bone.
Do it.
Stir into dumplings; salt and pepper to taste. Serves 5 to 6.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: pipi kaula(hawaiian dried beef)
directions: Pound steak to 1/4-inch thick with mallet and cut into 4 x 1-inch strips. Arrange strips in large baking dish. Combine soy sauce, sherry, minced onion, ginger and garlic in small bowl. Pour over meat.
Refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.

title: sausage bites
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Combine sausage, buttermilk mix and bourbon in a mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Form 1-inch balls and place on rack on cookie sheet, so that sausage fat drains.
Bake 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from rack immediately.
Serves about 60.

title: saltless salt
directions: Add zip to salads, meat, poultry and vegetables.
Mix your own blend of saltless seasoning!
This is an excellent salt alternative for those people on low sodium diets.

title: chicken with dressing
directions: Place chicken breasts in 9 x 13 pan. Salt and pepper to taste. Place 1 piece of cheese on each piece. Cover with undiluted chicken soup and sherry or wine. Cover with aluminum foil. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Serves 8.

title: bacon, onion, broccoli sauté
directions: In large pot of boiling salted water, cook broccoli until tender, 5 to 6 minutes; drain.
Meanwhile in nonstick skillet over medium-high heat, cook bacon until crisp.
Drain on paper towel.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburg and follow directions on taco seasoning mix. Just before serving, combine with rest of ingredients.
Decorate top with tomatoes and chips.

title: cheesy green beans
directions: Cook the bacon until crisp.
Drain and reserve 1/4 cup drippings. Crumble bacon; reserve 2 tablespoons.

title: beau monde dip
directions: Mix well.
Serve with raw vegetables.
Best if set overnight.

title: dirt pie
directions: *For rocks you can use chocolate chips, peanut butter chips, M&M's, crushed Heath bar, granola, Reese's pieces, etc.

title: buttermilk bread
directions: Soften yeast in water.
Add buttermilk, sugar, salt and baking soda.
Mix. Add 3 cups of the flour.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in butter.
Add remaining flour to make a light dough.
Turn onto lightly floured board.
Knead for about 8 minutes, or until smooth and elastic.
Place dough in greased bowl, turning dough to grease all surfaces; cover; let rise for about 1 1/2 hours, or until doubled in bulk.

title: beef-noodle soup
directions: Combine beef, salt and water in a large pan; simmer, covered, about 2 hours, until meat is tender.
Skim off excess fat; remove bones.
Separate meat into small pieces.
Add bouillon and celery; cover.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in noodles; cover. Simmer 7 to 10 minutes until noodles and celery are tender.
Add a little hot water if thinner soup is desired.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: pink paradise
directions: Mix in order: Cool Whip, sour cream and jello (dry).
Mix well until all pink.
Then add pineapple and oranges.
When all blended, add slivered almonds.

title: sausage stromboli
directions: Let dough rise, then roll out like pizza dough.
Saute onion and peppers.
Brown sausage; drain.
Place sausage, onion and peppers on top of dough.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Roll up and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: harvest casserole
directions: Saute ground beef and onion; drain fat.
Saute celery in small amount of margarine over low heat.
Mix all ingredients and spoon into 1 large casserole or several small ones.
Bake in preheated 350° oven until bubbly.
This casserole freezes well either before or after baking.

title: ground turkey delight
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
Mixture can be used for meatballs or your favorite pasta dish, or it can be used for burgers on the grill or on the stove.
Cook in your selected method (grill or stove).
They are simply great and are a healthy change for those unable to eat beef!!!

title: rice with green chilies
directions: In a bowl, combine rice with the sour cream and salt.
Arrange half of mixture in bottom of 1-quart casserole.

Layer green chilies on top of rice mixture, then cheese strips. Add the remaining rice mixture and dot the top with butter and the grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until cheese is melted and bubbly. Serves 4.

title: deer or beef jerky
directions: Soak beef or deer 24 hours. Cook on slow oven at 120° for 12 hours with door slightly ajar.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Pour into pie shells and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: dry jello salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.
Any fruit and flavor of Jell-O may be used.

title: grandma collyer's chewy ranger cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add the remaining ingredients, mixing in order.
Mix and drop on greased cookie sheets.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
